  line `13. Explanation ins. by s. 22, ibid., (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (809)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 35
  title `Submission of resolution plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=809&sectionno=30&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) A resolution applicant may submit a resolution plan ^1[along`
  line `with an affidavit stating that he is eligible under section 29A] to the resolution professional prepared on`
  line `the basis of the information memorandum.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional shall examine each resolution plan received by him to confirm that`
  line `each resolution plan--`
  line
  line `(a) provides for the payment of insolvency resolution process costs in a manner specified by the`
  line `Board in priority to the ^2[payment] of other debts of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `^3[(b) provides for the payment of debts of operational creditors in such manner as may be`
  line `specified by the Board which shall not be less than--`
  line
  line `(i) the amount to be paid to such creditors in the event of a liquidation of the corporate debtor`
  line `under section 53; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount that would have been paid to such creditors, if the amount to be distributed`
  line `under the resolution plan had been distributed in accordance with the order of priority in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 53,`
  line
  line `whichever is higher and provides for the payment of debts of financial creditors, who do not vote in`
  line `favour of the resolution plan, in such manner as may be specified by the Board, which shall not be`
  line `less than the amount to be paid to such creditors in accordance with sub-section (1) of section 53 in`
  line `the event of a liquidation of the corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that a distribution in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this clause shall be fair and equitable to such creditors.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.-- For the purposes of this clause, it is hereby declared that on and from the`
  line `date of commencement of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (Amendment) Act, 2019, the`
  line `provisions of this clause shall also apply to the corporate insolvency resolution process of a`
  line `corporate debtor--`
  line
  line `(i) where a resolution plan has not been approved or rejected by the Adjudicating`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(ii) where an appeal has been preferred under section 61 or section 62 or such an appeal`
  line `is not time barred under any provision of law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where a legal proceeding has been initiated in any court against the decision of the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority in respect of a resolution plan;]`
  line
  line `(c) provides for the management of the affairs of the Corporate debtor after approval of the`
  line `resolution plan;`
  line
  line `(d) the implementation and supervision of the resolution plan;`
  line
  line `(e) does not contravene any of the provisions of the law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(f) conforms to such other requirements as may be specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (e), if any approval of shareholders is required under`
  line `the Companies Act, 2013 or any other law for the time being in force for the implementation of actions`
  line `under the resolution plan, such approval shall be deemed to have been given and it shall not be a`
  line `contravention of that Act or law];`
  line
  line `(3) The resolution professional shall present to the committee of creditors for its approval such`
  line `resolution plans which confirm the conditions referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `^5[(4) The committee of creditors may approve a resolution plan by a vote of not less than ^6[sixty-six]`
  line `per cent. of voting share of the financial creditors, after considering its feasibility and viability, ^7[the`
  line `manner of distribution proposed, which may take into account the order of priority amongst creditors as`
  line `laid down in sub-section (1) of section 53, including the priority and value of the security interest of a`
  line `secured creditor] and such other requirements as may be specified by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the committee of creditors shall not approve a resolution plan, submitted before the`
  line `commencement of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (Amendment) Ordinance, 2017(Ord. 7 of 2017),`
  line `where the resolution applicant is ineligible under section 29A and may require the resolution professional`
  line `to invite a fresh resolution plan where no other resolution plan is available with it:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the resolution applicant referred to in the first proviso is ineligible under`
  line `clause (c) of section 29A, the resolution applicant shall be allowed by the committee of creditors such`
  line `period, not exceeding thirty days, to make payment of overdue amounts in accordance with the proviso to`
  line `clause (c) of section 29A:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing in the second proviso shall be construed as extension of period for the`
  line `purposes of the proviso to sub-section (3) of section 12, and the corporate insolvency resolution process`
  line `shall be completed within the period specified in that sub-section.]`
  line
  line `^8[Provided also that the eligibility criteria in section 29A as amended by the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code (Amendment) Ordinance, 2018 shall apply to the resolution applicant who has not`
  line `submitted resolution plan as on the date of commencement of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code`
  line `(Amendment) Ordinance, 2018.]`
  line
  line `(5) The resolution applicant may attend the meeting of the committee of creditors in which the`
  line `resolution plan of the applicant is considered:`
  line
  line `Provided that the resolution applicant shall not have a right to vote at the meeting of the committee of`
  line `creditors unless such resolution applicant is also a financial creditor.`
  line
  line `(6) The resolution professional shall submit the resolution plan as approved by the committee of`
  line `creditors to the Adjudicating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for "repayment" (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 2019, s. 6, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 8 of 2018, s. 6, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 23-11-2017).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 26 of 2018, s., 23, for "seventy-five" (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 26 of 2019, s. 6 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (810)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 36
  title `Approval of resolution plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=810&sectionno=31&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Adjudicating Authority is satisfied that the resolution`
  line `plan as approved by the committee of creditors under sub-section (4) of section 30 meets the requirements`
  line `as referred to in sub-section (2) of section 30, it shall by order approve the resolution plan which shall be`
  line `binding on the corporate debtor and its employees, members, creditors, ^1[including the Central`
  line `Government, any State Government or any local authority to whom a debt in respect of the payment of`
  line `dues arising under any law for the time being in force, such as authorities to whom statutory dues are`
  line `owed,] guarantors and other stakeholders involved in the resolution plan.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the Adjudicating Authority shall, before passing an order for approval of resolution`
  line `plan under this sub-section, satisfy that the resolution plan has provisions for its effective`
  line implementation.]
  line
  line `(2) Where the Adjudicating Authority is satisfied that the resolution plan does not confirm to the`
  line `requirements referred to in sub-section (1), it may, by an order, reject the resolution plan.`
  line `(3) After the order of approval under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the moratorium order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under section 14 shall cease to`
  line `have effect; and`
  line
  line `(b) the resolution professional shall forward all records relating to the conduct of the corporate`
  line `insolvency resolution process and the resolution plan to the Board to be recorded on its database.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The resolution applicant shall, pursuant to the resolution plan approved under sub-section (1),`
  line `obtain the necessary approval required under any law for the time being in force within a period of one`
  line `year from the date of approval of the resolution plan by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (1)`
  line `or within such period as provided for in such law, whichever is later:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the resolution plan contains a provision for combination, as referred to in section`
  line `5 of the Competition Act, 2002 (12 of 2003), the resolution applicant shall obtain the approval of the`
  line `Competition Commission of India under that Act prior to the approval of such resolution plan by the`
  line `committee of creditors.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2019, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 24 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (811)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 37
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=811&sectionno=32&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Any appeal from an order approving the resolution plan shall be in the manner and on`
  line `the grounds laid down in sub-section (3) of section 61.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (49831)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 38
  title `Liability for prior offences, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2020, s. 10 (w.e.f. 28-12-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=49831&sectionno=32A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Liability for prior offences, etc.--(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `this Code or any other law for the time being in force, the liability of a corporate debtor for an offence`
  line `committed prior to the commencement of the corporate insolvency resolution process shall cease, and the`
  line `corporate debtor shall not be prosecuted for such an offence from the date the resolution plan has been`
  line `approved by the Adjudicating Authority under section 31, if the resolution plan results in the change in`
  line `the management or control of the corporate debtor to a person who was not--`
  line
  line `(a) a promoter or in the management or control of the corporate debtor or a related party of such a`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(b) a person with regard to whom the relevant investigating authority has, on the basis of material`
  line `in its possession, reason to believe that he had abetted or conspired for the commission of the offence,`
  line `and has submitted or filed a report or a complaint to the relevant statutory authority or Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a prosecution had been instituted during the corporate insolvency resolution`
  line `process against such corporate debtor, it shall stand discharged from the date of approval of the`
  line `resolution plan subject to requirements of this sub-section having been fulfilled:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every person who was a designated partner as defined in clause (j) of`
  line `section 2 of the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), or an officer who is in default,`
  line `as defined in clause (60) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), or was in any manner`
  line `incharge of, or responsible to the corporate debtor for the conduct of its business or associated with`
  line `the corporate debtor in any manner and who was directly or indirectly involved in the commission of`
  line `such offence as per the report submitted or complaint filed by the investigating authority, shall`
  line `continue to be liable to be prosecuted and punished for such an offence committed by the corporate`
  line `debtor notwithstanding that the corporate debtor's liability has ceased under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) No action shall be taken against the property of the corporate debtor in relation to an offence`
  line `committed prior to the commencement of the corporate insolvency resolution process of the corporate`
  line `debtor, where such property is covered under a resolution plan approved by the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `under section 31, which results in the change in control of the corporate debtor to a person, or sale of`
  line `liquidation assets under the provisions of Chapter III of Part II of this Code to a person, who was not--`
  line
  line `(i) a promoter or in the management or control of the corporate debtor or a related party of such a`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a person with regard to whom the relevant investigating authority has, on the basis of material`
  line `in its possession reason to believe that he had abetted or conspired for the commission of the offence,`
  line `and has submitted or filed a report or a complaint to the relevant statutory authority or Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, it is hereby clarified that,--`
  line
  line `(i) an action against the property of the corporate debtor in relation to an offence shall include`
  line `the attachment, seizure, retention or confiscation of such property under such law as may be`
  line `applicable to the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(ii) nothing in this sub-section shall be construed to bar an action against the property of any`
  line `person, other than the corporate debtor or a person who has acquired such property through`
  line `corporate insolvency resolution process or liquidation process under this Code and fulfils the`
  line `requirements specified in this section, against whom such an action may be taken under such law`
  line `as may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), and notwithstanding the immunity`
  line `given in this section, the corporate debtor and any person who may be required to provide assistance`
  line `under such law as may be applicable to such corporate debtor or person, shall extend all assistance and`
  line `co-operation to any authority investigating an offence committed prior to the commencement of the`
  line `corporate insolvency resolution process.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (812)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 39
  title `Initiation of liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=812&sectionno=33&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Adjudicating Authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) before the expiry of the insolvency resolution process period or the maximum period`
  line `permitted for completion of the corporate insolvency resolution process under section 12 or the fast`
  line `track corporate insolvency resolution process under section 56, as the case may be, does not receive a`
  line `resolution plan under sub-section (6) of section 30; or`
  line
  line `(b) rejects the resolution plan under section 31 for the non-compliance of the requirements`
  line `specified therein,`
  line `it shall--`
  line
  line `(i) pass an order requiring the corporate debtor to be liquidated in the manner as laid down in this`
  line Chapter;
  line
  line `(ii) issue a public announcement stating that the corporate debtor is in liquidation; and`
  line
  line `(iii) require such order to be sent to the authority with which the corporate debtor is registered.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the resolution professional, at any time during the corporate insolvency resolution process`
  line `but before confirmation of resolution plan, intimates the Adjudicating Authority of the decision of the`
  line `committee of creditors ^1[approved by not less than sixty-six per cent. of the voting share] to liquidate the`
  line `corporate debtor, the Adjudicating Authority shall pass a liquidation order as referred to in sub-clauses (i),`
  line `(ii) and (iii) of clause (b) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, it is hereby declared that the committee of`
  line `creditors may take the decision to liquidate the corporate debtor, any time after its constitution under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21 and before the confirmation of the resolution plan, including at any time`
  line `before the preparation of the information memorandum.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where the resolution plan approved by the Adjudicating Authority ^3[under section 31 or under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 54L,]is contravened by the`
  line `concerned corporate debtor, any person other than the corporate debtor, whose interests are prejudicially`
  line `affected by such contravention, may make an application to the Adjudicating Authority for a liquidation`
  line `order as referred to in sub-clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) of clause (b) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an application under sub-section (3), if the Adjudicating Authority determines that`
  line `the corporate debtor has contravened the provisions of the resolution plan, it shall pass a liquidation order`
  line `as referred to in sub-clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) of clause (b) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to section 52, when a liquidation order has been passed, no suit or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall be instituted by or against the corporate debtor:`
  line
  line `Provided that a suit or other legal proceeding may be instituted by the liquidator, on behalf of the`
  line `corporate debtor, with the prior approval of the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of sub-section (5) shall not apply to legal proceedings in relation to such`
  line `transactions as may be notified by the Central Government in consultation with any financial sector`
  line regulator.
  line
  line `(7) The order for liquidation under this section shall be deemed to be a notice of discharge to the`
  line `officers, employees and workmen of the corporate debtor, except when the business of the corporate`
  line `debtor is continued during the liquidation process by the liquidator.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 25 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 26 of 2019, s. 8 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3.Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 6 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (813)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 40
  title `Appointment of liquidator and fee to be paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=813&sectionno=34&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Adjudicating Authority passes`
  line `an order for liquidation of the corporate debtor under section 33, the resolution professional appointed for`
  line `the corporate insolvency resolution process under ^1 [Chapter II ^2[or for the pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process under Chapter III-A] shall subject to submission of a written consent by the resolution professional to the Adjudicatory Authority in specified form,] act as the liquidator for the purposes of`
  line `liquidation unless replaced by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(2) On the appointment of a liquidator under this section, all powers of the board of directors, key`
  line `managerial personnel and the partners of the corporate debtor, as the case may be, shall cease to have`
  line `effect and shall be vested in the liquidator.`
  line
  line `(3) The personnel of the corporate debtor shall extend all assistance and cooperation to the liquidator`
  line `as may be required by him in managing the affairs of the corporate debtor and provisions of section 19`
  line `shall apply in relation to voluntary liquidation process as they apply in relation to liquidation process with`
  line `the substitution of references to the liquidator for references to the interim resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(4) The Adjudicating Authority shall by order replace the resolution professional, if`
  line
  line `(a) the resolution plan submitted by the resolution professional under section 30 was rejected for`
  line `failure to meet the requirements mentioned in sub-section (2) of section 30; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Board recommends the replacement of a resolution professional to the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority for reasons to be recorded ^3`
  line `[in writing; or]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(c) the resolution professional fails to submit written consent under sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of ^5`
  line `[clauses (a) and (c)] of sub-section (4), the Adjudicating Authority may direct`
  line `the Board to propose the name of another insolvency professional to be appointed as a liquidator. .`
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall propose the name of another insolvency professional ^4`
  line `[along with written consent`
  line `from the insolvency professional in the specified form,] within ten days of the direction issued by the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) The Adjudicating Authority shall, on receipt of the proposal of the Board for the appointment of`
  line `an insolvency professional as liquidator, by an order appoint such insolvency professional as the`
  line liquidator.
  line
  line `(8) An insolvency professional proposed to be appointed as a liquidator shall charge such fee for the`
  line `conduct of the liquidation proceedings and in such proportion to the value of the liquidation estate assets,`
  line `as may be specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(9) The fees for the conduct of the liquidation proceedings under sub-section (8) shall be paid to the`
  line `liquidator from the proceeds of the liquidation estate under section 53.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 26, ibid, for Chapter II shall (w.e.f 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 7 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 26, for in writing (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by s. 26, ibid (w.e.f 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `5 Subs. by s. 26, ibid, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (814)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 41
  title `Powers and duties of liquidator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1 The proviso ins. by Act 8 of 2018, s. 7 (w.e.f. 23-11-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=814&sectionno=35&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the directions of the Adjudicating Authority,`
  line `the liquidator shall have the following powers and duties, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to verify claims of all the creditors;`
  line
  line `(b) to take into his custody or control all the assets, property, effects and actionable claims of the`
  line `corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(c) to evaluate the assets and property of the corporate debtor in the manner as may be specified`
  line `by the Board and prepare a report;`
  line
  line `(d) to take such measures to protect and preserve the assets and properties of the corporate debtor`
  line `as he considers necessary;`
  line
  line `(e) to carry on the business of the corporate debtor for its beneficial liquidation as he considers`
  line necessary;
  line
  line `(f) subject to section 52, to sell the immovable and movable property and actionable claims of the`
  line `corporate debtor in liquidation by public auction or private contract, with power to transfer such`
  line `property to any person or body corporate, or to sell the same in parcels in such manner as may be`
  line specified;
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that the liquidator shall not sell the immovable and movable property or actionable`
  line `claims of the corporate debtor in liquidation to any person who is not eligible to be a resolution`
  line applicant].
  line
  line `(g) to draw, accept, make and endorse any negotiable instruments including bill of exchange,`
  line `hundi or promissory note in the name and on behalf of the corporate debtor, with the same effect with`
  line `respect to the liability as if such instruments were drawn, accepted, made or endorsed by or on behalf`
  line `of the corporate debtor in the ordinary course of its business;`
  line
  line `(h) to take out, in his official name, letter of administration to any deceased contributory and to`
  line `do in his official name any other act necessary for obtaining payment of any money due and payable`
  line `from a contributory or his estate which cannot be ordinarily done in the name of the corporate debtor,`
  line `and in all such cases, the money due and payable shall, for the purpose of enabling the liquidator to`
  line `take out the letter of administration or recover the money, be deemed to be due to the liquidator`
  line himself;
  line
  line `(i) to obtain any professional assistance from any person or appoint any professional, in discharge`
  line `of his duties, obligations and responsibilities;`
  line
  line `(j) to invite and settle claims of creditors and claimants and distribute proceeds in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Code;`
  line
  line `(k) to institute or defend any suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings, civil or criminal, in the`
  line `name of on behalf of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(l) to investigate the financial affairs of the corporate debtor to determine undervalued or`
  line `preferential transactions;`
  line
  line `(m) to take all such actions, steps, or to sign, execute and verify any paper, deed, receipt`
  line `document, application, petition, affidavit, bond or instrument and for such purpose to use the common`
  line `seal, if any, as may be necessary for liquidation, distribution of assets and in discharge of his duties`
  line `and obligations and functions as liquidator;`
  line
  line `(n) to apply to the Adjudicating Authority for such orders or directions as may be necessary for`
  line `the liquidation of the corporate debtor and to report the progress of the liquidation process in a`
  line `manner as may be specified by the Board; and`
  line
  line `(o) to perform such other functions as may be specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The liquidator shall have the power to consult any of the stakeholders entitled to a distribution of`
  line `proceeds under section 53:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such consultation shall not be binding on the liquidator:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the records of any such consultation shall be made available to all other`
  line `stakeholders not so consulted, in a manner specified by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (815)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 42
  title `Liquidation estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=815&sectionno=36&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of liquidation, the liquidator shall form an estate of the`
  line `assets mentioned in sub-section (3), which will be called the liquidation estate in relation to the corporate`
  line debtor.
  line
  line `(2) The liquidator shall hold the liquidation estate as a fiduciary for the benefit of all the creditors.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to sub-section (4), the liquidation estate shall comprise all liquidation estate assets which`
  line `shall include the following:—`
  line
  line `(a) any assets over which the corporate debtor has ownership rights, including all rights and`
  line `interests therein as evidenced in the balance sheet of the corporate debtor or an information utility or`
  line `records in the registry or any depository recording securities of the corporate debtor or by any other`
  line `means as may be specified by the Board, including shares held in any subsidiary of the corporate`
  line debtor;
  line
  line `(b) assets that may or may not be in possession of the corporate debtor including but not limited`
  line `to encumbered assets;`
  line
  line `(c) tangible assets, whether movable or immovable;`
  line
  line `(d) intangible assets including but not limited to intellectual property, securities (including shares`
  line `held in a subsidiary of the corporate debtor) and financial instruments, insurance policies, contractual`
  line rights;
  line
  line `(e) assets subject to the determination of ownership by the court or authority;`
  line
  line `(f) any assets or their value recovered through proceedings for avoidance of transactions in`
  line `accordance with this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(g) any asset of the corporate debtor in respect of which a secured creditor has relinquished`
  line `security interest;`
  line
  line `(h) any other property belonging to or vested in the corporate debtor at the insolvency`
  line `commencement date; and`
  line
  line `(i) all proceeds of liquidation as and when they are realised.`
  line
  line `(4) The following shall not be included in the liquidation estate assets and shall not be used for`
  line `recovery in the liquidation:—`
  line
  line `(a) assets owned by a third party which are in possession of the corporate debtor, including—`
  line
  line `(i) assets held in trust for any third party;`
  line
  line `(ii) bailment contracts;`
  line
  line `(iii) all sums due to any workman or employee from the provident fund, the pension fund and`
  line `the gratuity fund;`
  line
  line `(iv) other contractual arrangements which do not stipulate transfer of title but only use of the`
  line `assets; and`
  line
  line `(v) such other assets as may be notified by the Central Government in consultation with any`
  line `financial sector regulator;`
  line
  line `(b) assets in security collateral held by financial services providers and are subject to netting and`
  line `set-off in multi-lateral trading or clearing transactions;`
  line
  line `(c) personal assets of any shareholder or partner of a corporate debtor as the case may be`
  line `provided such assets are not held on account of avoidance transactions that may be avoided under this`
  line Chapter;
  line
  line `(d) assets of any Indian or foreign subsidiary of the corporate debtor; or`
  line
  line `(e) any other assets as may be specified by the Board, including assets which could be subject to`
  line `set-off on account of mutual dealings between the corporate debtor and any creditor.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (816)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 43
  title `Powers of liquidator to access information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=816&sectionno=37&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the liquidator shall have the power to access any information`
  line `systems for the purpose of admission and proof of claims and identification of the liquidation estate assets`
  line `relating to the corporate debtor from the following sources, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) an information utility;`
  line
  line `(b) credit information systems regulated under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(c) any agency of the Central, State or Local Government including any registration authorities;`
  line
  line `(d) information systems for financial and non-financial liabilities regulated under any law for the`
  line `time being in force;`
  line
  line `(e) information systems for securities and assets posted as security interest regulated under any`
  line `law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(f) any database maintained by the Board; and`
  line
  line `(g) any other source as may be specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The creditors may require the liquidator to provide them any financial information relating to the`
  line `corporate debtor in such manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The liquidator shall provide information referred to in sub-section (2) to such creditors who have`
  line `requested for such information within a period of seven days from the date of such request or provide`
  line `reasons for not providing such information.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (817)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 44
  title `Consolidation of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=817&sectionno=38&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liquidator shall receive or collect the claims of creditors`
  line `within a period of thirty days from the date of the commencement of the liquidation process.`
  line
  line `(2) A financial creditor may submit a claim to the liquidator by providing a record of such claim with`
  line `an information utility:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the information relating to the claim is not recorded in the information utility, the`
  line `financial creditor may submit the claim in the same manner as provided for the submission of claims for`
  line `the operational creditor under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) An operational creditor may submit a claim to the liquidator in such form and in such manner and`
  line `along with such supporting documents required to prove the claim as may be specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) A creditor who is partly a financial creditor and partly an operational creditor shall submit claims`
  line `to the liquidator to the extent of his financial debt in the manner as provided in sub-section (2) and to the`
  line `extent of his operational debt under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) A creditor may withdraw or vary his claim under this section within fourteen days of its`
  line submission.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (818)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 45
  title `Verification of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=818&sectionno=39&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liquidator shall verify the claims submitted under section 38`
  line `within such time as specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The liquidator may require any creditor or the corporate debtor or any other person to produce any`
  line `other document or evidence which he thinks necessary for the purpose of verifying the whole or any part`
  line `of the claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (819)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 46
  title `Admission or rejection of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=819&sectionno=40&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liquidator may, after verification of claims under`
  line `section 39, either admit or reject the claim, in whole or in part, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the liquidator rejects a claim, he shall record in writing the reasons for such`
  line rejection.
  line
  line `(2) The liquidator shall communicate his decision of admission or rejection of claims to the creditor`
  line `and corporate debtor within seven days of such admission or rejection of claims.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (820)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 47
  title `Determination of valuation of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=820&sectionno=41&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The liquidator shall determine the value of claims`
  line `admitted under section 40 in such manner as may be specified by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (821)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 48
  title `Appeal against the decision of liquidator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 27 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=821&sectionno=42&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `A creditor may appeal to the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority against the decision of the liquidator ^1`
  line `[accepting or] rejecting the claims within fourteen days of`
  line `the receipt of such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (822)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 49
  title `Preferential transactions and relevant time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=822&sectionno=43&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the liquidator or the resolution`
  line `professional, as the case may be, is of the opinion that the corporate debtor has at a relevant time given a`
  line `preference in such transactions and in such manner as laid down in sub-section (2) to any persons as`
  line `referred to in sub-section (4), he shall apply to the Adjudicating Authority for avoidance of preferential`
  line `transactions and for, one or more of the orders referred to in section 44.`
  line
  line `(2) A corporate debtor shall be deemed to have given a preference, if—`
  line
  line `(a) there is a transfer of property or an interest thereof of the corporate debtor for the benefit of a`
  line `creditor or a surety or a guarantor for or on account of an antecedent financial debt or operational debt`
  line `or other liabilities owed by the corporate debtor; and`
  line
  line `(b) the transfer under clause (a) has the effect of putting such creditor or a surety or a guarantor in`
  line `a beneficial position than it would have been in the event of a distribution of assets being made in`
  line `accordance with section 53.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-section (2), a preference shall not include the following transfers—`
  line
  line `(a) transfer made in the ordinary course of the business or financial affairs of the corporate debtor`
  line `or the transferee;`
  line
  line `(b) any transfer creating a security interest in property acquired by the corporate debtor to the`
  line `extent that—`
  line
  line `(i) such security interest secures new value and was given at the time of or after the signing of`
  line `a security agreement that contains a description of such property as security interest and was used`
  line `by corporate debtor to acquire such property; and`
  line
  line `(ii) such transfer was registered with an information utility on or before thirty days after the`
  line `corporate debtor receives possession of such property:`
  line
  line `Provided that any transfer made in pursuance of the order of a court shall not, preclude such transfer`
  line `to be deemed as giving of preference by the corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of sub-section (3) of this section, "new value" means money or its`
  line `worth in goods, services, or new credit, or release by the transferee of property previously transferred to`
  line `such transferee in a transaction that is neither void nor voidable by the liquidator or the resolution`
  line `professional under this Code, including proceeds of such property, but does not include a financial debt or`
  line `operational debt substituted for existing financial debt or operational debt.`
  line
  line `(4) A preference shall be deemed to be given at a relevant time, if—`
  line
  line `(a) it is given to a related party (other than by reason only of being an employee), during the`
  line `period of two years preceding the insolvency commencement date; or`
  line
  line `(b) a preference is given to a person other than a related party during the period of one year`
  line `preceding the insolvency commencement date.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (823)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 50
  title `Orders in case of preferential transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=823&sectionno=44&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Adjudicating Authority, may, on an`
  line `application made by the resolution professional or liquidator under sub-section (1) of section 43, by an`
  line `order:`
  line
  line `(a) require any property transferred in connection with the giving of the preference to be vested in`
  line `the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) require any property to be so vested if it represents the application either of the proceeds of`
  line `sale of property so transferred or of money so transferred;`
  line
  line `(c) release or discharge (in whole or in part) of any security interest created by the corporate`
  line debtor;
  line
  line `(d) require any person to pay such sums in respect of benefits received by him Adjudicating`
  line `Authority may direct;`
  line
  line `(e) direct any guarantor, whose financial debts or operational debts owed to any person were`
  line `released or discharged (in whole or in part) by the giving of the preference, to be under such new or`
  line `revived financial debts or operational debts to that person as the Adjudicating Authority deems`
  line appropriate;
  line
  line `(f) direct for providing security or charge on any property for the discharge of any financial debt`
  line `or operational debt under the order, and such security or charge to have the same priority as a security`
  line `or charge released or discharged wholly or in part by the giving of the preference; and`
  line
  line `(g) direct for providing the extent to which any person whose property is so vested in the`
  line `corporate debtor, or on whom financial debts or operational debts are imposed by the order, are to be`
  line `proved in the liquidation or the corporate insolvency resolution process for financial debts or`
  line `operational debts which arose from, or were released or discharged wholly or in part by the giving of`
  line `the preference:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order under this section shall not—`
  line
  line `(a) affect any interest in property which was acquired from a person other than the corporate`
  line `debtor or any interest derived from such interest and was acquired in good faith and for value;`
  line
  line `(b) require a person, who received a benefit from the preferential transaction in good faith and for`
  line `value to pay a sum to the liquidator or the resolution professional.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.— For the purpose of this section, it is clarified that where a person, who has acquired`
  line `an interest in property from another person other than the corporate debtor, or who has received a benefit`
  line `from the preference or such another person to whom the corporate debtor gave the preference,—`
  line
  line `(i) had sufficient information of the initiation or commencement of insolvency resolution process`
  line `of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(ii) is a related party,br`
  line
  line `it shall be presumed that the interest was acquired or the benefit was received otherwise than in good faith`
  line `unless the contrary is shown.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.—A person shall be deemed to have sufficient information or opportunity to avail such`
  line `information if a public announcement regarding the corporate insolvency resolution process has been`
  line `made under section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (824)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 51
  title `Avoidance of undervalued transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. The words and figures “of section 43” omitted by Act 26 of 2018, s. 28 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=824&sectionno=45&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the liquidator or the resolution professional, as`
  line `the case may be, on an examination of the transactions of the corporate debtor referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) ^1`
  line `*** determines that certain transactions were made during the relevant period under`
  line `section 46, which were undervalued, he shall make an application to the Adjudicating Authority to`
  line `declare such transactions as void and reverse the effect of such transaction in accordance with this`
  line Chapter.
  line
  line `(2) A transaction shall be considered undervalued where the corporate debtor—`
  line
  line `(a) makes a gift to a person; or`
  line
  line `(b) enters into a transaction with a person which involves the transfer of one or more assets by the`
  line `corporate debtor for a consideration the value of which is significantly less than the value of the`
  line `consideration provided by the corporate debtor,`
  line
  line `and such transaction has not taken place in the ordinary course of business of the corporate debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (825)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 52
  title `Relevant period for avoidable transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=825&sectionno=46&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) In an application for avoiding a transaction at`
  line `undervalue, the liquidator or the resolution professional, as the case may be, shall demonstrate that—`
  line
  line `(i) such transaction was made with any person within the period of one year preceding the`
  line `insolvency commencement date; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such transaction was made with a related party within the period of two years preceding the`
  line `insolvency commencement date.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority may require an independent expert to assess evidence relating to the`
  line `value of the transactions mentioned in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (826)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 53
  title `Application by creditor in cases of undervalued transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=826&sectionno=47&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an undervalued`
  line `transaction has taken place and the liquidator or the resolution professional as the case may be, has not`
  line `reported it to the Adjudicating Authority, a creditor, member or a partner of a corporate debtor, as the`
  line `case may be, may make an application to the Adjudicating Authority to declare such transactions void and`
  line `reverse their effect in accordance with this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Adjudicating Authority, after examination of the application made under`
  line `sub-section (1), is satisfied that—`
  line
  line `(a) undervalued transactions had occurred; and`
  line
  line `(b) liquidator or the resolution professional, as the case may be, after having sufficient`
  line `information or opportunity to avail information of such transactions did not report such transaction to`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority,`
  line
  line `it shall pass an order—`
  line
  line `(a) restoring the position as it existed before such transactions and reversing the effects thereof in the`
  line `manner as laid down in section 45 and section 48;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the Board to initiate disciplinary proceedings against the liquidator or the resolution`
  line `professional as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (827)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 54
  title `Order in cases of undervalued transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=827&sectionno=48&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The order of the Adjudicating Authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 45 may provide for the following:—`
  line
  line `(a) require any property transferred as part of the transaction, to be vested in the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) release or discharge (in whole or in part) any security interest granted by the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(c) require any person to pay such sums, in respect of benefits received by such person, to the`
  line `liquidator or the resolution professional as the case may be, as the Adjudicating Authority may direct;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) require the payment of such consideration for the transaction as may be determined by an`
  line `independent expert.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (828)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 55
  title `Transactions defrauding creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=828&sectionno=49&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where the corporate debtor has entered into an`
  line `undervalued transaction as referred to in sub-section (2) of section 45 and the Adjudicating Authority is`
  line `satisfied that such transaction was deliberately entered into by such corporate debtor—`
  line
  line `(a) for keeping assets of the corporate debtor beyond the reach of any person who is entitled to`
  line `make a claim against the corporate debtor; or`
  line
  line `(b) in order to adversely affect the interests of such a person in relation to the claim,`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority shall make an order—`
  line
  line `(i) restoring the position as it existed before such transaction as if the transaction had not been`
  line `entered into; and`
  line
  line `(ii) protecting the interests of persons who are victims of such transactions:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order under this sectionr—`
  line
  line `(a) shall not affect any interest in property which was acquired from a person other than the`
  line `corporate debtor and was acquired in good faith, for value and without notice of the relevant`
  line `circumstances, or affect any interest deriving from such an interest, and`
  line
  line `(b) shall not require a person who received a benefit from the transaction in good faith, for value`
  line `and without notice of the relevant circumstances to pay any sum unless he was a party to the`
  line transaction.
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (829)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 56
  title `Extortionate credit transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=829&sectionno=50&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the corporate debtor has been a party to an`
  line `extortionate credit transaction involving the receipt of financial or operational debt during the period`
  line `within two years preceding the insolvency commencement date, the liquidator or the resolution`
  line `professional as the case may be, may make an application for avoidance of such transaction to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority if the terms of such transaction required exorbitant payments to be made by the`
  line `corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may specify the circumstances in which a transactions which shall be covered under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section, it is clarified that any debt extended by any person`
  line `providing financial services which is in compliance with any law for the time being in force in relation to`
  line `such debt shall in no event be considered as an extortionate credit transaction.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (830)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 57
  title `Orders of Adjudicating Authority in respect of extortionate credit transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=830&sectionno=51&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Where the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority after examining the application made under sub-section (1) of section 50 is`
  line `satisfied that the terms of a credit transaction required exorbitant payments to be made by the corporate`
  line `debtor, it shall, by an order—`
  line
  line `(a) restore the position as it existed prior to such transaction;`
  line
  line `(b) set aside the whole or part of the debt created on account of the extortionate credit transaction;`
  line
  line `(c) modify the terms of the transaction;`
  line
  line `(d) require any person who is, or was, a party to the transaction to repay any amount received by`
  line `such person; or`
  line
  line `(e) require any security interest that was created as part of the extortionate credit transaction to be`
  line `relinquished in favour of the liquidator or the resolution professional, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (831)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 58
  title `Secured creditor in liquidation proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=831&sectionno=52&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) A secured creditor in the liquidation`
  line `proceedings may—`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish its security interest to the liquidation estate and receive proceeds from the sale of`
  line `assets by the liquidator in the manner specified in section 53; or`
  line
  line `(b) realise its security interest in the manner specified in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the secured creditor realises security interest under clause (b) of sub-section (1), he shall`
  line `inform the liquidator of such security interest and identify the asset subject to such security interest to be`
  line realised.
  line
  line `(3) Before any security interest is realised by the secured creditor under this section, the liquidator`
  line `shall verify such security interest and permit the secured creditor to realise only such security interest, the`
  line `existence of which may be proved either—`
  line
  line `(a) by the records of such security interest maintained by an information utility; or`
  line
  line `(b) by such other means as may be specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) A secured creditor may enforce, realise, settle, compromise or deal with the secured assets in`
  line `accordance with such law as applicable to the security interest being realised and to the secured creditor`
  line `and apply the proceeds to recover the debts due to it.`
  line
  line `(5) If in the course of realising a secured asset, any secured creditor faces resistance from the`
  line `corporate debtor or any person connected therewith in taking possession of, selling or otherwise disposing`
  line `of the security, the secured creditor may make an application to the Adjudicating Authority to facilitate`
  line `the secured creditor to realise such security interest in accordance with law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(6) The Adjudicating Authority, on the receipt of an application from a secured creditor under`
  line `sub-section (5) may pass such order as may be necessary to permit a secured creditor to realise security`
  line `interest in accordance with law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the enforcement of the security interest under sub-section (4) yields an amount by way of`
  line `proceeds which is in excess of the debts due to the secured creditor, the secured creditor shall—`
  line
  line `(a) account to the liquidator for such surplus; and`
  line
  line `(b) tender to the liquidator any surplus funds received from the enforcement of such secured`
  line assets.
  line
  line `(8) The amount of insolvency resolution process costs, due from secured creditors who realise their`
  line `security interests in the manner provided in this section, shall be deducted from the proceeds of any`
  line `realisation by such secured creditors, and they shall transfer such amounts to the liquidator to be included`
  line `in the liquidation estate.`
  line
  line `(9) Where the proceeds of the realisation of the secured assets are not adequate to repay debts owed to`
  line `the secured creditor, the unpaid debts of such secured creditor shall be paid by the liquidator in the`
  line `manner specified in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 53.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (832)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 59
  title `Distribution of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=832&sectionno=53&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law`
  line `enacted by the Parliament or any State Legislature for the time being in force, the proceeds from the sale`
  line `of the liquidation assets shall be distributed in the following order of priority and within such period and`
  line `in such manner as may be specified, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the insolvency resolution process costs and the liquidation costs paid in full;`
  line
  line `(b) the following debts which shall rank equally between and among the following:—`
  line
  line `(i) workmens dues for the period of twenty-four months preceding the liquidation`
  line `commencement date; and`
  line
  line `(ii) debts owed to a secured creditor in the event such secured creditor has relinquished`
  line `security in the manner set out in section 52;`
  line
  line `(c) wages and any unpaid dues owed to employees other than workmen for the period of twelve`
  line `months preceding the liquidation commencement date;`
  line
  line `(d) financial debts owed to unsecured creditors;`
  line
  line `(e) the following dues shall rank equally between and among the following:—`
  line
  line `(i) any amount due to the Central Government and the State Government including the`
  line `amount to be received on account of the Consolidated Fund of India and the Consolidated Fund`
  line `of a State, if any, in respect of the whole or any part of the period of two years preceding the`
  line `liquidation commencement date;`
  line
  line `(ii) debts owed to a secured creditor for any amount unpaid following the enforcement of`
  line `security interest;`
  line
  line `(f) any remaining debts and dues;`
  line
  line `(g) preference shareholders, if any; and`
  line
  line `(h) equity shareholders or partners, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any contractual arrangements between recipients under sub-section (1) with equal ranking, if`
  line `disrupting the order of priority under that sub-section shall be disregarded by the liquidator.`
  line
  line `(3) The fees payable to the liquidator shall be deducted proportionately from the proceeds payable to`
  line `each class of recipients under sub-section (1), and the proceeds to the relevant recipient shall be`
  line `distributed after such deduction.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— For the purpose of this section—`
  line
  line `(i) it is hereby clarified that at each stage of the distribution of proceeds in respect of a class of`
  line `recipients that rank equally, each of the debts will either be paid in full, or will be paid in equal`
  line `proportion within the same class of recipients, if the proceeds are insufficient to meet the debts in full;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) the term “workmen’s dues” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 326 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (833)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 60
  title `Dissolution of corporate debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=833&sectionno=54&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the assets of the corporate debtor have been`
  line `completely liquidated, the liquidator shall make an application to the Adjudicating Authority for the`
  line `dissolution of such corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall on application filed by the liquidator under sub-section (1) order`
  line `that the corporate debtor shall be dissolved from the date of that order and the corporate debtor shall be`
  line `dissolved accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of an order under sub-section (2) shall within seven days from the date of such order, be`
  line `forwarded to the authority with which the corporate debtor is registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_a:
  sectionId (57216)
  sectionNo 54A
  orderNo 61
  title `Corporate debtors eligible for pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 8 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57216&sectionno=54A&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[54A. Corporate debtors eligible for pre-packaged insolvency resolution process--(1) An`
  line `application for initiating pre-packaged insolvency resolution process may be made in respect of a`
  line `corporate debtor classified as a micro, small or medium enterprise under sub-section (1) of section 7 of`
  line `the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act, 2006 (27 of 2006).`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), an application for initiating pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process may be made in respect of a corporate debtor, who commits a default referred to in`
  line `section 4, subject to the following conditions, that—`
  line
  line `(a) it has not undergone pre-packaged insolvency resolution process or completed corporate`
  line `insolvency resolution process, as the case may be, during the period of three years preceding the`
  line `initiation date;`
  line
  line `(b) it is not undergoing a corporate insolvency resolution process;`
  line
  line `(c) no order requiring it to be liquidated is passed under section 33;`
  line
  line `(d) it is eligible to submit a resolution plan under section 29A;`
  line
  line `(e) the financial creditors of the corporate debtor, not being its related parties, representing such`
  line `number and in such manner as may be specified, have proposed the name of the insolvency`
  line `professional to be appointed as resolution professional for conducting the pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process of the corporate debtor, and the financial creditors of the corporate debtor, not`
  line `being its related parties, representing not less than sixty-six per cent. in value of the financial debt due`
  line `to such creditors, have approved such proposal in such form as may be specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a corporate debtor does not have any financial creditors, not being its related`
  line `parties, the proposal and approval under this clause shall be provided by such persons as may be`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(f) the majority of the directors or partners of the corporate debtor, as the case may be, have made`
  line `a declaration, in such form as may be specified, stating, inter alia, that--`
  line
  line `(i) the corporate debtor shall file an application for initiating pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process within a definite time period not exceeding ninety days;`
  line
  line `(ii) the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process is not being initiated to defraud any`
  line `person; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the name of the insolvency professional proposed and approved to be appointed as`
  line `resolution professional under clause (e);`
  line
  line `(g) the members of the corporate debtor have passed a special resolution, or at least three-fourth`
  line `of the total number of partners, as the case may be, of the corporate debtor have passed a resolution,`
  line `approving the filing of an application for initiating pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  line
  line `(3) The corporate debtor shall obtain an approval from its financial creditors, not being its related`
  line `parties, representing not less than sixty-six per cent. in value of the financial debt due to such creditors,`
  line `for the filing of an application for initiating pre-packaged insolvency resolution process, in such form as`
  line `may be specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a corporate debtor does not have any financial creditors, not being its related`
  line `parties, the approval under this sub-section shall be provided by such persons as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) Prior to seeking approval from financial creditors under sub-section (3), the corporate debtor shall`
  line `provide such financial creditors with--`
  line
  line `(a) the declaration referred to in clause (f) of sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(b) the special resolution or resolution referred to in clause (g) of sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(c) a base resolution plan which conforms to the requirements referred to in section 54K, and`
  line `such other conditions as may be specified; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other information and documents as may be specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_b:
  sectionId (57217)
  sectionNo 54B
  orderNo 62
  title `Duties of insolvency professional before initiation of pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57217&sectionno=54B&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_b_content:
  string
  line `54B. Duties of insolvency professional before initiation of pre-packaged insolvency resolution`
  line `process.--(1) The insolvency professional, proposed to be appointed as the resolution professional, shall`
  line `have the following duties commencing from the date of the approval under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 54A, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) prepare a report in such form as may be specified, confirming whether the corporate debtor`
  line `meets the requirements of section 54A, and the base resolution plan conforms to the requirements`
  line `referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (4) of section 54A;`
  line
  line `(b) file such reports and other documents, with the Board, as may be specified; and`
  line
  line `(c) perform such other duties as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The duties of the insolvency professional under sub-section (1) shall cease, if,--`
  line
  line `(a) the corporate debtor fails to file an application for initiating pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process within the time period as stated under the declaration referred to in clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 54A; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application for initiating pre-packaged insolvency resolution process is admitted or`
  line `rejected by the Adjudicating Authority,`
  line
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The fees payable to the insolvency professional in relation to the duties performed under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be determined and borne in such manner as may be specified and such fees shall`
  line `form part of the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process costs, if the application for initiation of prepackaged insolvency resolution process is admitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_c:
  sectionId (57218)
  sectionNo 54C
  orderNo 63
  title `Application to initiate pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57218&sectionno=54C&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_c_content:
  string
  line `54C. Application to initiate pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.--(1) Where a corporate`
  line `debtor meets the requirements of section 54A, a corporate applicant thereof may file an application with`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority for initiating pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  line
  line `(2) The application under sub-section (1) shall be filed in such form, containing such particulars, in`
  line `such manner and accompanied with such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The corporate applicant shall, along with the application, furnish--`
  line
  line `(a) the declaration, special resolution or resolution, as the case may be, and the approval of`
  line `financial creditors for initiating pre-packaged insolvency resolution process in terms of section 54A;`
  line
  line `(b) the name and written consent, in such form as may be specified, of the insolvency`
  line `professional proposed to be appointed as resolution professional, as approved under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 54A, and his report as referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line 54B;
  line
  line `(c) a declaration regarding the existence of any transactions of the corporate debtor that may be`
  line `within the scope of provisions in respect of avoidance of transactions under Chapter III or fraudulent`
  line `or wrongful trading under Chapter VI, in such form as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(d) information relating to books of account of the corporate debtor and such other documents`
  line `relating to such period as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The Adjudicating Authority shall, within a period of fourteen days of the receipt of the`
  line `application, by an order,--`
  line
  line `(a) admit the application, if it is complete; or`
  line
  line `(b) reject the application, if it is incomplete:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Adjudicating Authority shall, before rejecting an application, give notice to the`
  line `applicant to rectify the defect in the application within seven days from the date of receipt of such notice`
  line `from the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The pre-packaged insolvency resolution process shall commence from the date of admission of`
  line `the application under clause (a) of sub-section (4).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_d:
  sectionId (57219)
  sectionNo 54D
  orderNo 64
  title `Time-limit for completion of pre-packaged insolvency resolution process`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57219&sectionno=54D&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_d_content:
  string
  line `54D. Time-limit for completion of pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.--(1) The prepackaged insolvency resolution process shall be completed within a period of one hundred and twenty`
  line `days from the pre-packaged insolvency commencement date.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1), the resolution professional shall submit the resolution plan,`
  line `as approved by the committee of creditors, to the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (4) or`
  line `sub-section (12), as the case may be, of section 54K, within a period of ninety days from the prepackaged insolvency commencement date.`
  line
  line `(3) Where no resolution plan is approved by the committee of creditors within the time period`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2), the resolution professional shall, on the day after the expiry of such time`
  line `period, file an application with the Adjudicating Authority for termination of the pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process in such form and manner as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_e:
  sectionId (57220)
  sectionNo 54E
  orderNo 65
  title `Declaration of moratorium and public announcement during pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57220&sectionno=54E&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_e_content:
  string
  line `54E. Declaration of moratorium and public announcement during prepackaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process.--(1) The Adjudicating Authority shall, on the pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `commencement date, along with the order of admission under section 54C--`
  line
  line `(a) declare a moratorium for the purposes referred to in sub-section (1) read with sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 14, which shall, mutatis mutandis apply, to the proceedings under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(b) appoint a resolution professional--`
  line
  line `(i) as named in the application, if no disciplinary proceeding is pending against him; or`
  line
  line `(ii) based on the recommendation made by the Board, if any disciplinary proceeding is`
  line `pending against the insolvency professional named in the application;`
  line
  line `(c) cause a public announcement of the initiation of the pre-packaged insolvency resolution`
  line `process to be made by the resolution professional, in such form and manner as may be specified,`
  line `immediately after his appointment.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of moratorium shall have effect from the date of such order till the date on which the`
  line `pre-packaged insolvency resolution process period comes to an end.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_e_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_f:
  sectionId (57221)
  sectionNo 54F
  orderNo 66
  title `Duties and powers of resolution professional during pre-packaged insolvency resolution process`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57221&sectionno=54F&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_f_content:
  string
  line `Duties and powers of resolution professional during prepackaged insolvency resolution`
  line `process.--(1) The resolution professional shall conduct the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process`
  line `of a corporate debtor during the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process period.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional shall perform the following duties, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) confirm the list of claims submitted by the corporate debtor under section 54G, in such`
  line `manner as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(b) inform creditors regarding their claims as confirmed under clause (a), in such manner as may`
  line `be specified;`
  line
  line `(c) maintain an updated list of claims, in such manner as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(d) monitor management of the affairs of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(e) inform the committee of creditors in the event of breach of any of the obligations of the Board`
  line `of Directors or partners, as the case may be, of the corporate debtor, under the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter and the rules and regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(f) constitute the committee of creditors and convene and attend all its meetings;`
  line
  line `(g) prepare the information memorandum on the basis of the preliminary information`
  line `memorandum submitted under section 54G and any other relevant information, in such form and`
  line `manner as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(h) file applications for avoidance of transactions under Chapter III or fraudulent or wrongful`
  line `trading under Chapter VI, if any; and`
  line
  line `(i) such other duties as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The resolution professional shall exercise the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) access all books of account, records and information available with the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) access the electronic records of the corporate debtor from an information utility having`
  line `financial information of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(c) access the books of account, records and other relevant documents of the corporate debtor`
  line `available with Government authorities, statutory auditors, accountants and such other persons as may`
  line `be specified;`
  line
  line `(d) attend meetings of members, Board of Directors and committee of directors, or partners, as`
  line `the case may be, of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(e) appoint accountants, legal or other professionals in such manner as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(f) collect all information relating to the assets, finances and operations of the corporate debtor for`
  line `determining the financial position of the corporate debtor and the existence of any transactions that`
  line `may be within the scope of provisions relating to avoidance of transactions under Chapter III or`
  line `fraudulent or wrongful trading under Chapter VI, including information relating to--`
  line
  line `(i) business operations for the previous two years from the date of pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `commencement date;`
  line
  line `(ii) financial and operational payments for the previous two years from the date of prepackaged insolvency commencement date;`
  line
  line `(iii) list of assets and liabilities as on the initiation date; and`
  line
  line `(iv) such other matters as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(g) take such other actions in such manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) From the date of appointment of the resolution professional, the financial institutions maintaining`
  line `accounts of the corporate debtor shall furnish all information relating to the corporate debtor available`
  line `with them to the resolution professional, as and when required by him.`
  line
  line `(5) The personnel of the corporate debtor, its promoters and any other person associated with the`
  line `management of the corporate debtor shall extend all assistance and cooperation to the resolution`
  line `professional as may be required by him to perform his duties and exercise his powers, and for such`
  line `purposes, the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 19 shall, mutatis mutandis apply, in relation`
  line `to the proceedings under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(6) The fees of the resolution professional and any expenses incurred by him for conducting the prepackaged insolvency resolution process shall be determined in such manner as may be specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that the committee of creditors may impose limits and conditions on such fees and expenses:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the fees and expenses for the period prior to the constitution of the committee of`
  line `creditors shall be subject to ratification by it.`
  line
  line `(7) The fees and expenses referred to in sub-section (6) shall be borne in such manner as may be`
  line specified.
obj_root_law_sections_54_f_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_g:
  sectionId (57222)
  sectionNo 54G
  orderNo 67
  title `List of claims and preliminary information memorandum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57222&sectionno=54G&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_g_content:
  string
  line `54G. List of claims and preliminary information memorandum.--(1) The corporate debtor shall,`
  line `within two days of the pre-packaged insolvency commencement date, submit to the resolution`
  line `professional the following information, updated as on that date, in such form and manner as may be`
  line `specified, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a list of claims, along with details of the respective creditors, their security interests and`
  line `guarantees, if any; and`
  line
  line `(b) a preliminary information memorandum containing information relevant for formulating a`
  line `resolution plan.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person has sustained any loss or damage as a consequence of the omission of any`
  line `material information or inclusion of any misleading information in the list of claims or the preliminary`
  line `information memorandum submitted by the corporate debtor, every person who--`
  line
  line `(a) is a promoter or director or partner of the corporate debtor, as the case may be, at the time of`
  line `submission of the list of claims or the preliminary information memorandum by the corporate debtor;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) has authorised the submission of the list of claims or the preliminary information`
  line `memorandum by the corporate debtor,`
  line
  line `shall, without prejudice to section 77A, be liable to pay compensation to every person who has sustained`
  line `such loss or damage.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be liable under sub-section (2), if the list of claims or the preliminary information`
  line `memorandum was submitted by the corporate debtor without his knowledge or consent.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to section 54E, any person, who sustained any loss or damage as a consequence of`
  line `omission of material information or inclusion of any misleading information in the list of claims or the`
  line `preliminary information memorandum shall be entitled to move a court having jurisdiction for seeking`
  line `compensation for such loss or damage.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_g_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_h:
  sectionId (57223)
  sectionNo 54H
  orderNo 68
  title `Management of affairs of corporate debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57223&sectionno=54H&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_h_content:
  string
  line `54H. Management of affairs of corporate debtor.--During the pre-packaged insolvency resolution`
  line `process period,--`
  line
  line `(a) the management of the affairs of the corporate debtor shall continue to vest in the Board of`
  line `Directors or the partners, as the case may be, of the corporate debtor, subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be specified;`
  line
  line `(b) the Board of Directors or the partners, as the case may be, of the corporate debtor, shall make`
  line `every endeavour to protect and preserve the value of the property of the corporate debtor, and manage`
  line `its operations as a going concern; and`
  line
  line `(c) the promoters, members, personnel and partners, as the case may be, of the corporate debtor,`
  line `shall exercise and discharge their contractual or statutory rights and obligations in relation to the`
  line `corporate debtor, subject to the provisions of this Chapter and such other conditions and restrictions`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_h_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_i:
  sectionId (57224)
  sectionNo 54-I
  orderNo 69
  title `Committee of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57224&sectionno=54-I&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_i_content:
  string
  line `54-I. Committee of creditors.--(1) The resolution professional shall, within seven days of the`
  line `pre-packaged insolvency commencement date, constitute a committee of creditors, based on the list of`
  line `claims confirmed under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 54F:`
  line
  line `Provided that the composition of the committee of creditors shall be altered on the basis of the`
  line `updated list of claims, in such manner as may be specified, and any such alteration shall not affect the`
  line `validity of any past decision of the committee of creditors.`
  line
  line `(2) The first meeting of the committee of creditors shall be held within seven days of the constitution`
  line `of the committee of creditors.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 21, except sub-section (1) thereof, shall, mutatis mutandis apply, in`
  line `relation to the committee of creditors under this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of this sub-section, references to “resolution professional” under`
  line `sub-sections (9) and (10) of section 21, shall be construed as references to “corporate debtor or the`
  line `resolution professional”.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_i_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_j:
  sectionId (57225)
  sectionNo 54J
  orderNo 70
  title `Vesting management of corporate debtor with resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57225&sectionno=54J&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_j_content:
  string
  line `54J. Vesting management of corporate debtor with resolution professional.--(1) Where the`
  line `committee of creditors, at any time during the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process period, by a`
  line `vote of not less than sixty-six per cent. of the voting shares, resolves to vest the management of the`
  line `corporate debtor with the resolution professional, the resolution professional shall make an application for`
  line `this purpose to the Adjudicating Authority, in such form and manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) On an application made under sub-section (1), if the Adjudicating Authority is of the opinion that`
  line `during the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process--`
  line
  line `(a) the affairs of the corporate debtor have been conducted in a fraudulent manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) there has been gross mismanagement of the affairs of the corporate debtor,`
  line
  line `it shall pass an order vesting the management of the corporate debtor with the resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Chapter, the provisions of--`
  line
  line `(a) sub-sections (2) and (2A) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) clauses (e) to (g) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(d) sections 19 and 20;`
  line
  line `(e) sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(f) clauses (a) to (c) and clause (k) of sub-section (2) of section 25; and`
  line
  line `(g) section 28,`
  line
  line `shall, mutatis mutandis apply, to the proceedings under this Chapter, from the date of the order under`
  line `sub-section (2), until the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process period comes to an end.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_j_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_k:
  sectionId (57226)
  sectionNo 54K
  orderNo 71
  title `Consideration and approval of resolution plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57226&sectionno=54K&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_k_content:
  string
  line `54K. Consideration and approval of resolution plan.--(1) The corporate debtor shall submit the`
  line `base resolution plan, referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (4) of section 54A, to the resolution`
  line `professional within two days of the pre-packaged insolvency commencement date, and the resolution`
  line `professional shall present it to the committee of creditors.`
  line
  line `(2) The committee of creditors may provide the corporate debtor an opportunity to revise the base`
  line `resolution plan prior to its approval under sub-section (4) or invitation of prospective resolution`
  line `applicants under sub-section (5), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The resolution plans and the base resolution plan, submitted under this section shall conform to`
  line `the requirements referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 30, and the provisions of sub-sections`
  line `(1), (2) and (5) of section 30 shall, mutatis mutandis apply, to the proceedings under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(4) The committee of creditors may approve the base resolution plan for submission to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority if it does not impair any claims owed by the corporate debtor to the operational`
  line creditors.
  line
  line `(5) Where--`
  line `(a) the committee of creditors does not approve the base resolution plan under sub-section (4); or`
  line
  line `(b) the base resolution plan impairs any claims owed by the corporate debtor to the operational`
  line creditors,
  line
  line `the resolution professional shall invite prospective resolution applicants to submit a resolution plan or`
  line `plans, to compete with the base resolution plan, in such manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(6) The resolution applicants submitting resolution plans pursuant to invitation under sub-section (5),`
  line `shall fulfil such criteria as may be laid down by the resolution professional with the approval of the`
  line `committee of creditors, having regard to the complexity and scale of operations of the business of the`
  line `corporate debtor and such other conditions as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(7) The resolution professional shall provide to the resolution applicants,--`
  line
  line `(a) the basis for evaluation of resolution plans for the purposes of sub-section (9), as approved by`
  line `the committee of creditors subject to such conditions as may be specified; and`
  line
  line `(b) the relevant information referred to in section 29, which shall, mutatis mutandis apply, to the`
  line `proceedings under this Chapter,`
  line
  line `in such manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(8) The resolution professional shall present to the committee of creditors, for its evaluation,`
  line `resolution plans which conform to the requirements referred to in sub-section (2) of section 30.`
  line
  line `(9) The committee of creditors shall evaluate the resolution plans presented by the resolution`
  line `professional and select a resolution plan from amongst them.`
  line
  line `(10) Where, on the basis of such criteria as may be laid down by it, the committee of creditors decides`
  line `that the resolution plan selected under sub-section (9) is significantly better than the base resolution plan,`
  line `such resolution plan may be selected for approval under sub-section (12):`
  line
  line `Provided that the criteria laid down by the committee of creditors under this sub-section shall be`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(11) Where the resolution plan selected under sub-section (9) is not considered for approval or does`
  line `not fulfil the requirements of sub-section (10), it shall compete with the base resolution plan, in such`
  line `manner and subject to such conditions as may be specified, and one of them shall be selected for approval`
  line `under sub-section (12).`
  line
  line `(12) The resolution plan selected for approval under sub-section (10) or sub-section (11), as the case`
  line `may be, may be approved by the committee of creditors for submission to the Adjudicating Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the resolution plan selected for approval under sub-section (11) is not approved`
  line `by the committee of creditors, the resolution professional shall file an application for termination of the`
  line `pre-packaged insolvency resolution process in such form and manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(13) The approval of the resolution plan under sub-section (4) or sub-section (12), as the case may be,`
  line `by the committee of creditors, shall be by a vote of not less than sixty-six per cent. of the voting shares,`
  line `after considering its feasibility and viability, the manner of distribution proposed, taking into account the`
  line `order of priority amongst creditors as laid down in sub-section (1) of section 53, including the priority and`
  line `value of the security interest of a secured creditor and such other requirements as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(14) While considering the feasibility and viability of a resolution plan, where the resolution plan`
  line `submitted by the corporate debtor provides for impairment of any claims owed by the corporate debtor,`
  line `the committee of creditors may require the promoters of the corporate debtor to dilute their shareholding`
  line `or voting or control rights in the corporate debtor:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the resolution plan does not provide for such dilution, the committee of creditors`
  line `shall, prior to the approval of such resolution plan under sub-section (4) or sub-section (12), as the case`
  line `may be, record reasons for its approval.`
  line
  line `(15) The resolution professional shall submit the resolution plan as approved by the committee of`
  line `creditors under sub-section (4) or sub-section (12), as the case may be, to the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that, the corporate debtor being a`
  line `resolution applicant under clause (25) of section 5, may submit the base resolution plan either individually`
  line `or jointly with any other person.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of sub-sections (4) and (14), claims shall be considered to be impaired`
  line `where the resolution plan does not provide for the full payment of the confirmed claims as per the updated`
  line `list of claims maintained by the resolution professional.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_k_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_l:
  sectionId (57227)
  sectionNo 54L
  orderNo 72
  title `Approval of resolution plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_l_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_l_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57227&sectionno=54L&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_l_content:
  string
  line `54L. Approval of resolution plan.--(1) If the Adjudicating Authority is satisfied that the resolution`
  line `plan as approved by the committee of creditors under sub-section (4) or sub-section (12), as the case may`
  line `be of section 54K, subject to the conditions provided therein, meets the requirements as referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 30, it shall, within thirty days of the receipt of such resolution plan, by order,`
  line `approve the resolution plan:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Adjudicating Authority shall, before passing an order for approval of a resolution`
  line `plan under this sub-section, satisfy itself that the resolution plan has provisions for its effective`
  line implementation.
  line
  line `(2) The order of approval under sub-section (1) shall have such effect as provided under sub-sections`
  line `(1), (3) and (4) of section 31, which shall, mutatis mutandis apply, to the proceedings under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Adjudicating Authority is satisfied that the resolution plan does not conform to the`
  line `requirements referred to in sub-section (1), it may, within thirty days of the receipt of such resolution`
  line `plan, by an order, reject the resolution plan and pass an order under section 54N.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this section, where the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority has passed an order under sub-section (2) of section 54J and the resolution plan approved by`
  line `the committee of creditors under sub-section (4) or sub-section (12), as the case may be of section 54K,`
  line `does not result in the change in the management or control of the corporate debtor to a person who was not a promoter or in the management or control of the corporate debtor, the Adjudicating Authority shall`
  line `pass an order--`
  line
  line `(a) rejecting such resolution plan;`
  line
  line `(b) terminating the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process and passing a liquidation order in`
  line `respect of the corporate debtor as referred to in sub-clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 33; and`
  line
  line `(c) declaring that the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process costs, if any, shall be included`
  line `as part of the liquidation costs for the purposes of liquidation of the corporate debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_l_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_m:
  sectionId (57228)
  sectionNo 54M
  orderNo 73
  title `Appeal against order under section 54L.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57228&sectionno=54M&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_m_content:
  string
  line `54M. Appeal against order under section 54L.--Any appeal against an order approving the`
  line `resolution plan under sub-section (1) of section 54L, shall be on the grounds laid down in sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 61.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_m_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_n:
  sectionId (57229)
  sectionNo 54N
  orderNo 74
  title `Termination of pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57229&sectionno=54N&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_n_content:
  string
  line `54N. Termination of prepackaged insolvency resolution process.--(1) Where the resolution`
  line `professional files an application with the Adjudicating Authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) under the proviso to sub-section (12) of section 54K; or`
  line
  line `(b) under sub-section (3) of section 54D,`
  line
  line `the Adjudicating Authority shall, within thirty days of the date of such application, by an order,--`
  line
  line `(i) terminate the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process; and`
  line
  line `(ii) provide for the manner of continuation of proceedings initiated for avoidance of transactions`
  line `under Chapter III or proceedings initiated under section 66 and section 67A, if any.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the resolution professional, at any time after the pre-packaged insolvency commencement`
  line `date, but before the approval of resolution plan under sub-section (4) or sub-section (12), as the case may`
  line `be of section 54K, intimates the Adjudicating Authority of the decision of the committee of creditors,`
  line `approved by a vote of not less than sixty-six per cent. of the voting shares, to terminate the pre-packaged`
  line `insolvency resolution process, the Adjudicating Authority shall pass an order under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Adjudicating Authority passes an order under sub-section (1), the corporate debtor`
  line `shall bear the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process costs, if any.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this section, where the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority has passed an order under sub-section (2) of section 54J and the pre-packaged insolvency`
  line `resolution process is required to be terminated under sub-section (1), the Adjudicating Authority shall`
  line `pass an order--`
  line
  line `(a) of liquidation in respect of the corporate debtor as referred to in sub-clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) of`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 33; and`
  line
  line `(b) declare that the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process costs, if any, shall be included as`
  line `part of the liquidation costs for the purposes of liquidation of the corporate debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_n_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_o:
  sectionId (57230)
  sectionNo 54-O
  orderNo 75
  title `Initiation of corporate insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_o_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_o_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57230&sectionno=54-O&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_o_content:
  string
  line `54-O. Initiation of corporate insolvency resolution process.--(1) The committee of creditors, at`
  line `any time after the pre-packaged insolvency commencement date but before the approval of resolution`
  line `plan under sub-section (4) or sub-section (12), as the case may be of section 54K, by a vote of not less`
  line `than sixty-six per cent. of the voting shares, may resolve to initiate a corporate insolvency resolution process in respect of the corporate debtor, if such corporate debtor is eligible for corporate insolvency`
  line `resolution process under Chapter II.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in Chapter II, where the resolution`
  line `professional intimates the Adjudicating Authority of the decision of the committee of creditors under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Adjudicating Authority shall, within thirty days of the date of such intimation, pass an`
  line `order to--`
  line
  line `(a) terminate the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process and initiate corporate insolvency`
  line `resolution process under Chapter II in respect of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) appoint the resolution professional referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 54E`
  line `as the interim resolution professional, subject to submission of written consent by such resolution`
  line `professional to the Adjudicating Authority in such form as may be specified; and`
  line
  line `(c) declare that the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process costs, if any, shall be included as`
  line `part of insolvency resolution process costs for the purposes of the corporate insolvency resolution`
  line `process of the corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the resolution professional fails to submit written consent under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2), the Adjudicating Authority shall appoint an interim resolution professional by making a`
  line `reference to the Board for recommendation, in the manner as provided under section 16.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Adjudicating Authority passes an order under sub-section (2)--`
  line
  line `(a) such order shall be deemed to be an order of admission of an application under section 7 and`
  line `shall have the same effect;`
  line
  line `(b) the corporate insolvency resolution process shall commence from the date of such order;`
  line
  line `(c) the proceedings initiated for avoidance of transactions under Chapter III or proceedings`
  line `initiated under section 66 and section 67A, if any, shall continue during the corporate insolvency`
  line `resolution process;`
  line
  line `(d) for the purposes of sections 43, 46 and 50, references to “insolvency commencement date”`
  line `shall mean “pre-packaged insolvency commencement date”; and`
  line
  line `(e) in computing the relevant time or the period for avoidable transactions, the time-period for the`
  line `duration of the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process shall also be included, notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in sections 43, 46 and 50.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_o_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54_p:
  sectionId (57231)
  sectionNo 54P
  orderNo 76
  title `Application of provisions of Chapters II, III, VI and VII to this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_p_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_p_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57231&sectionno=54P&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_54_p_content:
  string
  line `54P. Application of provisions of Chapters II, III, VI and VII to this Chapter.--(1) Save as`
  line `provided under this Chapter, the provisions of sections 24, 25A, 26, 27, 28, 29A, 32A, 43 to 51, and the`
  line `provisions of Chapters VI and VII of this Part shall, mutatis mutandis apply, to the pre-packaged`
  line `insolvency resolution process, subject to the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) reference to “members of the suspended Board of Directors or the partners” under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 24 shall be construed as reference to “members of the Board of Directors`
  line `or the partners, unless an order has been passed by the Adjudicating Authority under section 54J”;`
  line
  line `(b) reference to “clause (j) of sub-section (2) of section 25” under section 26 shall be construed as`
  line `reference to “clause (h) of sub-section (2) of section 54F”;`
  line
  line `(c) reference to “section 16” under section 27 shall be construed as reference to “section 54E”;`
  line
  line `(d) reference to “resolution professional” in sub-sections (1) and (4) of section 28 shall be`
  line `construed as “corporate debtor”;`
  line
  line `(e) reference to “section 31” under sub-section (3) of section 61 shall be construed as reference to`
  line `“sub-section (1) of section 54L”;`
  line
  line `(f) reference to “section 14” in sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 74 shall be construed as`
  line `reference to “clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 54E”;`
  line
  line `(g) reference to “section 31” in sub-section (3) of section 74 shall be construed as reference to`
  line `“sub-section (1) of section 54L”.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of this Chapter and unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line `where the provisions of Chapters II, III, VI and VII are applied to the proceedings under this Chapter,`
  line `references to--`
  line
  line `(a) “insolvency commencement date” shall be construed as references to “pre-packaged`
  line `insolvency commencement date”;`
  line
  line `(b) “resolution professional” or “interim resolution professional”, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `construed as references to the resolution professional appointed under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(c) “corporate insolvency resolution process” shall be construed as references to “pre-packaged`
  line `insolvency resolution process”; and`
  line
  line `(d) “insolvency resolution process period” shall be construed as references to “pre-packaged`
  line `insolvency resolution process period”.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_p_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (834)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 77
  title `Fast track corporate insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=834&sectionno=55&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) A corporate insolvency resolution`
  line `process carried out in accordance with this Chapter shall be called as fast track corporate insolvency`
  line `resolution process.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for fast track corporate insolvency resolution process may be made in respect of`
  line `the following corporate debtors, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a corporate debtor with assets and income below a level as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) a corporate debtor with such class of creditors or such amount of debt as may be notified by`
  line `the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) such other category of corporate persons as may be notified by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (835)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 78
  title `Time period for completion of fast track corporate insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=835&sectionno=56&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), the fast track corporate insolvency resolution process shall be`
  line `completed within a period of ninety days from the insolvency commencement date.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional shall file an application to the Adjudicating Authority to extend the`
  line `period of the fast track corporate insolvency resolution process beyond ninety days if instructed to`
  line `do so by a resolution passed at a meeting of the committee of creditors and supported by a vote of`
  line `seventy five per cent. of the voting share.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (2), if the Adjudicating Authority is satisfied that`
  line `the subject matter of the case is such that fast track corporate insolvency resolution process cannot be`
  line `completed within a period of ninety days, it may, by order, extend the duration of such process beyond`
  line `the said period of ninety days by such further period, as it thinks fit, but not exceeding forty-five days:`
  line
  line `Provided that any extension of the fast track corporate insolvency resolution process under this`
  line `section shall not be granted more than once.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (836)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 79
  title `Manner of initiating fast track corporate insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=836&sectionno=57&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `An application for`
  line `fast track corporate insolvency resolution process may be filed by a creditor or corporate debtor as the`
  line `case may be, along with—`
  line
  line `(a) the proof of the existence of default as evidenced by records available with an information`
  line `utility or such other means as may be specified by the Board; and`
  line
  line `(b) such other information as may be specified by the Board to establish that the corporate debtor`
  line `is eligible for fast track corporate insolvency resolution process.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (837)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 80
  title `Applicability of Chapter II to this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=837&sectionno=58&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The process for conducting a corporate`
  line `insolvency resolution process under Chapter II and the provisions relating to offences and penalties under`
  line `Chapter VII shall apply to this Chapter as the context may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (838)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 81
  title `Voluntary liquidation of corporate persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=838&sectionno=59&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) A corporate person who intends to liquidate`
  line `itself voluntarily and has not committed any default may initiate voluntary liquidation proceedings under`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `(2) The voluntary liquidation of a corporate person under sub-section (1) shall meet such conditions`
  line `and procedural requirements as may be specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to sub-section (2), voluntary liquidation proceedings of a corporate person`
  line `registered as a company shall meet the following conditions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a declaration from majority of the directors of the company verified by an affidavit stating`
  line that—
  line
  line `(i) they have made a full inquiry into the affairs of the company and they have formed an`
  line `opinion that either the company has no debt or that it will be able to pay its debts in full from the`
  line `proceeds of assets to be sold in the voluntary liquidation; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the company is not being liquidated to defraud any person;`
  line
  line `(b) the declaration under sub-clause (a) shall be accompanied with the following documents,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) audited financial statements and record of business operations of the company for the`
  line `previous two years or for the period since its incorporation, whichever is later;`
  line
  line `(ii) a report of the valuation of the assets of the company, if any prepared by a registered`
  line valuer;
  line
  line `(c) within four weeks of a declaration under sub-clause (a), there shall be—`
  line
  line `(i) a special resolution of the members of the company in a general meeting requiring the`
  line `company to be liquidated voluntarily and appointing an insolvency professional to act as the`
  line `liquidator; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a resolution of the members of the company in a general meeting requiring the company`
  line `to be liquidated voluntarily as a result of expiry of the period of its duration, if any, fixed by its`
  line `articles or on the occurrence of any event in respect of which the articles provide that the`
  line `company shall be dissolved, as the case may be and appointing an insolvency professional to act`
  line `as the liquidator:`
  line
  line `Provided that the company owes any debt to any person, creditors representing two-thirds in value of`
  line `the debt of the company shall approve the resolution passed under sub-clause (c) within seven days of`
  line `such resolution.`
  line
  line `(4) The company shall notify the Registrar of Companies and the Board about the resolution under`
  line `sub-section (3) to liquidate the company within seven days of such resolution or the subsequent approval`
  line `by the creditors, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to approval of the creditors under sub-section (3), the voluntary liquidation proceedings in`
  line `respect of a company shall be deemed to have commenced from the date of passing of the resolution`
  line `under sub-clause (c) of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of sections 35 to 53 of Chapter III and Chapter VII shall apply to voluntary`
  line `liquidation proceedings for corporate persons with such modifications as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the affairs of the corporate person have been completely wound up, and its assets`
  line `completely liquidated, the liquidator shall make an application to the Adjudicating Authority for the`
  line `dissolution of such corporate person.`
  line
  line `(8) The Adjudicating Authority shall on an application filed by the liquidator under sub-section (7),`
  line `pass an order that the corporate debtor shall be dissolved from the date of that order and the corporate`
  line `debtor shall be dissolved accordingly`
  line
  line `(9) A copy of an order under sub-section (8) shall within fourteen days from the date of such order, be`
  line `forwarded to the authority with which the corporate person is registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (839)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 82
  title `Adjudicating Authority for corporate persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=839&sectionno=60&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Authority, in relation to`
  line `insolvency resolution and liquidation for corporate persons including corporate debtors and personal`
  line `guarantors thereof shall be the National Company Law Tribunal having territorial jurisdiction over the`
  line `place where the registered office of the corporate person is located.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to sub-section (1) and notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `this Code, where a corporate insolvency resolution process or liquidation proceeding of a corporate debtor`
  line `is pending before a National Company Law Tribunal, an application relating to the insolvency resolution`
  line `or ^1`
  line `[liquidation or bankruptcy of a corporate guarantor or personal guarantor, as the case may be, of such`
  line `corporate debtor] shall be filed before such National Company Law Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) An insolvency resolution process or ^2`
  line `[liquidation or bankruptcy proceeding of a corporate`
  line `guarantor or personal guarantor, as the case may be, of the corporate debtor] pending in any court or`
  line `tribunal shall stand transferred to the Adjudicating Authority dealing with insolvency resolution process`
  line `or liquidation proceeding of such corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `(4) The National Company Law Tribunal shall be vested with all the powers of the Debt Recovery`
  line `Tribunal as contemplated under Part III of this Code for the purpose of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `the National Company Law Tribunal shall have jurisdiction to entertain or dispose of—`
  line
  line `(a) any application or proceeding by or against the corporate debtor or corporate person;`
  line
  line `(b) any claim made by or against the corporate debtor or corporate person, including claims by or`
  line `against any of its subsidiaries situated in India; and`
  line
  line `(c) any question of priorities or any question of law or facts, arising out of or in relation to the`
  line `insolvency resolution or liquidation proceedings of the corporate debtor or corporate person under`
  line `this Code.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) or in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, in computing the period of limitation specified for any suit or application by or`
  line `against a corporate debtor for which an order of moratorium has been made under this Part, the period`
  line `during which such moratorium is in place shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line `1Subs. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 29, for “bankruptcy of a personal guarantor of such corporate debtor” (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for “bankruptcy proceeding of a personal guarantor of the corporate debtor” (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (840)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 83
  title `Appeals and Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 9, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=840&sectionno=61&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `under the Companies Act 2013 (18 of 2013), any person aggrieved by the order of the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority under this part may prefer an appeal to the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within thirty days before the National Company`
  line `Law Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal may allow an appeal to be filed after the`
  line `expiry of the said period of thirty days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing the`
  line `appeal but such period shall not exceed fifteen days.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal against an order approving a resolution plan under section 31 may be filed on the`
  line `following grounds, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) the approved resolution plan is in contravention of the provisions of any law for the time being`
  line `in force;`
  line
  line `(ii) there has been material irregularity in exercise of the powers by the resolution professional`
  line `during the corporate insolvency resolution period;`
  line
  line `(iii) the debts owed to operational creditors of the corporate debtor have not been provided for in`
  line `the resolution plan in the manner specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(iv) the insolvency resolution process costs have not been provided for repayment in priority to all`
  line `other debts; or`
  line
  line `(v) the resolution plan does not comply with any other criteria specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) An appeal against a liquidation order passed under section 33, or sub-section (4) of section 54L,`
  line `or sub-section (4) of section 54N, may be filed on grounds of material irregularity or fraud committed in`
  line `relation to such a liquidation order.`
  line
  line `(5) An appeal against an order for initiation of corporate insolvency resolution process passed under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 54-O, may be filed on grounds of material irregularity or fraud committed in`
  line `relation to such an order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (841)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 84
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=841&sectionno=62&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the National Company`
  line `Law Appellate Tribunal may file an appeal to the Supreme Court on a question of law arising out of such`
  line `order under this Code within forty-five days from the date of receipt of such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Supreme Court may, if it is satisfied that a person was prevented by sufficient cause from`
  line `filing an appeal within forty-five days, allow the appeal to be filed within a further period not exceeding`
  line `fifteen days.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (842)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 85
  title `Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=842&sectionno=63&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `No civil court or authority shall have jurisdiction to`
  line `entertain any suit or proceedings in respect of any matter on which National Company Law Tribunal or`
  line `the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal has jurisdiction under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (843)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 86
  title `Expeditious disposal of applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=843&sectionno=64&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an application is not disposed of or an order is`
  line `not passed within the period specified in this Code, the National Company Law Tribunal or the National`
  line `Company Law Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, shall record the reasons for not doing so within the`
  line `period so specified; and the President of the National Company Law Tribunal or the Chairperson of the`
  line `National Company Law Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, may, after taking into account the`
  line `reasons so recorded, extend the period specified in the Act but not exceeding ten days.`
  line
  line `(2) No injunction shall be granted by any court, tribunal or authority in respect of any action taken, or`
  line `to be taken, in pursuance of any power conferred on the National Company Law Tribunal or the National`
  line `Company Law Appellate Tribunal under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (844)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 87
  title `Fraudulent or malicious initiation of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 10 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=844&sectionno=65&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, any person initiates the insolvency`
  line `resolution process or liquidation proceedings fraudulently or with malicious intent for any purpose other`
  line `than for the resolution of insolvency, or liquidation, as the case may be, the Adjudicating Authority may`
  line `impose upon such person a penalty which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one`
  line `crore rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If, any person initiates voluntary liquidation proceedings with the intent to defraud any person, the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority may impose upon such person a penalty which shall not be less than one lakh`
  line `rupees but may extend to one crore rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) If any person initiates the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process--`
  line
  line `(a) fraudulently or with malicious intent for any purpose other than for the resolution of`
  line `insolvency; or`
  line
  line `(b) with the intent to defraud any person,`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority may impose upon such person a penalty which shall not be less than one lakh`
  line `rupees, but may extend to one crore rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (845)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 88
  title `Fraudulent trading or wrongful trading.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=845&sectionno=66&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) If during the corporate insolvency resolution`
  line `process or a liquidation process, it is found that any business of the corporate debtor has been carried on`
  line `with intent to defraud creditors of the corporate debtor or for any fraudulent purpose, the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority may on the application of the resolution professional pass an order that any persons who were`
  line `knowingly parties to the carrying on of the business in such manner shall be liable to make such`
  line `contributions to the assets of the corporate debtor as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) On an application made by a resolution professional during the corporate insolvency resolution`
  line `process, the Adjudicating Authority may by an order direct that a director or partner of the corporate`
  line `debtor, as the case may be, shall be liable to make such contribution to the assets of the corporate debtor`
  line `as it may deem fit, if—`
  line
  line `(a) before the insolvency commencement date, such director or partner knew or ought to have`
  line `known that there was no reasonable prospect of avoiding the commencement of a corporate`
  line `insolvency resolution process in respect of such corporate debtor; and`
  line
  line `(b) such director or partner did not exercise due diligence in minimising the potential loss to the`
  line `creditors of the corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section a director or partner of the corporate debtor, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be deemed to have exercised due diligence if such diligence was reasonably expected`
  line `of a person carrying out the same functions as are carried out by such director or partner, as the case may`
  line `be, in relation to the corporate debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (846)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 89
  title `Proceedings under section 66.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=846&sectionno=67&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Adjudicating Authority has passed an order under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 66, as the case may be, it may give such further directions as`
  line `it may deem appropriate for giving effect to the order, and in particular, the Adjudicating Authority`
  line may—
  line
  line `(a) provide for the liability of any person under the order to be a charge on any debt or obligation`
  line `due from the corporate debtor to him, or on any mortgage or charge or any interest in a mortgage or`
  line `charge on assets of the corporate debtor held by or vested in him, or any person on his behalf, or any`
  line `person claiming as assignee from or through the person liable or any person acting on his behalf; and`
  line
  line `(b) from time to time, make such further directions as may be necessary for enforcing any charge`
  line `imposed under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, “assignee” includes a person to whom or in whose`
  line `favour, by the directions of the person held liable under clause (a) the debt, obligation, mortgage or`
  line `charge was created, issued or transferred or the interest created, but does not include an assignee for`
  line `valuable consideration given in good faith and without notice of any of the grounds on which the`
  line `directions have been made.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Adjudicating Authority has passed an order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 66, as the case may be, in relation to a person who is a creditor of the corporate debtor, it may, by`
  line `an order, direct that the whole or any part of any debt owed by the corporate debtor to that person and any`
  line `interest thereon shall rank in the order of priority of payment under section 53 after all other debts owed`
  line `by the corporate debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67_a:
  sectionId (57232)
  sectionNo 67A
  orderNo 90
  title `Fraudulent management of corporate debtor during pre-packaged insolvency resolution process`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 11 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57232&sectionno=67A&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[67A. Fraudulent management of corporate debtor during pre-packaged insolvency resolution`
  line `process.--On and after the pre-packaged insolvency commencement date, where an officer of the`
  line `corporate debtor manages its affairs with the intent to defraud creditors of the corporate debtor or for any`
  line `fraudulent purpose, the Adjudicating Authority may, on an application by the resolution professional,`
  line `pass an order imposing upon any such officer, a penalty which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but`
  line `may extend to one crore rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (847)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 91
  title `Punishment for concealment of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=847&sectionno=68&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Where any officer of the corporate debtor has,—`
  line
  line `(i) within the twelve months immediately preceding the insolvency commencement date,—`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully concealed any property or part of such property of the corporate debtor or`
  line `concealed any debt due to, or from, the corporate debtor, of the value of ten thousand rupees or`
  line `more; or`
  line
  line `(b) fraudulently removed any part of the property of the corporate debtor of the value of ten`
  line `thousand rupees or more; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully concealed, destroyed, mutilated or falsified any book or paper affecting or`
  line `relating to the property of the corporate debtor or its affairs, or`
  line
  line `(d) wilfully made any false entry in any book or paper affecting or relating to the property of`
  line `the corporate debtor or its affairs; or`
  line
  line `(e) fraudulently parted with, altered or made any omission in any document affecting or`
  line `relating to the property of the corporate debtor or its affairs; or`
  line
  line `(f) wilfully created any security interest over, transferred or disposed of any property of the`
  line `corporate debtor which has been obtained on credit and has not been paid for unless such`
  line `creation, transfer or disposal was in the ordinary course of the business of the corporate debtor; or`
  line
  line `(g) wilfully concealed the knowledge of the doing by others of any of the acts mentioned in`
  line `clauses (c), (d) or clause (e); or`
  line
  line `(ii) at any time after the insolvency commencement date, committed any of the acts mentioned in`
  line `sub-clause (a) to (f) of clause (i) or has the knowledge of the doing by others of any of the things`
  line `mentioned in sub-clauses (c) to (e) of clause (i); or`
  line
  line `(iii) at any time after the insolvency commencement date, taken in pawn or pledge, or otherwise`
  line `received the property knowing it to be so secured, transferred or disposed,`
  line
  line `such officer shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but`
  line `which may extend to five years, or with fine, which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend`
  line `to one crore rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall render a person liable to any punishment under this section`
  line `if he proves that he had no intent to defraud or to conceal the state of affairs of the corporate debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (848)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 92
  title `Punishment for transactions defrauding creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 30, for "On or after the insolvency commencement date, if"(w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=848&sectionno=69&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[If] an officer of the corporate debtor or`
  line `the corporate debtor—`
  line
  line `(a) has made or caused to be made any gift or transfer of, or charge on, or has caused or connived`
  line `in the execution of a decree or order against, the property of the corporate debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) has concealed or removed any part of the property of the corporate debtor within two months`
  line `before the date of any unsatisfied judgment, decree or order for payment of money obtained against`
  line `the corporate debtor,`
  line
  line `such officer of the corporate debtor or the corporate debtor, as the case may be, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year, but which may extend to five years, or`
  line `with fine, which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one crore rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be punishable under this section if the acts mentioned in clause (a)`
  line `were committed more than five years before the insolvency commencement date; or if he proves that, at`
  line `the time of commission of those acts, he had no intent to defraud the creditors of the corporate debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (849)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 93
  title `Punishment for misconduct in course of corporate insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=849&sectionno=70&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) On or`
  line `after the insolvency commencement date, where an officer of the corporate debtor`
  line
  line `(a) does not disclose to the resolution professional all the details of property of the corporate`
  line `debtor, and details of transactions thereof, or any such other information as the resolution professional`
  line `may require; or`
  line
  line `(b) does not deliver to the resolution professional all or part of the property of the corporate`
  line `debtor in his control or custody and which he is required to deliver; or`
  line
  line `(c) does not deliver to the resolution professional all books and papers in his control or custody`
  line `belonging to the corporate debtor and which he is required to deliver; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to inform there solution professional the information in his knowledge that a debt has`
  line `been falsely proved by any person during the corporate insolvency resolution process; or`
  line
  line `(e) prevents the production of any book or paper affecting or relating to the property or affairs of`
  line `the corporate debtor; or`
  line
  line `(f) accounts for any part of the property of the corporate debtor by fictitious losses or expenses, or`
  line `if he has so attempted at any meeting of the creditors of the corporate debtor within the twelve`
  line `months immediately preceding the insolvency commencement date,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years, but which`
  line `may extend to five years, or with fine, which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one`
  line `crore rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall render a person liable to any punishment under this section`
  line `if he proves that he had no intent to do so in relation to the state of affairs of the corporate debtor.`
  line
  line `(2) If an insolvency professional deliberately contravenes the provisions of this Part he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to five lakhs rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (850)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 94
  title `Punishment for falsification of books of corporate debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=850&sectionno=71&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `On and after the insolvency`
  line `commencement date, where any person destroys, mutilates, alters or falsifies any books, papers or`
  line `securities, or makes or is in the knowledge of making of any false or fraudulent entry in any register,`
  line `books of account or document belonging to the corporate debtor with intent to defraud or deceive any`
  line `person, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years, but`
  line `which may extend to five years, or with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend`
  line `to one crore rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (851)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 95
  title `Punishment for wilful and material omissions from statements relating to affairs of corporate debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=851&sectionno=72&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Where an officer of the corporate debtor makes any material and wilful omission in`
  line `any statement relating to the affairs of the corporate debtor, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for`
  line `a term which shall not be less than three years but which may extend to five years, or with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one crore rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (852)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 96
  title `Punishment for false representations to creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=852&sectionno=73&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Where any officer of the corporate`
  line debtor—
  line
  line `(a) on or after the insolvency commencement date, makes a false representation or commits any`
  line `fraud for the purpose of obtaining the consent of the creditors of the corporate debtor or any of them`
  line `to an agreement with reference to the affairs of the corporate debtor, during the corporate insolvency`
  line `resolution process, or the liquidation process;`
  line
  line `(b) prior to the insolvency commencement date, has made any false representation, or committed`
  line `any fraud, for that purpose,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years, but may`
  line `extend to five years or with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one crore`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (853)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 97
  title `Punishment for contravention of moratorium or the resolution plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=853&sectionno=74&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `corporate debtor or any of its officer violates the provisions of section 14, any such officer who`
  line `knowingly or wilfully committed or authorised or permitted such contravention shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years, but may extend to five years or with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to three lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any creditor violates the provisions of section 14, any person who knowingly and wilfully`
  line `authorised or permitted such contravention by a creditor shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than one year, but may extend to five years, or with fine which shall not be less`
  line `than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one crore rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the corporate debtor, any of its officers or creditors or any person on whom the approved`
  line `resolution plan is binding under section 31, knowingly and wilfully contravenes any of the terms of such`
  line `resolution plan or abets such contravention, such corporate debtor, officer, creditor or person shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment of not less than one year, but may extend to five years, or with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one crore rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (854)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 98
  title `Punishment for false information furnished in application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=854&sectionno=75&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Where any person furnishes`
  line `information in the application made under section 7, which is false in material particulars, knowing it to`
  line `be false or omits any material fact, knowing it to be material, such person shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to one crore rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (855)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 99
  title `Punishment for non-disclosure of dispute or payment of debt by operational creditor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 31, for "repayment" (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=855&sectionno=76&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `76. Punishment for non-disclosure of dispute or ^1`
  line `[payment] of debt by operational creditor.— Where—`
  line
  line `(a) an operational creditor has wilfully or knowingly concealed in an application under section 9`
  line `the fact that the corporate debtor had notified him of a dispute in respect of the unpaid operational`
  line `debt or the full and final ^1 [payment of the unpaid operational debt; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who knowingly and wilfully authorised or permitted such concealment under`
  line `clause (a),`
  line
  line `such operational creditor or person, as the case may be, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than one year but may extend to five years or with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `one lakh rupees but may extend to one crore rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (856)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 100
  title `Punishment for providing false information in application made by corporate debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes `1.The Explanation omitted by Act 26 of 2021, s. 12 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=856&sectionno=77&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line Where
  line
  line `(a) a corporate debtor provides information in the application under section 10 which is false in`
  line `material particulars, knowing it to be false and omits any material fact, knowing it to be material; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who knowingly and wilfully authorised or permitted the furnishing of such`
  line `information under sub-clause (a),`
  line
  line `such corporate debtor or person, as the case may be, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than three years, but which may extend to five years or with fine which shall not`
  line `be less than one lakh rupees, but which may extend to one crore rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line ^1*****
obj_root_law_sections_77_a:
  sectionId (57233)
  sectionNo 77A
  orderNo 101
  title `Punishment for offences related to pre-packaged insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content
  footnotes `1Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 13 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=57233&sectionno=77A&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[77A. Punishment for offences related to prepackaged insolvency resolution process.--(1)`
  line Where--
  line
  line `(a) a corporate debtor provides any information in the application under section 54C which is`
  line `false in material particulars, knowing it to be false or omits any material fact, knowing it to be`
  line `material; or`
  line
  line `(b) a corporate debtor provides any information in the list of claims or the preliminary`
  line `information memorandum submitted under sub-section (1) of section 54G which is false in material`
  line `particulars, knowing it to be false or omits any material fact, knowing it to be material; or`
  line
  line `(c) any person who knowingly and wilfully authorised or permitted the furnishing of such`
  line `information under sub-clauses (a) and (b),`
  line
  line `such corporate debtor or person, as the case may be, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than three years, but which may extend to five years or with fine which shall not`
  line `be less than one lakh rupees, but which may extend to one crore rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If a director or partner of the corporate debtor, as the case may be, deliberately contravenes the`
  line `provisions of Chapter III-A, such person shall be punishable with imprisonment for not less than three`
  line `years, but which may extend to five years, or with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but`
  line `which may extend to one crore rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and sections 75, 76 and 77, an application shall be`
  line `deemed to be false in material particulars in case the facts mentioned or omitted in the application, if true,`
  line `or not omitted from the application, as the case may be, would have been sufficient to determine the`
  line `existence of a default under this Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (857)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 102
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=857&sectionno=78&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `This Part shall apply to matters relating to fresh start, insolvency and bankruptcy`
  line `of individuals and partnership firms where the amount of the default is not less than one thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, specify the minimum amount of default`
  line `of higher value which shall not be more than one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (858)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 103
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=858&sectionno=79&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(1) “Adjudicating Authority” means the Debt Recovery Tribunal constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions`
  line `Act, 1993 (51 of 1993);`
  line
  line `(2) “associate” of the debtor means—`
  line
  line `(a) a person who belongs to the immediate family of the debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) a person who is a relative of the debtor or a relative of the spouse of the debtor;`
  line
  line `(c) a person who is in partnership with the debtor;`
  line
  line `(d) a person who is a spouse or a relative of any person with whom the debtor is in`
  line partnership;
  line
  line `(e) a person who is employer of the debtor or employee of the debtor;`
  line
  line `(f) a person who is a trustee of a trust in which the beneficiaries of the trust include a debtor,`
  line `or the terms of the trust confer a power on the trustee which may be exercised for the benefit of`
  line `the debtor; and`
  line
  line `(g) a company, where the debtor or the debtor along with his associates, own more than fifty`
  line `per cent. of the share capital of the company or control the appointment of the board of directors`
  line `of the company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this clause, “relative”, with reference to any person, means`
  line `anyone who is related to another, if—`
  line
  line `(i) they are members of a Hindu Undivided Family;`
  line
  line `(ii) one person is related to the other in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(3) “bankrupt” means—`
  line
  line `(a) a debtor who has been adjudged as bankrupt by a bankruptcy order under section 126;`
  line
  line `(b) each of the partners of a firm, where a bankruptcy order under section 126 has been made`
  line `against a firm; or`
  line
  line `(c) any person adjudged as an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(4) “bankruptcy” means the state of being bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(5) “bankruptcy debt”, in relation to a bankrupt, means—`
  line
  line `(a) any debt owed by him as on the bankruptcy commencement date;`
  line
  line `(b) any debt for which he may become liable after bankruptcy commencement date but before`
  line `his discharge by reason of any transaction entered into before the bankruptcy commencement`
  line `date; and`
  line
  line `(c) any interest which is a part of the debt under section 171;`
  line
  line `(6) “bankruptcy commencement date” means the date on which a bankruptcy order is passed by`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority under section 126;`
  line
  line `(7) “bankruptcy order” means an order passed by an Adjudicating Authority under section 126;`
  line
  line `(8) “bankruptcy process” means a process against a debtor under Chapters IV and V of this Part;`
  line
  line `(9) “bankruptcy trustee” means the insolvency professional appointed as a trustee for the estate of`
  line `the bankrupt under section 125;`
  line
  line `(10) “Chapter” means a chapter under this Part;`
  line
  line `(11) “committee of creditors” means a committee constituted under section 134;`
  line
  line `(12) “debtor” includes a judgment-debtor;`
  line
  line `(13) “discharge order” means an order passed by the Adjudicating Authority discharging the`
  line `debtor under sections 92, 119 and section 138, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(14) “excluded assets” for the purposes of this part includes—`
  line
  line `(a) unencumbered tools, books, vehicles and other equipment as are necessary to the debtor`
  line `or bankrupt for his personal use or for the purpose of his employment, business or vocation,`
  line
  line `(b) unencumbered furniture, household equipment and provisions as are necessary for`
  line `satisfying the basic domestic needs of the bankrupt and his immediate family;`
  line
  line `(c) any unencumbered personal ornaments of such value, as may be prescribed, of the debtor`
  line `or his immediate family which cannot be parted with, in accordance with religious usage;`
  line
  line `(d) any unencumbered life insurance policy or pension plan taken in the name of debtor or his`
  line `immediate family; and`
  line
  line `(e) an unencumbered single dwelling unit owned by the debtor of such value as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(15) “excluded debt” means—`
  line
  line `(a) liability to pay fine imposed by a court or tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) liability to pay damages for negligence, nuisance or breach of a statutory, contractual or`
  line `other legal obligation;`
  line
  line `(c) liability to pay maintenance to any person under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(d) liability in relation to a student loan; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other debt as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(16) “firm” means a body of individuals carrying on business in partnership whether or not`
  line `registered under section 59 of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932);`
  line
  line `(17) “immediate family” of the debtor means his spouse, dependent children and dependent`
  line parents;
  line
  line `(18) “partnership debt” means a debt for which all the partners in a firm are jointly liable;`
  line
  line `(19) “qualifying debt” means amount due, which includes interest or any other sum due in respect`
  line `of the amounts owed under any contract, by the debtor for a liquidated sum either immediately or at`
  line `certain future time and does not include—`
  line
  line `(a) an excluded debt;`
  line
  line `(b) a debt to the extent it is secured; and`
  line
  line `(c) any debt which has been incurred three months prior to the date of the application for`
  line `fresh start process;`
  line
  line `(20) “repayment plan” means a plan prepared by the debtor in consultation with the resolution`
  line `professional under section 105 containing a proposal to the committee of creditors for restructuring of`
  line `his debts or affairs;`
  line
  line `(21) “resolution professional” means an insolvency professional appointed under this part as a`
  line `resolution professional for conducting the fresh start process or insolvency resolution process;`
  line
  line `(22) “undischarged bankrupt” means a bankrupt who has not received a discharge order under`
  line `section 138.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (859)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 104
  title `Eligibility for making an application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=859&sectionno=80&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) A debtor, who is unable to pay his debt and fulfils`
  line `the conditions specified in sub-section (2), shall be entitled to make an application for a fresh start for`
  line `discharge of his qualifying debt under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) A debtor may apply, either personally or through a resolution professional, for a fresh start under`
  line `this Chapter in respect of his qualifying debts to the Adjudicating Authority if —`
  line
  line `(a) the gross annual income of the debtor does not exceed sixty thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) the aggregate value of the assets of the debtor does not exceed twenty thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) the aggregate value of the qualifying debts does not exceed thirty-five thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(d) he is not an undischarged bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(e) he does not own a dwelling unit, irrespective of whether it is encumbered or not;`
  line
  line `(f) a fresh start process, insolvency resolution process or bankruptcy process is not subsisting`
  line `against him; and`
  line
  line `(g) no previous fresh start order under this Chapter has been made in relation to him in the`
  line `preceding twelve months of the date of the application for fresh start.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (860)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 105
  title `Application for fresh start order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=860&sectionno=81&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application is filed under section 80 by a`
  line `debtor, an interim-moratorium shall commence on the date of filing of said application in relation to all`
  line `the debts and shall cease to have effect on the date of admission or rejection of such application, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) During the interim-moratorium period,—`
  line
  line `(i) any legal action or legal proceeding pending in respect of any of his debts shall be deemed to`
  line `have been stayed; and`
  line
  line `(ii) no creditor shall initiate any legal action or proceedings in respect of such debt.`
  line
  line `(3) The application under section 80 shall be in such form and manner and accompanied by such fee,`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The application under sub-section (3) shall contain the following information supported by an`
  line `affidavit, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a list of all debts owed by the debtor as on the date of the said application along with details`
  line `relating to the amount of each debt, interest payable thereon and the names of the creditors to whom`
  line `each debt is owed;`
  line
  line `(b) the interest payable on the debts and the rate thereof stipulated in the contract;`
  line
  line `(c) a list of security held in respect of any of the debts;`
  line
  line `(d) the financial information of the debtor and his immediate family up to two years prior to the`
  line `date of the application;`
  line
  line `(e) the particulars of the debtor's personal details, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(f) the reasons for making the application;`
  line
  line `(g) the particulars of any legal proceedings which, to the debtor's knowledge has been`
  line `commenced against him;`
  line
  line `(h) the confirmation that no previous fresh start order under this Chapter has been made in respect`
  line `of the qualifying debts of the debtor in the preceding twelve months of the date of the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (861)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 106
  title `Appointment of resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=861&sectionno=82&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an application under section 80 is filed by`
  line `the debtor through a resolution professional, the Adjudicating Authority shall direct the Board within`
  line `seven days of the date of receipt of the application and shall seek confirmation from the Board that there`
  line `are no disciplinary proceedings against the resolution professional who has submitted such application.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall communicate to the Adjudicating Authority in writing either—`
  line
  line `(a) confirmation of the appointment of the resolution professional who filed an application under`
  line `sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) rejection of the appointment of the resolution professional who filed an application under`
  line `sub-section (1) and nominate a resolution professional suitable for the fresh start process.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application under section 80 is filed by the debtor himself and not through the resolution`
  line `professional, the Adjudicating Authority shall direct the Board within seven days of the date of the receipt`
  line `of an application to nominate a resolution professional for the fresh start process.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall nominate a resolution professional within ten days of receiving the direction`
  line `issued by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Adjudicating Authority shall by order appoint the resolution professional recommended or`
  line `nominated by the Board under sub-section (2) or sub-section (4), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) A resolution professional appointed by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (5) shall be`
  line `provided a copy of the application for fresh start.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (862)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 107
  title `Examination of application by resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=862&sectionno=83&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall`
  line `examine the application made under section 80 within ten days of his appointment, and submit a report to`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority, either recommending acceptance or rejection of the application.`
  line
  line `(2) The report referred to in sub-section (1) shall contain the details of the amounts mentioned in the`
  line `application which in the opinion of the resolution professional are—`
  line
  line `(a) qualifying debts; and`
  line
  line `(b) liabilities eligible for discharge under sub-section (3) of section 92.`
  line
  line `(3) The resolution professional may call for such further information or explanation in connection`
  line `with the application as may be required from the debtor or any other person who, in the opinion of the`
  line `resolution professional, may provide such information.`
  line
  line `(4) The debtor or any other person, as the case may be, shall furnish such information or explanation`
  line `within seven days of receipt of the request under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The resolution professional shall presume that the debtor is unable to pay his debts at the date of`
  line `the application if—`
  line
  line `(a) in his opinion the information supplied in the application indicates that the debtor is unable to`
  line `pay his debts and he has no reason to believe that the information supplied is incorrect or incomplete;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) he has reason to believe that there is no change in the financial circumstances of the debtor`
  line `since the date of the application enabling the debtor to pay his debts.`
  line
  line `(6) The resolution professional shall reject the application, if in his opinion—`
  line
  line `(a) the debtor does not satisfy the conditions specified under section 80; or`
  line
  line `(b) the debts disclosed in the application by the debtor are not qualifying debts; or`
  line
  line `(c) the debtor has deliberately made a false representation or omission in the application or with`
  line `respect to the documents or information submitted.`
  line
  line `(7) The resolution professional shall record the reasons for recommending the acceptance or rejection`
  line `of the application in the report to the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (1) and shall give a copy`
  line `of the report to the debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (863)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 108
  title `Admission or rejection of application by Adjudicating Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=863&sectionno=84&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating`
  line `Authority may within fourteen days from the date of submission of the report by the resolution`
  line `professional, pass an order either admitting or rejecting the application made under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 81.`
  line
  line `(2) The order passed under sub-section (1) accepting the application shall state the amount which has`
  line `been accepted as qualifying debts by the resolution professional and other amounts eligible for discharge`
  line `under section 92 for the purposes of the fresh start order.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (1) along with a copy`
  line `of the application shall be provided to the creditors mentioned in the application within seven days of the`
  line `passing of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (864)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 109
  title `Effect of admission of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=864&sectionno=85&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the date of admission of the application, the`
  line `moratorium period shall commence in respect of all the debts.`
  line
  line `(2) During the moratorium period--`
  line
  line `(a) any pending legal action or legal proceeding in respect of any debt shall be deemed to have`
  line `been stayed; and`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the provisions of section 86, the creditors shall not initiate any legal action or`
  line `proceedings in respect of any debt.`
  line
  line `(3) During the moratorium period, the debtor shall--`
  line
  line `(a) not act as a director of any company, or directly or indirectly take part in or be concerned in`
  line `the promotion, formation or management of a company;`
  line
  line `(b) not dispose of or alienate any of his assets;`
  line
  line `(c) inform his business partners that he is undergoing a fresh start process;`
  line
  line `(d) be required to inform prior to entering into any financial or commercial transaction of such`
  line `value as may be notified by the Central Government, either individually or jointly, that he is`
  line `undergoing a fresh start process;`
  line
  line `(e) disclose the name under which he enters into business transactions, if it is different from the`
  line `name in the application admitted under section 84;`
  line
  line `(f) not travel outside India except with the permission of the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The moratorium ceases to have effect at the end of the period of one hundred and eighty days`
  line `beginning with the date of admission unless the order admitting the application is revoked under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 91.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (865)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 110
  title `Objections by creditor and their examination by resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=865&sectionno=86&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any creditor`
  line `mentioned in the order of the Adjudicating Authority under section 84 to whom a qualifying debt is owed`
  line `may, within a period of ten days from the date of receipt of the order under section 84, object only on the`
  line `following grounds, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) inclusion of a debt as a qualifying debt; or`
  line
  line `(b) incorrectness of the details of the qualifying debt specified in the order under section 84.`
  line
  line `(2) A creditor may file an objection under sub-section (1) by way of an application to the resolution`
  line professional.
  line
  line `(3) The application under sub-section (2) shall be supported by such information and documents as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The resolution professional shall consider every objection made under this section.`
  line
  line `(5) The resolution professional shall examine the objections under sub-section (2) and either accept or`
  line `reject the objections, within ten days of the date of the application.`
  line
  line `(6) The resolution professional may examine any matter that appears to him to be relevant to the`
  line `making of a final list of qualifying debts for the purposes of section 92.`
  line
  line `(7) On the basis of the examination under sub-section (5) or sub-section (6), the resolution`
  line `professional shall—`
  line
  line `(a) prepare an amended list of qualifying debts for the purpose of the discharge order;`
  line
  line `(b) make an application to the Adjudicating Authority for directions under section 90; or`
  line
  line `(c) take such other steps as he considers necessary in relation to the debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (866)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 111
  title `Application against decision of resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=866&sectionno=87&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The debtor or the creditor who is`
  line `aggrieved by the action taken by the resolution professional under section 86 may, within ten days of such`
  line `decision, make an application to the Adjudicating Authority challenging such action on any of the`
  line `following grounds, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) that the resolution professional has not given an opportunity to the debtor or the creditor to`
  line `make a representation; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the resolution professional colluded with the other party in arriving at the decision; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the resolution professional has not complied with the requirements of section 86.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall decide the application referred to in sub-section (1) within`
  line `fourteen days of such application, and make an order as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the application under sub-section (1) has been allowed by the Adjudicating Authority, it`
  line `shall forward its order to the Board and the Board may take such action as may be required under Chapter`
  line `VI of Part IV against the resolution professional.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (867)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 112
  title `General duties of debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=867&sectionno=88&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The debtor shall—`
  line
  line `(a) make available to the resolution professional all information relating to his affairs, attend`
  line `meetings and comply with the requests of the resolution professional in relation to the fresh start`
  line process.
  line
  line `(b) inform the resolution professional as soon as reasonably possible of—`
  line
  line `(i) any material error or omission in relation to the information or document supplied to the`
  line `resolution professional; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any change in financial circumstances after the date of application, where such change has`
  line `an impact on the fresh start process.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (868)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 113
  title `Replacement of resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=868&sectionno=89&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the debtor or the creditor is of the opinion`
  line `that the resolution professional appointed under section 82 is required to be replaced, he may apply to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority for the replacement of such resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall within seven days of the receipt of the application under`
  line `sub-section (1) make a reference to the Board for replacement of the resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall, within ten days of the receipt of a reference from the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `under sub-section (2), recommend the name of an insolvency professional to the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `against whom no disciplinary proceedings are pending.`
  line
  line `(4) The Adjudicating Authority shall appoint another resolution professional for the purposes of the`
  line `fresh start process on the basis of the recommendation by the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Adjudicating Authority may give directions to the resolution professional replaced under`
  line `sub-section (4)—`
  line
  line `(a) to share all information with the new resolution professional in respect of the fresh start`
  line `process; and`
  line
  line `(b) to co-operate with the new resolution professional as may be required.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (869)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 114
  title `Directions for compliances of restrictions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=869&sectionno=90&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional may apply to`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority for any of the following directions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) compliance of any restrictions referred to in sub-section (3) of section 85, in case of`
  line `non-compliance by the debtor; or`
  line
  line `(b) compliance of the duties of the debtor referred to in section 88, in case of non-compliance by`
  line `the debtor.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional may apply to the Adjudicating Authority for directions in relation to`
  line `any other matter under this Chapter for which no specific provisions have been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (870)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 115
  title `Revocation of order admitting application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=870&sectionno=91&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional may submit an`
  line `application to the Adjudicating Authority seeking revocation of its order made under section 84 on the`
  line `following grounds, namely :—`
  line
  line `(a) if due to any change in the financial circumstances of the debtor, the debtor is ineligible for a`
  line `fresh start process; or`
  line
  line `(b) non-compliance by the debtor of the restrictions imposed under sub-section (3) of section 85;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) if the debtor has acted in a mala fide manner and has wilfully failed to comply with the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall, within fourteen days of the receipt of the application under subsection`
  line
  line `(1), may by order admit or reject the application.`
  line
  line `(3) On passing of the order admitting the application referred to in sub-section (1) , the moratorium`
  line `and the fresh start process shall cease to have effect.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under this section shall be provided to`
  line `the Board for the purpose of recording an entry in the register referred to in section 196.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (871)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 116
  title `Discharge order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=871&sectionno=92&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall prepare a final list of qualifying debts`
  line `and submit such list to the Adjudicating Authority at least seven days before the moratorium period`
  line `comes to an end.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall pass a discharge order at the end of the moratorium period for`
  line `discharge of the debtor from the qualifying debts mentioned in the list under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), the Adjudicating Authority shall discharge`
  line `the debtor from the following liabilities, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) penalties in respect of the qualifying debts from the date of application till the date of the`
  line `discharge order;`
  line
  line `(b) interest including penal interest in respect of the qualifying debts from the date of application`
  line `till the date of the discharge order; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other sums owed under any contract in respect of the qualifying debts from the date of`
  line `application till the date of the discharge order.`
  line
  line `(4) The discharge order shall not discharge the debtor from any debt not included in sub-section (2)`
  line `and from any liability not included under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The discharge order shall be forwarded to the Board for the purpose of recording an entry in the`
  line `register referred to in section 196.`
  line
  line `(6) A discharge order under sub-section (2) shall not discharge any other person from any liability in`
  line `respect of the qualifying debts.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (872)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 117
  title `Standard of conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=872&sectionno=93&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `The resolution professional shall perform his functions and duties in`
  line `compliance with the code of conduct provided under section 208.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (873)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 118
  title `Application by debtor to initiate insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=873&sectionno=94&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) A debtor who commits a`
  line `default may apply, either personally or through a resolution professional, to the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `for initiating the insolvency resolution process, by submitting an application.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the debtor is a partner of a firm, such debtor shall not apply under this Chapter to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority in respect of the firm unless all or a majority of the partners of the firm file the`
  line `application jointly.`
  line
  line `(3) An application under sub-section (1) shall be submitted only in respect of debts which are not`
  line `excluded debts.`
  line
  line `(4) A debtor shall not be entitled to make an application under sub-section (1) if he is—`
  line
  line `(a) an undischarged bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(b) undergoing a fresh start process;`
  line
  line `(c) undergoing an insolvency resolution process; or`
  line
  line `(d) undergoing a bankruptcy process.`
  line
  line `(5) A debtor shall not be eligible to apply under sub-section (1) if an application under this Chapter`
  line `has been admitted in respect of the debtor during the period of twelve months preceding the date of`
  line `submission of the application under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) The application referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in such form and manner and accompanied`
  line `with such fee as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (874)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 119
  title `Application by creditor to initiate insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=874&sectionno=95&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) A creditor may apply`
  line `either by himself, or jointly with other creditors, or through a resolution professional to the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority for initiating an insolvency resolution process under this section by submitting an application.`
  line
  line `(2) A creditor may apply under sub-section (1) in relation to any partnership debt owed to him for`
  line `initiating an insolvency resolution process against—`
  line
  line `(a) any one or more partners of the firm; or`
  line
  line `(b) the firm.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application has been made against one partner in a firm, any other application against`
  line `another partner in the same firm shall be presented in or transferred to the Adjudicating Authority in`
  line `which the first mentioned application is pending for adjudication and such Adjudicating Authority may`
  line `give such directions for consolidating the proceedings under the applications as it thinks just.`
  line
  line `(4) An application under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied with details and documents relating`
  line to—
  line
  line `(a) the debts owed by the debtor to the creditor or creditors submitting the application for`
  line `insolvency resolution process as on the date of application;`
  line
  line `(b) the failure by the debtor to pay the debt within a period of fourteen days of the service of the`
  line `notice of demand; and`
  line
  line `(c) relevant evidence of such default or non-repayment of debt.`
  line
  line `(5) The creditor shall also provide a copy of the application made under sub-section (1) to the debtor.`
  line
  line `(6) The application referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in such form and manner and accompanied`
  line `by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The details and documents required to be submitted under sub-section (4) shall be such as may be`
  line specified.
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (875)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 120
  title `Interim moratorium.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=875&sectionno=96&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application is filed under section 94 or section 95—`
  line
  line `(a) an interim-moratorium shall commence on the date of the application in relation to all the`
  line `debts and shall cease to have effect on the date of admission of such application; and`
  line
  line `(b) during the interim-moratorium period—`
  line
  line `(i) any legal action or proceeding pending in respect of any debt shall be deemed to have been`
  line `stayed; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the creditors of the debtor shall not initiate any legal action or proceedings in respect of`
  line `any debt.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the application has been made in relation to a firm, the interim-moratorium under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall operate against all the partners of the firm as on the date of the application.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to such transactions as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with any financial sector regulator.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (876)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 121
  title `Appointment of resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=876&sectionno=97&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the application under section 94 or 95 is filed`
  line `through a resolution professional, the Adjudicating Authority shall direct the Board within seven days of`
  line `the date of the application to confirm that there are no disciplinary proceedings pending against resolution`
  line professional.
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall within seven days of receipt of directions under sub-section (1) communicate to`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority in writing either--`
  line
  line `(a) confirming the appointment of the resolution professional; or`
  line
  line `(b) rejecting the appointment of the resolution professional and nominating another resolution`
  line `professional for the insolvency resolution process.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application under section 94 or 95 is filed by the debtor or the creditor himself, as the`
  line `case may be, and not through the resolution professional, the Adjudicating Authority shall direct the`
  line `Board, within seven days of the filing of such application, to nominate a resolution professional for the`
  line `insolvency resolution process.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall nominate a resolution professional within ten days of receiving the direction`
  line `issued by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Adjudicating Authority shall by order appoint the resolution professional recommended under`
  line `sub-section (2) or as nominated by the Board under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) A resolution professional appointed by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (5) shall be`
  line `provided a copy of the application for insolvency resolution process.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (877)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 122
  title `Replacement of resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=877&sectionno=98&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the debtor or the creditor is of the opinion`
  line `that the resolution professional appointed under section 97 is required to be replaced, he may apply to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority for the replacement of such resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall within seven days of the receipt of the application under`
  line `sub-section (1) make a reference to the Board for replacement of the resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall, within ten days of the receipt of a reference from the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `under sub-section (2), recommend the name of the resolution professional to the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `against whom no disciplinary proceedings are pending.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the creditors may apply to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority for replacement of the resolution professional where it has been decided in the`
  line `meeting of the creditors, to replace the resolution professional with a new resolution professional for`
  line `implementation of the repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Adjudicating Authority admits an application made under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (4), it shall direct the Board to confirm that there are no disciplinary proceedings pending`
  line `against the proposed resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall send a communication within ten days of receipt of the direction under`
  line `sub-section (5) either—`
  line
  line `(a) confirming appointment of the nominated resolution professional; or`
  line
  line `(b) rejecting appointment of the nominated resolution professional and recommend a new`
  line `resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(7) On the basis of the communication of the Board under sub-section (3) or sub-section (6), the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority shall pass an order appointing a new resolution professional.`
  line
  line `(8) The Adjudicating Authority may give directions to the resolution professional replaced under`
  line `sub-section (7)—`
  line
  line `(a) to share all information with the new resolution professional in respect of the insolvency`
  line `resolution process; and`
  line
  line `(b) to co-operate with the new resolution professional in such matters as may be required.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (878)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 123
  title `Submission of report by resolution professional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=878&sectionno=99&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall`
  line `examine the application referred to in section 94 or section 95, as the case may be, within ten days of his`
  line `appointment, and submit a report to the Adjudicating Authority recommending for approval or rejection`
  line `of the application.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the application has been filed under section 95, the resolution professional may require the`
  line `debtor to prove repayment of the debt claimed as unpaid by the creditor by furnishing—`
  line
  line `(a) evidence of electronic transfer of the unpaid amount from the bank account of the debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) evidence of encashment of a cheque issued by the debtor; or`
  line
  line `(c) a signed acknowledgment by the creditor accepting receipt of dues.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the debt for which an application has been filed by a creditor is registered with the`
  line `information utility, the debtor shall not be entitled to dispute the validity of such debt.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of examining an application, the resolution professional may seek such further`
  line `information or explanation in connection with the application as may be required from the debtor or the`
  line `creditor or any other person who, in the opinion of the resolution professional, may provide such`
  line information.
  line
  line `(5) The person from whom information or explanation is sought under sub-section (4) shall furnish`
  line `such information or explanation within seven days of receipt of the request.`
  line
  line `(6) The resolution professional shall examine the application and ascertain that—`
  line
  line `(a) the application satisfies the requirements set out in section 94 or 95;`
  line
  line `(b) the applicant has provided information and given explanation sought by the resolution`
  line `professional under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(7) After examination of the application under sub-section (6), he may recommend acceptance or`
  line `rejection of the application in his report.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the resolution professional finds that the debtor is eligible for a fresh start under Chapter II,`
  line `the resolution professional shall submit a report recommending that the application by the debtor under`
  line `section 94 be treated as an application under section 81 by the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(9) The resolution professional shall record the reasons for recommending the acceptance or rejection`
  line `of the application in the report under sub-section (7).`
  line
  line `(10) The resolution professional shall give a copy of the report under sub-section (7) to the debtor or`
  line `the creditor, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (879)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 124
  title `Admission or rejection of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=879&sectionno=100&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Authority shall, within fourteen`
  line `days from the date of submission of the report under section 99 pass an order either admitting or rejecting`
  line `the application referred to in section 94 or 95, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Adjudicating Authority admits an application under sub-section (1), it may, on the`
  line `request of the resolution professional, issue instructions for the purpose of conducting negotiations`
  line `between the debtor and creditors and for arriving at a repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Authority shall provide a copy of the order passed under sub-section (1) along`
  line `with the report of the resolution professional and the application referred to in section 94 or 95, as the`
  line `case may be, to the creditors within seven days from the date of the said order.`
  line
  line `(4) If the application referred to in section 94 or 95, as the case may be, is rejected by the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority on the basis of report submitted by the resolution professional that the application`
  line `was made with the intention to defraud his creditors or the resolution professional, the order under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall record that the creditor is entitled to file for a bankruptcy order under Chapter IV.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (880)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 125
  title Moratorium.
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=880&sectionno=101&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the application is admitted under section 100, a moratorium shall`
  line `commence in relation to all the debts and shall cease to have effect at the end of the period of one hundred`
  line `and eighty days beginning with the date of admission of the application or on the date the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority passes an order on the repayment plan under section 114, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) During the moratorium period—`
  line
  line `(a) any pending legal action or proceeding in respect of any debt shall be deemed to have been`
  line stayed;
  line
  line `(b) the creditors shall not initiate any legal action or legal proceedings in respect of any debt; and`
  line
  line `(c) the debtor shall not transfer, alienate, encumber or dispose of any of his assets or his legal`
  line `rights or beneficial interest therein;`
  line
  line `(3) Where an order admitting the application under section 96 has been made in relation to a firm, the`
  line `moratorium under sub-section (1) shall operate against all the partners of the firm.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply to such transactions as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with any financial sector regulator.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (881)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 126
  title `Public notice and claims from creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=881&sectionno=102&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Authority shall issue a public`
  line `notice within seven days of passing the order under section 100 inviting claims from all creditors within`
  line `twenty-one days of such issue.`
  line
  line `(2) The notice under sub-section (1) shall include—`
  line
  line `(a) details of the order admitting the application;`
  line
  line `(b) particulars of the resolution professional with whom the claims are to be registered; and`
  line
  line `(c) the last date for submission of claims.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) published in at least one English and one vernacular newspaper which is in circulation in the`
  line `state where the debtor resides;`
  line
  line `(b) affixed in the premises of the Adjudicating Authority; and`
  line
  line `(c) placed on the website of the Adjudicating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (882)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 127
  title `Registering of claims by creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=882&sectionno=103&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) The creditors shall register claims with the resolution`
  line `professional by sending details of the claims by way of electronic communications or through courier,`
  line `speed post or registered letter.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the claims referred to in sub-section (1), the creditor shall provide to the resolution`
  line `professional, personal information and such particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (883)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 128
  title `Preparation of list of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=883&sectionno=104&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall prepare a list of`
  line `creditors on the basis of—`
  line
  line `(a) the information disclosed in the application filed by the debtor under section 94 or 95, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) claims received by the resolution professional under section 102.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional shall prepare the list mentioned in sub-section (1) within thirty days`
  line `from the date of the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (884)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 129
  title `Repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=884&sectionno=105&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) The debtor shall prepare, in consultation with the resolution`
  line `professional, a repayment plan containing a proposal to the creditors for restructuring of his debts or`
  line affairs.
  line
  line `(2) The repayment plan may authorise or require the resolution professional to—`
  line
  line `(a) carry on the debtor's business or trade on his behalf or in his name; or`
  line
  line `(b) realise the assets of the debtor; or`
  line
  line `(c) administer or dispose of any funds of the debtor.`
  line
  line `(3) The repayment plan shall include the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) justification for preparation of such repayment plan and reasons on the basis of which the`
  line `creditors may agree upon the plan;`
  line
  line `(b) provision for payment of fee to the resolution professional;`
  line
  line `(c) such other matters as may be specified`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (885)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 130
  title `Report of resolution professional on repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=885&sectionno=106&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall`
  line `submit the repayment plan under section 105 along with his report on such plan to the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority within a period of twenty-one days from the last date of submission of claims under`
  line `section 102.`
  line
  line `(2) The report referred in sub-section (1) shall include that—`
  line
  line `(a) the repayment plan is in compliance with the provisions of any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) the repayment plan has a reasonable prospect of being approved and implemented; and`
  line
  line `(c) there is a necessity of summoning a meeting of the creditors, if required, to consider the`
  line `repayment plan:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the resolution professional recommends that a meeting of the creditors is not`
  line `required to be summoned, reasons for the same shall be provided.`
  line
  line `(3) The report referred to in sub-section (2) shall also specify the date on which, and the time and`
  line `place at which, the meeting should be held if he is of the opinion that a meeting of the creditors should be`
  line summoned.
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-section (3)—`
  line
  line `(a) the date on which the meeting is to be held shall be not less than fourteen days and not more`
  line `than twenty eight days from the date of submission of report under sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) the resolution professional shall consider the convenience of creditors in fixing the date and`
  line `venue of the meeting of the creditors.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (886)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 131
  title `Summoning of meeting of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=886&sectionno=107&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall issue a notice`
  line `calling the meeting of the creditors at least fourteen days before the date fixed for such meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional shall send the notice of the meeting to the list of creditors prepared`
  line `under section 104.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice sent under sub-section (1) shall state the address of the Adjudicating Authority to`
  line `which the repayment plan and report of the resolution professional on the repayment plan has been`
  line `submitted and shall be accompanied by—`
  line
  line `(a) a copy of the repayment plan;`
  line
  line `(b) a copy of the statement of affairs of the debtor;`
  line
  line `(c) a copy of the said report of the resolution professional; and`
  line
  line `(d) forms for proxy voting.`
  line
  line `(4) The proxy voting, including electronic proxy voting shall take place in such manner and form as`
  line `may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (887)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 132
  title `Conduct of meeting of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=887&sectionno=108&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) The meeting of the creditors shall be conducted in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this section and sections 109,110 and 111.`
  line
  line `(2) In the meeting of the creditors, the creditors may decide to approve, modify or reject the`
  line `repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(3) The resolution professional shall ensure that if modifications are suggested by the creditors,`
  line `consent of the debtor shall be obtained for each modification.`
  line
  line `(4) The resolution professional may for a sufficient cause adjourn the meeting of the creditors for a`
  line `period of not more than seven days at a time.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (888)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 133
  title `Voting rights in meeting of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=888&sectionno=109&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) A creditor shall be entitled to vote at every meeting`
  line `of the creditors in respect of the repayment plan in accordance with the voting share assigned to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional shall determine the voting share to be assigned to each creditor in the`
  line `manner specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) A creditor shall not be entitled to vote in respect of a debt for an unliquidated amount.`
  line
  line `(4) A creditor shall not be entitled to vote in a meeting of the creditors if he—`
  line
  line `(a) is not a creditor mentioned in the list of creditors under section 104; or`
  line
  line `(b) is an associate of the debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (889)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 134
  title `Rights of secured creditors in relation to repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=889&sectionno=110&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) Secured creditors shall be`
  line `entitled to participate and vote in the meetings of the creditors.`
  line
  line `(2) A secured creditor participating in the meetings of the creditors and voting in relation to the`
  line `repayment plan shall forfeit his right to enforce the security during the period of the repayment plan in`
  line `accordance with the terms of the repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a secured creditor does not forfeit his right to enforce security, he shall submit an affidavit`
  line `to the resolution professional at the meeting of the creditors stating—`
  line
  line `(a) that the right to vote exercised by the secured creditor is only in respect of the unsecured part`
  line `of the debt; and`
  line
  line `(b) the estimated value of the unsecured part of the debt.`
  line
  line `(4) In case a secured creditor participates in the voting on the repayment plan by submitting an`
  line `affidavit under sub-section (3), the secured and unsecured parts of the debt shall be treated as separate`
  line debts.
  line
  line `(5) The concurrence of the secured creditor shall be obtained if he does not participate in the voting`
  line `on repayment plan but provision of the repayment plan affects his right to enforce security.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, “period of the repayment plan” means the period from`
  line `the date of the order passed under section 114 till the date on which the notice is given by the resolution`
  line `professional under section 117 or report submitted by the resolution professional under section 118, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (890)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 135
  title `Approval of repayment plan by creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=890&sectionno=111&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `The repayment plan or any modification to the`
  line `repayment plan shall be approved by a majority of more than three-fourth in value of the creditors present`
  line `in person or by proxy and voting on the resolution in a meeting of the creditors.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (891)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 136
  title `Report of meeting of creditors on repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=891&sectionno=112&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall`
  line `prepare a report of the meeting of the creditors on repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(2) The report under sub-section (1) shall contain—`
  line
  line `(a) whether the repayment plan was approved or rejected and if approved, the list the`
  line `modifications, if any;`
  line
  line `(b) the resolutions which were proposed at the meeting and the decision on such resolutions;`
  line
  line `(c) list of the creditors who were present or represented at the meeting, and the voting records of`
  line `each creditor for all meetings of the creditors; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other information as the resolution professional thinks appropriate to make known to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (892)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 137
  title `Notice of decisions taken at meeting of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=892&sectionno=113&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `The resolution professional shall provide a`
  line `copy of the report of the meeting of creditors prepared under section 99 to—`
  line
  line `(a) the debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) the creditors, including those who were not present at the meeting; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Adjudicating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (893)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 138
  title `Order of Adjudicating Authority on repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=893&sectionno=114&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Authority shall`
  line `by an order approve or reject the repayment plan on the basis of the report of the meeting of the creditors`
  line `submitted by the resolution professional under section 112:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a meeting of creditors is not summoned, the Adjudicating Authority shall pass an`
  line `order on the basis of the report prepared by the resolution professional under section 106.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of the Adjudicating Authority approving the repayment plan may also provide for`
  line `directions for implementing the repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Adjudicating Authority is of the opinion that the repayment plan requires modification,`
  line `it may direct the resolution professional to re-convene a meeting of the creditors for reconsidering the`
  line `repayment plan.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (894)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 139
  title `Effect of order of Adjudicating Authority on repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=894&sectionno=115&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority has approved the repayment plan under section 114, such repayment plan shall—`
  line
  line `(a) take effect as if proposed by the debtor in the meeting; and`
  line
  line `(b) be binding on creditors mentioned in the repayment plan and the debtor.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Adjudicating Authority rejects the repayment plan under section 114, the debtor and`
  line `the creditors shall be entitled to file an application for bankruptcy under Chapter IV.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (2) shall be provided`
  line `to the Board, for the purpose of recording an entry in the register referred to in section 196.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (895)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 140
  title `Implementation and supervision of repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=895&sectionno=116&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional`
  line `appointed under section 97 or under section 98 shall supervise the implementation of the repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional may apply to the Adjudicating Authority for directions, if necessary,`
  line `in relation to any particular matter arising under the repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Authority may issue directions to the resolution professional on the basis of an`
  line `application under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (896)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 141
  title `Completion of repayment plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=896&sectionno=117&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) The resolution professional shall within fourteen days of`
  line `the completion of the repayment plan, forward to the persons who are bound by the repayment plan under`
  line `section 115 and the Adjudicating Authority, the following documents, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a notice that the repayment plan has been fully implemented; and`
  line
  line `(b) a copy of a report by the resolution professional summarising all receipts and payments made`
  line `in pursuance of the repayment plan and extent of the implementation of such plan as compared with`
  line `the repayment plan approved by the meeting of the creditors.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional may apply to the Adjudicating Authority to extend the time mentioned`
  line `in sub-section (1) for such further period not exceeding seven days.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (897)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 142
  title `Repayment plan coming to end prematurely.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=897&sectionno=118&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) A repayment plan shall be deemed to have`
  line `come to an end prematurely if it has not been fully implemented in respect of all persons bound by it`
  line `within the period as mentioned in the repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a repayment plan comes to an end prematurely under this section, the resolution`
  line `professional shall submit a report to the Adjudicating Authority which shall state—`
  line
  line `(a) the receipts and payments made in pursuance of the repayment plan;`
  line
  line `(b) the reasons for premature end of the repayment plan; and`
  line
  line `(c) the details of the creditors whose claims have not been fully satisfied.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Authority shall pass an order on the basis of the report submitted under`
  line `sub-section (2) by the resolution professional that the repayment plan has not been completely`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(4) The debtor or the creditor, whose claims under repayment plan have not been fully satisfied, shall`
  line `be entitled to apply for a bankruptcy order under Chapter IV.`
  line
  line `(5) The Adjudicating Authority shall forward to the persons bound by the repayment plan under`
  line `section 115, a copy of the—`
  line
  line `(a) report submitted by the resolution professional to the Adjudicating Authority under`
  line `sub-section (2); and`
  line
  line `(b) order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(6) The Adjudicating Authority shall forward a copy of the order passed under sub-section (4) to the`
  line `Board, for the purpose of recording entries in the register referred to in section 196.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (898)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 143
  title `Discharge order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=898&sectionno=119&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the basis of the repayment plan, the resolution professional shall`
  line `apply to the Adjudicating Authority for a discharge order in relation to the debts mentioned in the`
  line `repayment plan and the Adjudicating Authority may pass such discharge order.`
  line
  line `(2) The repayment plan may provide for—`
  line
  line `(a) early discharge; or`
  line
  line `(b) discharge on complete implementation of the repayment plan.`
  line
  line `(3) The discharge order shall be forwarded to the Board, for the purpose of recording entries in the`
  line `register referred to in section 196.`
  line
  line `(4) The discharge order under sub-section (3) shall not discharge any other person from any liability`
  line `in respect of his debt.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (899)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 144
  title `Standard of conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=899&sectionno=120&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `The resolution professional shall perform his functions and duties in`
  line `compliance with the code of conduct provided under section 208.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (900)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 145
  title `Application for bankruptcy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=900&sectionno=121&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for bankruptcy of a debtor may be made, by`
  line `a creditor individually or jointly with other creditors or by a debtor, to the Adjudicating Authority in the`
  line `following circumstances, namely;—`
  line
  line `(a) where an order has been passed by an Adjudicating Authority under sub-section 4 of`
  line `section 100; or`
  line
  line `(b) where an order has been passed by an Adjudicating Authority under sub-section 2 of`
  line `section 115; or`
  line
  line `(c) where an order has been passed by an Adjudicating Authority under sub-section 3 of`
  line `section 118.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for bankruptcy shall be filed within a period of three months of the date of the`
  line `order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under the sections referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the debtor is a firm, the application under sub-section (1) may be filed by any of its`
  line partners.
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (901)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 146
  title `Application by debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=901&sectionno=122&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) The application for bankruptcy by the debtor shall be accompanied`
  line by—
  line
  line `(a) the records of insolvency resolution process undertaken under Chapter III of Part III;`
  line
  line `(b) the statement of affairs of the debtor in such form and manner as may be prescribed, on the`
  line `date of the application for bankruptcy; and`
  line
  line `(c) a copy of the order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under Chapter III of Part III`
  line `permitting the debtor to apply for bankruptcy.`
  line
  line `(2) The debtor may propose an insolvency professional as the bankruptcy trustee in the application for`
  line bankruptcy.
  line
  line `(3) The application referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in such form and manner and accompanied`
  line `by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) An application for bankruptcy by the debtor shall not be withdrawn without the leave of the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (902)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 147
  title `Application by creditor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=902&sectionno=123&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) The application for bankruptcy by the creditor shall be`
  line `accompanied by—`
  line
  line `(a) the records of insolvency resolution process undertaken under Chapter III;`
  line
  line `(b) a copy of the order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under Chapter III permitting the`
  line `creditor to apply for bankruptcy;`
  line
  line `(c) details of the debts owed by the debtor to the creditor as on the date of the application for`
  line `bankruptcy; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other information as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) made in respect of a debt which is secured, shall be`
  line `accompanied with—`
  line
  line `(a) a statement by the creditor having the right to enforce the security that he shall, in the event`
  line `of a bankruptcy order being made, give up his security for the benefit of all the creditors of the`
  line `bankrupt; or`
  line
  line `(b) a statement by the creditor stating—`
  line
  line `(i) that the application for bankruptcy is only in respect of the unsecured part of the debt; and`
  line
  line `(ii) an estimated value of the unsecured part of the debt.`
  line
  line `(3) If a secured creditor makes an application for bankruptcy and submits a statement under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (2), the secured and unsecured parts of the debt shall be treated as separate debts.`
  line
  line `(4) The creditor may propose an insolvency professional as the bankruptcy trustee in the application`
  line `for bankruptcy.`
  line
  line `(5) An application for bankruptcy under sub-section (1), in case of a deceased debtor, may be filed`
  line `against his legal representatives.`
  line
  line `(6) The application for bankruptcy shall be in such form and manner and accompanied by such fee as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) An application for bankruptcy by the creditor shall not be withdrawn without the permission of`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (903)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 148
  title `Effect of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=903&sectionno=124&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application is filed under section 122 or section 123,—`
  line
  line `(a) an interim-moratorium shall commence on the date of the making of the application on all`
  line `actions against the properties of the debtor in respect of his debts and such moratorium shall cease to`
  line `have effect on the bankruptcy commencement date; and`
  line
  line `(b) during the interim-moratorium period—`
  line
  line `(i) any pending legal action or legal proceeding against any property of the debtor in respect`
  line `of any of his debts shall be deemed to have been stayed;`
  line
  line `(ii) the creditors of the debtor shall not be entitled to initiate any legal action or legal`
  line `proceedings against any property of the debtor in respect of any of his debts.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the application has been made in relation to a firm, the interim-moratorium under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall operate against all the partners of the firm as on the date of the making of the`
  line application.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section shall not apply to such transactions as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with any financial sector regulator.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (904)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 149
  title `Appointment of insolvency professional as bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=904&sectionno=125&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an insolvency`
  line `professional is proposed as the bankruptcy trustee in the application for bankruptcy under section 122 or`
  line `section 123, the Adjudicating Authority shall direct the Board within seven days of receiving the`
  line `application for bankruptcy to confirm that there are no disciplinary proceedings pending against such`
  line professional.
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall within ten days of the receipt of the direction under sub-section (1) in writing`
  line either--
  line
  line `(a) confirm the appointment of the proposed insolvency professional as the bankruptcy trustee for`
  line `the bankruptcy process; or`
  line
  line `(b) reject the appointment of the proposed insolvency professional as the bankruptcy trustee and`
  line `nominate another bankruptcy trustee for the bankruptcy process.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a bankruptcy trustee is not proposed by the debtor or creditor under section 122 or 123, the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority shall direct the Board within seven days of receiving the application to nominate a`
  line `bankruptcy trustee for the bankruptcy process.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall nominate a bankruptcy trustee within ten days of receiving the direction of the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The bankruptcy trustee confirmed or nominated under this section shall be appointed as the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee by the Adjudicating Authority in the bankruptcy order under section 126.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (905)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 150
  title `Bankruptcy order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=905&sectionno=126&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Authority shall pass a bankruptcy order within`
  line `fourteen days of receiving the confirmation or nomination of the bankruptcy trustee under section 125.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall provide the following documents to bankrupt, creditors and the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee within seven days of the passing of the bankruptcy order, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a copy of the application for bankruptcy; and`
  line
  line `(b) a copy of the bankruptcy order.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (906)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 151
  title `Validity of bankruptcy order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=906&sectionno=127&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `The bankruptcy order passed by the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `under section 126 shall continue to have effect till the debtor is discharged under section 138.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (907)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 152
  title `Effect of bankruptcy order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=907&sectionno=128&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the passing of the bankruptcy order under section 126,—`
  line
  line `(a) the estate of the bankrupt shall vest in the bankruptcy trustee as provided in section 154;`
  line
  line `(b) the estate of the bankrupt shall be divided among his creditors;`
  line
  line `(c) subject to provisions of sub-section (2), a creditor of the bankrupt indebted in respect of any`
  line `debt claimed as a bankruptcy debt shall not—`
  line
  line `(i) initiate any action against the property of the bankrupt in respect of such debt; or`
  line
  line `(ii) commence any suit or other legal proceedings except with the leave of the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority and on such terms as the Adjudicating Authority may impose.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 123, the bankruptcy order shall not affect the right of any`
  line `secured creditor to realise or otherwise deal with his security interest in the same manner as he would`
  line `have been entitled if the bankruptcy order had not been passed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no secured creditor shall be entitled to any interest in respect of his debt after the`
  line `bankruptcy commencement date if he does not take any action to realise his security within thirty days`
  line `from the said date.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a bankruptcy order under section 126 has been passed against a firm, the order shall`
  line `operate as if it were a bankruptcy order made against each of the individuals who, on the date of the order,`
  line `is a partner in the firm.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to such transactions as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with any financial sector regulator.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (908)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 153
  title `Statement of financial position.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=908&sectionno=129&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a bankruptcy order is passed on the application for`
  line `bankruptcy by a creditor under section 123, the bankrupt shall submit his statement of financial position`
  line `to the bankruptcy trustee within seven days from the bankruptcy commencement date.`
  line
  line `(2) The statement of financial position shall be submitted in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Where the bankrupt is a firm, its partners on the date of the order shall submit a joint statement of`
  line `financial position of the firm, and each partner of the firm shall submit a statement of his financial`
  line position.
  line
  line `(4) The bankruptcy trustee may require the bankrupt or any other person to submit in writing further`
  line `information explaining or modifying any matter contained in the statement of financial position.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (909)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 154
  title `Public notice inviting claims from creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=909&sectionno=130&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Authority shall—`
  line
  line `(a) send notices within ten days of the bankruptcy commencement date, to the creditors`
  line `mentioned in—`
  line
  line `(i) the statement of affairs submitted by the bankrupt under section 129; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the application for bankruptcy submitted by the bankrupt under section 122.`
  line
  line `(b) issue a public notice inviting claims from creditors.`
  line
  line `(2) The public notice under clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall include the last date up to which the`
  line `claims shall be submitted and such other matters and details as may be prescribed and shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) published in leading newspapers, one in English and another in vernacular having sufficient`
  line `circulation where the bankrupt resides;`
  line
  line `(b) affixed on the premises of the Adjudicating Authority; and`
  line
  line `(c) placed on the website of the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice to the creditors referred to under clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall include such`
  line `matters and details as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (910)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 155
  title `Registration of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=910&sectionno=131&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) The creditors shall register claims with the bankruptcy trustee`
  line `within seven days of the publication of the public notice, by sending details of the claims to the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The creditor, in addition to the details of his claims, shall provide such other information and in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (911)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 156
  title `Preparation of list of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=911&sectionno=132&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `The bankruptcy trustee shall, within fourteen days from the`
  line `bankruptcy commencement date, prepare a list of creditors of the bankrupt on the basis of—`
  line
  line `(a) the information disclosed by the bankrupt in the application for bankruptcy filed by the`
  line `bankrupt under section 118 and the statement of affairs filed under section 125; and`
  line
  line `(b) claims received by the bankruptcy trustee under sub-section (2) of section 130.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (912)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 157
  title `Summoning of meeting of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=912&sectionno=133&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall, within twenty-one`
  line `days from the bankruptcy commencement date, issue a notice for calling a meeting of the creditors, to`
  line `every creditor of the bankrupt as mentioned in the list prepared under section 132.`
  line
  line `(2) The notices issued under sub-section (1) shall—`
  line
  line `(a) state the date of the meeting of the creditors, which shall not be later than twenty-one days`
  line `from the bankruptcy commencement date;`
  line
  line `(b) be accompanied with forms of proxy voting;`
  line
  line `(c) specify the form and manner in which the proxy voting may take place.`
  line
  line `(3) The proxy voting, including electronic proxy voting shall take place in such manner and form as`
  line `may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (913)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 158
  title `Conduct of meeting of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=913&sectionno=134&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall be the convener of the`
  line `meeting of the creditors summoned under section 133.`
  line
  line `(2) The bankruptcy trustee shall decide the quorum for the meeting of the creditors, and conduct the`
  line `meeting only if the quorum is present.`
  line
  line `(3) The following business shall be conducted in the meeting of the creditors in which regard a`
  line `resolution may be passed, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the establishment of a committee of creditors;`
  line
  line `(b) any other business that the bankruptcy trustee thinks fit to be transacted.`
  line
  line `(4) The bankruptcy trustee shall cause the minutes of the meeting of the creditors to be recorded,`
  line `signed and retained as a part of the records of the bankruptcy process.`
  line
  line `(5) The bankruptcy trustee shall not adjourn the meeting of the creditors for any purpose for more`
  line `than seven days at a time.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (914)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 159
  title `Voting rights of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=914&sectionno=135&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every creditor mentioned in the list under section 132 or his`
  line `proxy shall be entitled to vote in respect of the resolutions in the meeting of the creditors in accordance`
  line `with the voting share assigned to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The resolution professional shall determine the voting share to be assigned to each creditor in the`
  line `manner specified by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) A creditor shall not be entitled to vote in respect of a debt for an unliquidated amount.`
  line
  line `(4) The following creditors shall not be entitled to vote under this section, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) creditors who are not mentioned in the list of creditors under section 132 and those who have`
  line `not been given a notice by the bankruptcy trustee;`
  line
  line `(b) creditors who are associates of the bankrupt.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (915)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 160
  title `Administration and distribution of estate of bankruptcy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=915&sectionno=136&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `The bankruptcy trustee shall`
  line `conduct the administration and distribution of the estate of the bankrupt in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of Chapter V.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (916)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 161
  title `Completion of administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=916&sectionno=137&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall convene a meeting of the`
  line `committee of creditors on completion of the administration and distribution of the estate of the bankrupt`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of Chapter V.`
  line
  line `(2) The bankruptcy trustee shall provide the committee of creditors with a report of the administration`
  line `of the estate of the bankrupt in the meeting of the said committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The committee of creditors shall approve the report submitted by the bankruptcy trustee under`
  line `sub-section (2) within seven days of the receipt of the report and determine whether the bankruptcy`
  line `trustee should be released under section 148.`
  line
  line `(4) The bankruptcy trustee shall retain sufficient sums from the estate of the bankrupt to meet the`
  line `expenses of convening and conducting the meeting required under this section during the administration`
  line `of the estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (917)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 162
  title `Discharge order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=917&sectionno=138&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall apply to the Adjudicating Authority for a`
  line `discharge order—`
  line
  line `(a) on the expiry of one year from the bankruptcy commencement date; or`
  line
  line `(b) within seven days of the approval of the committee of creditors of the completion of`
  line `administration of the estates of the bankrupt under section 137, where such approval is obtained prior`
  line `to the period mentioned in clause (a).`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall pass a discharge order on an application by the bankruptcy`
  line `trustee under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the discharge order shall be provided to the Board for the purpose of recording an entry`
  line `in the register referred to in section 196.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (918)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 163
  title `Effect of discharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=918&sectionno=139&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `The discharge order under sub-section (2) of section 138 shall release the`
  line `bankrupt from all the bankruptcy debt:`
  line
  line `Provided that discharge shall not—`
  line
  line `(a) affect the functions of the bankruptcy trustee; or`
  line
  line `(b) affect the operation of the provisions of Chapters IV and V of Part III; or`
  line
  line `(c) release the bankrupt from any debt incurred by means of fraud or breach of trust to which he`
  line `was a party; or`
  line
  line `(d) discharge the bankrupt from any excluded debt.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (919)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 164
  title `Disqualification of bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=919&sectionno=140&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankrupt shall, from the bankruptcy commencement`
  line `date, be subject to the disqualifications mentioned in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to any disqualification under any other law for the time being in force, a bankrupt shall`
  line `be disqualified from—`
  line
  line `(a) being appointed or acting as a trustee or representative in respect of any trust, estate or`
  line settlement;
  line
  line `(b) being appointed or acting as a public servant;`
  line
  line `(c) being elected to any public office where the appointment to such office is by election; and`
  line
  line `(d) being elected or sitting or voting as a member of any local authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Any disqualification to which a bankrupt may be subject under this section shall cease to have`
  line `effect, if—`
  line
  line `(a) the bankruptcy order against him is modified or recalled under section 142; or`
  line
  line `(b) he is discharged under section 138.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the term “public servant” shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (920)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 165
  title `Restrictions on bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=920&sectionno=141&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) A bankrupt, from the bankruptcy commencement date, shall`
  line
  line `(a) not act as a director of any company, or directly or indirectly take part in or be concerned in`
  line `the promotion, formation or management of a company;`
  line
  line `(b) without the previous sanction of the bankruptcy trustee, be prohibited from creating any`
  line `charge on his estate or taking any further debt;`
  line
  line `(c) be required to inform his business partners that he is undergoing a bankruptcy process;`
  line
  line `(d) prior to entering into any financial or commercial transaction of such value as may be`
  line `prescribed, either individually or jointly, inform all the parties involved in such transaction that he is`
  line `undergoing a bankruptcy process;`
  line
  line `(e) without the previous sanction of the Adjudicating Authority, be incompetent to maintain any`
  line `legal action or proceedings in relation to the bankruptcy debts; and`
  line
  line `(f) not be permitted to travel overseas without the permission of the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Any restriction to which a bankrupt may be subject under this section shall cease to have effect,`
  line if--
  line
  line `(a) the bankruptcy order against him is modified or recalled under section 142; or`
  line
  line `(b) he is discharged under section 138.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (921)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 166
  title `Modification or recall of bankruptcy order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=921&sectionno=142&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Authority may, on an`
  line `application or suo motu, modify or recall a bankruptcy order, whether or not the bankrupt is discharged, if`
  line `it appears to the Adjudicating Authority that--`
  line
  line `(a) there exists an error apparent on the face of such order; or`
  line
  line `(b) both the bankruptcy debts and the expenses of the bankruptcy have, after the making of the`
  line `bankruptcy order, either been paid for or secured to the satisfaction of the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Adjudicating Authority modifies or recalls the bankruptcy order under this section, any`
  line `sale or other disposition of property, payment made or other things duly done by the bankruptcy trustee`
  line `shall be valid except that the property of the bankrupt shall vest in such person as the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority may appoint or, in default of any such appointment, revert to the bankrupt on such terms as the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the order passed by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (1) shall be provided`
  line `to the Board, for the purpose of recording an entry in the register referred to in section 191.`
  line
  line `(4) The modification or recall of the order by the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be binding on all creditors so far as it relates to any debts due to them which form a part of the`
  line bankruptcy.
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (922)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 167
  title `Standard of conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=922&sectionno=143&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `The bankruptcy trustee shall perform his functions and duties in`
  line `compliance with the code of conduct provided under section 208.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (923)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 168
  title `Fees of bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=923&sectionno=144&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) A bankruptcy trustee appointed for conducting the bankruptcy`
  line `process shall charge such fees as may be specified in proportion to the value of the estate of the bankrupt.`
  line
  line `(2) The fees for the conduct of the bankruptcy process shall be paid to the bankruptcy trustee from the`
  line `distribution of the estate of the bankrupt in the manner provided in section 178.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (924)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 169
  title `Replacement of bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=924&sectionno=145&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where Committee of creditors is of the opinion that at`
  line `any time during the bankruptcy process, a bankruptcy trustee appointed under section 125 is required to`
  line `be replaced, it may replace him with another bankruptcy trustee in the manner provided under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(2) The Committee of creditors may, at a meeting, by a vote of seventy-five per cent. of voting share,`
  line `propose to replace the bankruptcy trustee appointed under section 125 with another bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee of creditors may apply to the Adjudicating Authority for the replacement of the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Adjudicating Authority shall within seven days of the receipt of the application under subsection`
  line
  line `(3) direct the Board to recommend for replacement of bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall, within ten days of the direction of the Adjudicating Authority under sub-section`
  line `(4), recommend a bankruptcy trustee for replacement against whom no disciplinary proceedings are`
  line pending.
  line
  line `(6) The Adjudicating Authority shall, by an order, appoint the bankruptcy trustee as recommended by`
  line `the Board under sub-section (5) within fourteen days of receiving such recommendation.`
  line
  line `(7) The earlier bankruptcy trustee shall deliver possession of the estate of the bankrupt to the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee appointed under sub-section (6), on the date of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(8) The Adjudicating Authority may give directions to the earlier bankruptcy trustee--`
  line
  line `(a) to share all information with the new bankruptcy trustee in respect of the bankruptcy process;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) to co-operate with the new bankruptcy trustee in such matters as may be required.`
  line
  line `(9) The earlier bankruptcy trustee replaced under this section shall be released in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 148.`
  line
  line `(10) The bankruptcy trustee appointed under this section shall give a notice of his appointment to the`
  line `bankrupt within seven days of his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (925)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 170
  title `Resignation by bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=925&sectionno=146&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `(1) A bankruptcy trustee may resign if—`
  line
  line `(a) he intends to cease practising as an insolvency professional; or`
  line
  line `(b) there is conflict of interest or change of personal circumstances which preclude the further`
  line `discharge of his duties as a bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority shall, within seven days of the acceptance of the resignation of the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee, direct the Board for his replacement.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall, within ten days of the direction of the Adjudicating Authority under`
  line `sub-section (2) recommend another bankruptcy trustee as a replacement.`
  line
  line `(4) The Adjudicating Authority shall appoint the bankruptcy trustee recommended by the Board`
  line `under sub-section (3) within fourteen days of receiving the recommendation.`
  line
  line `(5) The replaced bankruptcy trustee shall deliver possession of the estate of the bankrupt to the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee appointed under sub-section (4), on the date of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(6) The Adjudicating Authority may give directions to the bankruptcy trustee who has resigned—`
  line
  line `(a) to share all information with the new bankruptcy trustee in respect of the bankruptcy process;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) to co-operate with the new bankruptcy trustee in such matters as may be required.`
  line
  line `(7) The bankruptcy trustee appointed under this section shall give a notice of his appointment to the`
  line `committee of creditors and the bankrupt within seven days of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(8) The bankruptcy trustee replaced under this section shall be released in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 148.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (926)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 171
  title `Vacancy in office of bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=926&sectionno=147&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a vacancy occurs in the office of the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee for any reason other than his replacement or resignation, the vacancy shall be filled in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of the occurrence of vacancy referred to in sub-section (1), the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority shall direct the Board for replacement of a bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall, within ten days of the direction of the Adjudicating Authority under`
  line `sub-section (2), recommend a bankruptcy trustee as a replacement.`
  line
  line `(4) The Adjudicating Authority shall appoint the bankruptcy trustee recommended by the Board`
  line `under sub-section (3) within fourteen days of receiving the recommendation.`
  line
  line `(5) The earlier bankruptcy trustee shall deliver possession of the estate of the bankrupt to the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee appointed under sub-section (4), on the date of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(6) The Adjudicating Authority may give directions to the bankruptcy trustee who has vacated the`
  line office--
  line
  line `(a) to share all information with the new bankruptcy trustee in respect of the bankruptcy;`
  line
  line `(b) to co-operate with the new bankruptcy trustee in such matters as may be required.`
  line
  line `(7) The bankruptcy trustee appointed under sub-section (4) shall give a notice of his appointment to`
  line `the committee of creditors and the bankrupt within seven days of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(8) The earlier bankruptcy trustee replaced under this section shall be released in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 148:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply if the vacancy has occurred due to temporary illness or`
  line `temporary leave of the bankruptcy trustee.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (927)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 172
  title `Release of bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=927&sectionno=148&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) A bankruptcy trustee shall be released from his office with`
  line `effect from the date on which the Adjudicating Authority passes an order appointing a new bankruptcy`
  line `trustee in the event of replacement, resignation or occurrence of vacancy under sections 145, 146 or`
  line `section 147, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the release under sub-section (1), the bankruptcy trustee who has been so`
  line `released, shall share all information with the new bankruptcy trustee in respect of the bankruptcy process`
  line `and co-operate with the new bankruptcy trustee in such matters as may be required.`
  line
  line `(3) A bankruptcy trustee who has completed the administration of the bankruptcy process shall be`
  line `released of his duties with effect from the date on which the committee of creditors approves the report of`
  line `the bankruptcy trustee under section 137.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (928)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 173
  title `Functions of bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=928&sectionno=149&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `The bankruptcy trustee shall perform the following`
  line `functions in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter—`
  line
  line `(a) investigate the affairs of the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(b) realise the estate of the bankrupt; and`
  line
  line `(c) distribute the estate of the bankrupt`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (929)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 174
  title `Duties of bankrupt towards bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=929&sectionno=150&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankrupt shall assist the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee in carrying out his functions under this Chapter by—`
  line
  line `(a) giving to the bankruptcy trustee the information of his affairs;`
  line
  line `(b) attending on the bankruptcy trustee at such times as may be required;`
  line
  line `(c) giving notice to the bankruptcy trustee of any of the following events which have occurred`
  line `after the bankruptcy commencement date,—`
  line
  line `(i) acquisition of any property by the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(ii) devolution of any property upon the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(iii) increase in the income of the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(d) doing all other things as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The bankrupt shall give notice of the increase in income or acquisition or devolution of property`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (1) within seven days of such increase, acquisition or devolution.`
  line
  line `(3) The bankrupt shall continue to discharge the duties under sub-section (1) other than the duties`
  line `under clause (c) even after the discharge under section 138.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (930)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 175
  title `Rights of bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=930&sectionno=151&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of performing his functions under this`
  line `Chapter, the bankruptcy trustee may, by his official name—`
  line
  line `(a) hold property of every description;`
  line
  line `(b) make contracts;`
  line
  line `(c) sue and be sued;`
  line
  line `(d) enter into engagements in respect of the estate of the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(e) employ persons to assist him;`
  line
  line `(f) execute any power of attorney, deed or other instrument; and`
  line
  line `(g) do any other act which is necessary or expedient for the purposes of or in connection with the`
  line `exercise of his rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (931)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 176
  title `General powers of bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=931&sectionno=152&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `The bankruptcy trustee may while discharging his`
  line `functions under this Chapter,—`
  line
  line `(a) sell any part of the estate of the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(b) give receipts for any money received by him;`
  line
  line `(c) prove, rank, claim and draw a dividend in respect of such debts due to the bankrupt as are`
  line `comprised in his estate;`
  line
  line `(d) where any property comprised in the estate of the bankrupt is held by any person by way of`
  line `pledge or hypothecation, exercise the right of redemption in respect of any such property subject to`
  line `the relevant contract by giving notice to the said person;`
  line
  line `(e) where any part of the estate of the bankrupt consists of securities in a company or any other`
  line `property which is transferable in the books of a person, exercise the right to transfer the property to`
  line `the same extent as the bankrupt might have exercised it if he had not become bankrupt; and`
  line
  line `(f) deal with any property comprised in the estate of the bankrupt to which the bankrupt is`
  line `beneficially entitled in the same manner as he might have dealt with it.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (932)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 177
  title `Approval of creditors for certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=932&sectionno=153&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `The bankruptcy trustee for the purposes of this`
  line `Chapter may after procuring the approval of the committee of creditors,—`
  line
  line `(a) carry on any business of the bankrupt as far as may be necessary for winding it up`
  line beneficially;
  line
  line `(b) bring, institute or defend any legal action or proceedings relating to the property comprised in`
  line `the estate of the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(c) accept as consideration for the sale of any property a sum of money due at a future time`
  line `subject to certain stipulations such as security;`
  line
  line `(d) mortgage or pledge any property for the purpose of raising money for the payment of the`
  line `debts of the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(e) where any right, option or other power forms part of the estate of the bankrupt, make`
  line `payments or incur liabilities with a view to obtaining, for the benefit of the creditors, any property`
  line `which is the subject of such right, option or power;`
  line
  line `(f) refer to arbitration or compromise on such terms as may be agreed, any debts subsisting or`
  line `supposed to subsist between the bankrupt and any person who may have incurred any liability to the`
  line bankrupt;
  line
  line `(g) make compromise or other arrangement as may be considered expedient, with the creditors;`
  line
  line `(h) make compromise or other arrangement as he may deem expedient with respect to any claim`
  line `arising out of or incidental to the bankrupt's estate;`
  line
  line `(i) appoint the bankrupt to—`
  line
  line `(A) supervise the management of the estate of the bankrupt or any part of it;`
  line
  line `(B) carry on his business for the benefit of his creditors;`
  line
  line `(C) assist the bankruptcy trustee in administering the estate of the bankrupt.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (933)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 178
  title `Vesting of estate of bankrupt in bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=933&sectionno=154&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) The estate of the bankrupt shall`
  line `vest in the bankruptcy trustee immediately from the date of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(2) The vesting under sub-section (1) shall take effect without any conveyance, assignment or`
  line transfer.
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (934)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 179
  title `Estate of bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=934&sectionno=155&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) The estate of the bankrupt shall include,—`
  line
  line `(a) all property belonging to or vested in the bankrupt at the bankruptcy commencement date;`
  line
  line `(b) the capacity to exercise and to initiate proceedings for exercising all such powers in or over or`
  line `in respect of property as might have been exercised by the bankrupt for his own benefit at the`
  line `bankruptcy commencement date or before the date of the discharge order passed under section 138;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) all property which by virtue of any of the provisions of this Chapter is comprised in the estate.`
  line
  line `(2) The estate of the bankrupt shall not include—`
  line
  line `(a) excluded assets;`
  line
  line `(b) property held by the bankrupt on trust for any other person;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums due to any workman or employee from the provident fund, the pension fund and the`
  line `gratuity fund; and`
  line
  line `(d) such assets as may be notified by the Central Government in consultation with any financial`
  line `sector regulator.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (935)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 180
  title `Delivery of property and documents to bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=935&sectionno=156&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `The bankrupt, his banker or`
  line `agent or any other person having possession of any property, books, papers or other records which`
  line `bankruptcy trustee is required to take possession for the purposes of the bankruptcy process shall deliver`
  line `the said property and documents to the bankruptcy trustee.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (936)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 181
  title `Acquisition of control by bankruptcy trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=936&sectionno=157&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall take`
  line `possession and control of all property, books, papers and other records relating to the estate of the`
  line `bankrupt or affairs of the bankrupt which belong to him or are in his possession or under his control.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any part of the estate of the bankrupt consists of things in actionable claims, they shall be`
  line `deemed to have been assigned to the bankruptcy trustee without any notice of the assignment.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (937)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 182
  title `Restrictions on disposition of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=937&sectionno=158&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any disposition of property made by the debtor, during the period between the date of filing of the application for bankruptcy and the bankruptcy`
  line `commencement date shall be void.`
  line
  line `(2) Any disposition of property made under sub-section (1) shall not give rise to any right against any`
  line `person, in respect of such property, even if he has received such property before the bankruptcy`
  line `commencement date in--`
  line
  line `(a) good faith;`
  line
  line `(b) for value; and`
  line
  line `(c) without notice of the filing of the application for bankruptcy.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, the term "property" means all the property of the debtor, whether or not it is comprised in the estate of the bankrupt, but shall not include property held by the debtor in`
  line `trust for any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (938)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 183
  title `After-acquired property of bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=938&sectionno=159&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall be entitled to claim`
  line `for the estate of the bankrupt, any after-acquired property by giving a notice to the bankrupt.`
  line
  line `(2) A notice under sub-section (1) shall not be served in respect of—`
  line
  line `(a) excluded assets; or`
  line
  line `(b) any property which is acquired by or devolves upon the bankrupt after a discharge order is`
  line `passed under section 138.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice under sub-section (2) shall be given within fifteen days from the day on which the`
  line `acquisition or devolution of the after-acquired property comes to the knowledge of the bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-section (3)—`
  line
  line `(a) anything which comes to the knowledge of the bankruptcy trustee shall be deemed to have`
  line `come to the knowledge of the successor of the bankruptcy trustee at the same time; and`
  line
  line `(b) anything which comes to the knowledge of a person before he is appointed as a bankruptcy`
  line `trustee shall be deemed to have come to his knowledge on the date of his appointment as bankruptcy`
  line trustee.
  line
  line `(5) The bankruptcy trustee shall not be entitled, by virtue of this section, to claim from any person`
  line `who has acquired any right over after-acquired property, in good faith, for value and without notice of the`
  line bankruptcy.
  line
  line `(6) A notice may be served after the expiry of the period under sub-section (3) only with the approval`
  line `of the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the term “after-acquired property” means any`
  line `property which has been acquired by or has devolved upon the bankrupt after the bankruptcy`
  line `commencement date.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (939)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 184
  title `Onerous property of bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=939&sectionno=160&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee may, by giving notice to the`
  line `bankrupt or any person interested in the onerous property, disclaim any onerous property which forms a`
  line `part of the estate of the bankrupt.`
  line
  line `(2) The bankruptcy trustee may give the notice under sub-section (1) notwithstanding that he has`
  line `taken possession of the onerous property, endeavoured to sell it or has exercised rights of ownership in`
  line `relation to it.`
  line
  line `(3) A notice of disclaimer under sub-section (1) shall—`
  line
  line `(a) determine, as from the date of such notice, the rights, interests and liabilities of the bankrupt`
  line `in respect of the onerous property disclaimed;`
  line
  line `(b) discharge the bankruptcy trustee from all personal liability in respect of the onerous property`
  line `as from the date of appointment of the bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(4) A notice of disclaimer under sub-section (1) shall not be given in respect of the property which`
  line `has been claimed for the estate of the bankrupt under section 155 without the permission of the committee`
  line `of creditors.`
  line
  line `(5) A notice of disclaimer under sub-section (1) shall not affect the rights or liabilities of any other`
  line `person, and any person who sustains a loss or damage in consequence of the operation of a disclaimer`
  line `under this section shall be deemed to be a creditor of the bankrupt to the extent of the loss or damage.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the term “onerous property” means—`
  line
  line `(i) any unprofitable contract; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any other property comprised in the estate of the bankrupt which is unsaleable or not readily`
  line `saleable, or is such that it may give rise to a claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (940)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 185
  title `Notice to disclaim onerous property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=940&sectionno=161&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) No notice of disclaimer under section 160 shall be`
  line `necessary if—`
  line
  line `(a) a person interested in the onerous property has applied in writing to the bankruptcy trustee or`
  line `his predecessor requiring him to decide whether the onerous property should be disclaimed or not;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) a decision under clause (a) has not been taken by the bankruptcy trustee within seven days of`
  line `receipt of the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Any onerous property which cannot be disclaimed under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be`
  line `part of the estate of the bankrupt.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, an onerous property is said to be disclaimed where`
  line `notice in relation to that property has been given by the bankruptcy trustee under section 160.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (941)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 186
  title `Disclaimer of leaseholds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=941&sectionno=162&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall not be entitled to disclaim any`
  line `leasehold interest, unless a notice of disclaimer has been served on every interested person and—`
  line
  line `(a) no application objecting to the disclaimer by the interested person, has been filed with respect`
  line `to the leasehold interest, within fourteen days of the date on which notice was served; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the application objecting to the disclaimer has been filed by the interested person, the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority has directed under section 163 that the disclaimer shall take effect.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Adjudicating Authority gives a direction under clause (b) of sub-section (1), it may also`
  line `make order with respect to fixtures, improvements by tenant and other matters arising out of the lease as it`
  line `may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (942)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 187
  title `Challenge against disclaimed property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=942&sectionno=163&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application challenging the disclaimer may`
  line `be made by the following persons under this section to the Adjudicating Authority—`
  line
  line `(a) any person who claims an interest in the disclaimed property; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who is under any liability in respect of the disclaimed property; or`
  line
  line `(c) where the disclaimed property is a dwelling house, any person who on the date of application`
  line `for bankruptcy was in occupation of or entitled to occupy that dwelling house.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority may on an application under sub-section (1) make an order`
  line `for the vesting of the disclaimed property in, or for its delivery to any of the persons mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1)`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Authority shall not make an order in favour of a person who has made an`
  line `application under clause (b) of sub-section (1) except where it appears to the Adjudicating Authority that`
  line `it would be just to do so for the purpose of compensating the person.`
  line
  line `(4) The effect of an order under this section shall be taken into account while assessing loss or`
  line `damage sustained by any person in consequence of the disclaimer under sub-section (5) of section 160.`
  line
  line `(5) An order under sub-section (2) vesting property in any person need not be completed by any`
  line `consequence, assignment or transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (943)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 188
  title `Undervalued transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=943&sectionno=164&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee may apply to the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority for an order under this section in respect of an undervalued transaction between a bankrupt and`
  line `any person.`
  line
  line `(2) The undervalued transaction referred to in sub-section (1) should have—`
  line
  line `(a) been entered into during the period of two years ending on the filing of the application for`
  line `bankruptcy; and`
  line
  line `(b) caused bankruptcy process to be triggered.`
  line
  line `(3) A transaction between a bankrupt and his associate entered into during the period of two years`
  line `preceding the date of making of the application for bankruptcy shall be deemed to be an undervalued`
  line `transaction under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) On the application of the bankruptcy trustee under sub-section (1), the Adjudicating Authority`
  line may—
  line
  line `(a) pass an order declaring an undervalued transaction void;`
  line
  line `(b) pass an order requiring any property transferred as a part of an undervalued transaction to be`
  line `vested with the bankruptcy trustee as a part of the estate of the bankrupt; and`
  line
  line `(c) pass any other order it thinks fit for restoring the position to what it would have been if the`
  line `bankrupt had not entered into the undervalued transaction.`
  line
  line `(5) The order under clause (a) of sub-section (4) shall not be passed if it is proved by the bankrupt`
  line `that the transaction was undertaken in the ordinary course of business of the bankrupt:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not be applicable to undervalued transaction`
  line `entered into between a bankrupt and his associate under sub-section (3) of this section.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of this section, a bankrupt enters into an undervalued transaction with any person`
  line if—
  line
  line `(a) he makes a gift to that person;`
  line
  line `(b) no consideration has been received by that person from the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(c) it is in consideration of marriage; or`
  line
  line `(d) it is for a consideration, the value of which in money or money's worth is significantly less`
  line `than the value in money or money's worth of the consideration provided by the bankrupt.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (944)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 189
  title `Preference transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=944&sectionno=165&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee may apply to the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `for an order under this section if a bankrupt has given a preference to any person.`
  line
  line `(2) The transaction giving preference to an associate of the bankrupt under sub-section (1) should`
  line `have been entered into by the bankrupt with the associate during the period of two years ending on the`
  line `date of the application for bankruptcy.`
  line
  line `(3) Any transaction giving preference not covered under sub-section (2) should have been entered`
  line `into by the bankrupt during the period of six months ending on the date of the application for bankruptcy.`
  line
  line `(4) The transaction giving preference under sub-section (2) or under sub-section (3) should have`
  line `caused the bankruptcy process to be triggered.`
  line
  line `(5) On the application of the bankruptcy trustee under sub-section (1), the Adjudicating Authority`
  line may—
  line
  line `(a) pass an order declaring a transaction giving preference void;`
  line
  line `(b) pass an order requiring any property transferred in respect of a transaction giving preference`
  line `to be vested with the bankruptcy trustee as a part of the estate of the bankrupt; and`
  line
  line `(c) pass any other order it thinks fit for restoring the position to what it would have been if the`
  line `bankrupt had not entered into the transaction giving preference.`
  line
  line `(6) The Adjudicating Authority shall not pass an order under sub-section (5) unless the bankrupt was`
  line `influenced in his decision of giving preference to a person by a desire to produce in relation to that person`
  line `an effect under clause (b) of sub-section (8).`
  line
  line `(7) For the purpose of sub-section (6), if the person is an associate of the bankrupt, (otherwise than by`
  line `reason only of being his employee), at the time when the preference was given, it shall be presumed that`
  line `the bankrupt was influenced in his decision under that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(8) For the purposes of this section, a bankrupt shall be deemed to have entered into a transaction`
  line `giving preference to any person if—`
  line
  line `(a) the person is the creditor or surety or guarantor for any debt of the bankrupt; and`
  line
  line `(b) the bankrupt does anything or suffers anything to be done which has the effect of putting that`
  line `person into a position which, in the event of the debtor becoming a bankrupt, will be better than the`
  line `position he would have been in, if that thing had not been done.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (945)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 190
  title `Effect of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=945&sectionno=166&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provision of sub-section (2), an order passed by the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority under section 164 or section 165 shall not,—`
  line
  line `(a) give rise to a right against a person interested in the property which was acquired in an`
  line `undervalued transaction or a transaction giving preference, whether or not he is the person with whom`
  line `the bankrupt entered into such transaction; and`
  line
  line `(b) require any person to pay a sum to the bankruptcy trustee in respect of the benefit received`
  line `from the undervalued transaction or a transaction giving preference, whether or not he is the person`
  line `with whom the bankrupt entered into such transaction.`
  line
  line `(2) The provision of sub-section (1) shall apply only if the interest was acquired or the benefit was`
  line received—
  line
  line `(a) in good faith;`
  line
  line `(b) for value;`
  line
  line `(c) without notice that the bankrupt entered into the transaction at an undervalue or for giving`
  line preference;
  line
  line `(d) without notice that the bankrupt has filed an application for bankruptcy or a bankruptcy order`
  line `has been passed; and`
  line
  line `(e) by any person who at the time of acquiring the interest or receiving the benefit was not an`
  line `associate of the bankrupt.`
  line
  line `(3) Any sum required to be paid to the bankruptcy trustee under sub-section (1) shall be included in`
  line `the estate of the bankrupt.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (946)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 191
  title `Extortionate credit transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=946&sectionno=167&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to sub-section (6), on an application by the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee, the Adjudicating Authority may make an order under this section in respect of`
  line `extortionate credit transactions to which the bankrupt is or has been a party.`
  line
  line `(2) The transactions under sub-section (1) should have been entered into by the bankrupt during the`
  line `period of two years ending on the bankruptcy commencement date.`
  line
  line `(3) An order of the Adjudicating Authority may—`
  line
  line `(a) set aside the whole or part of any debt created by the transaction;`
  line
  line `(b) vary the terms of the transaction or vary the terms on which any security for the purposes of`
  line `the transaction is held;`
  line
  line `(c) require any person who has been paid by the bankrupt under any transaction, to pay a sum to`
  line `the bankruptcy trustee;`
  line
  line `(d) require any person to surrender to the bankruptcy trustee any property of the bankrupt held as`
  line `security for the purposes of the transaction.`
  line
  line `(4) Any sum paid or any property surrendered to the bankruptcy trustee shall be included in the estate`
  line `of the bankrupt.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section, an extortionate credit transaction is a transaction for or involving`
  line `the provision of credit to the bankrupt by any person—`
  line
  line `(a) on terms requiring the bankrupt to make exorbitant payments in respect of the credit provided;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) which is unconscionable under the principles of law relating to contracts.`
  line
  line `(6) Any debt extended by a person regulated for the provision of financial services in compliance`
  line `with the law in force in relation to such debt, shall not be considered as an extortionate credit transaction`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (947)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 192
  title `Obligations under contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=947&sectionno=168&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) This section shall apply where a contract has been entered`
  line `into by the bankrupt with a person before the bankruptcy commencement date.`
  line
  line `(2) Any party to a contract, other than the bankrupt under sub-section (1), may apply to the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority for—`
  line
  line `(a) an order discharging the obligations of the applicant or the bankrupt under the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) payment of damages by the party or the bankrupt, for non-performance of the contract or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `(3) Any damages payable by the bankrupt by virtue of an order under clause (b) of sub-section (2)`
  line `shall be provable as bankruptcy debt.`
  line
  line `(4) When a bankrupt is a party to the contract under this section jointly with another person, that`
  line `person may sue or be sued in respect of the contract without joinder of the bankrupt.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (948)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 193
  title `Continuance of proceedings on death of bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=948&sectionno=169&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `If a bankrupt dies, the bankruptcy`
  line `proceedings shall, continue as if he were alive.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (949)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 194
  title `Administration of estate of deceased bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=949&sectionno=170&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `(1) All the provisions of Chapter V relating`
  line `to the administration and distribution of the estate of the bankrupt shall, so far as the same are applicable,`
  line `apply to the administration of the estate of a deceased bankrupt.`
  line
  line `(2) While administering the estate of a deceased bankrupt, the bankruptcy trustee shall have regard to`
  line `the claims by the legal representatives of the deceased bankrupt to payment of the proper funeral and`
  line `testamentary expenses incurred by them.`
  line
  line `(3) The claims under sub-section (2) shall rank equally to the secured creditors in the priority`
  line `provided under section 178.`
  line
  line `(4) If, on the administration of the estate of a deceased bankrupt, any surplus remains in the hands of`
  line `the bankruptcy trustee after payment in full of all the debts due from the deceased bankrupt, together with`
  line `the costs of the administration and interest as provided under section 178, such surplus shall be paid to the`
  line `legal representatives of the estate of the deceased bankrupt or dealt with in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (950)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 195
  title `Proof of debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=950&sectionno=171&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee shall give notice to each of the creditors to submit`
  line `proof of debt within fourteen days of preparing the list of creditors under section 132.`
  line
  line `(2) The proof of debt shall—`
  line
  line `(a) require the creditor to give full particulars of debt, including the date on which the debt was`
  line `contracted and the value at which that person assesses it;`
  line
  line `(b) require the creditor to give full particulars of the security, including the date on which the`
  line `security was given and the value at which that person assesses it;`
  line
  line `(c) be in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) In case the creditor is a decree holder against the bankrupt, a copy of the decree shall be a valid`
  line `proof of debt.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a debt bears interest, that interest shall be provable as part of the debt except in so far as it`
  line `is owed in respect of any period after the bankruptcy commencement date.`
  line
  line `(5) The bankruptcy trustee shall estimate the value of any bankruptcy debt which does not have a`
  line `specific value.`
  line
  line `(6) The value assigned by the bankruptcy trustee under sub-section (5) shall be the amount provable`
  line `by the concerned creditor.`
  line
  line `(7) A creditor may prove for a debt where payment would have become due at a date later than the`
  line `bankruptcy commencement date as if it were owed presently and may receive dividends in a manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the bankruptcy trustee serves a notice under sub-section (1) and the person on whom the`
  line `notice is served does not file a proof of security within thirty days after the date of service of the notice,`
  line `the bankruptcy trustee may, with leave of the Adjudicating Authority, sell or dispose of any property that`
  line `was subject to the security, free of that security.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (951)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 196
  title `Proof of debt by secured creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=951&sectionno=172&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a secured creditor realises his security, he may`
  line `produce proof of the balance due to him.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a secured creditor surrenders his security to the bankruptcy trustee for the general benefit`
  line `of the creditors, he may produce proof of his whole claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (952)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 197
  title `Mutual credit and set-off.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=952&sectionno=173&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where before the bankruptcy commencement date, there have`
  line `been mutual dealings between the bankrupt and any creditor, the bankruptcy trustee shall—`
  line
  line `(a) take an account of what is due from each party to the other in respect of the mutual dealings`
  line `and the sums due from one party shall be set-off against the sums due from the other; and`
  line
  line `(b) only the balance shall be provable as a bankruptcy debt or as the amount payable to the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee as part of the estate of the bankrupt.`
  line
  line `(2) Sums due from the bankrupt to another party shall not be included in the account taken by the`
  line `bankruptcy trustee under sub-section (1), if that other party had notice at the time they became due that an`
  line `application for bankruptcy relating to the bankrupt was pending.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (953)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 198
  title `Distribution of interim dividend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=953&sectionno=174&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the bankruptcy trustee has sufficient funds in`
  line `his hand, he may declare and distribute interim dividend among the creditors in respect of the bankruptcy`
  line `debts which they have respectively proved.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the bankruptcy trustee has declared any interim dividend, he shall give notice of such`
  line `dividend and the manner in which it is proposed to be distributed.`
  line
  line `(3) In the calculation and distribution of the interim dividend, the bankruptcy trustee shall make`
  line `provision for—`
  line
  line `(a) any bankruptcy debts which appear to him to be due to persons who, by reason of the distance`
  line `of their place of residence, may not have had sufficient time to tender and establish their debts; and`
  line
  line `(b) any bankruptcy debts which are subject of claims which have not yet been determined;`
  line
  line `(c) disputed proofs and claims; and`
  line
  line `(d) expenses necessary for the administration of the estate of the bankrupt.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (954)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 199
  title `Distribution of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=954&sectionno=175&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `(1) The bankruptcy trustee may, with the approval of the committee`
  line `of creditors, divide in its existing form amongst the creditors, according to its estimated value, any`
  line `property in its existing form which from its peculiar nature or other special circumstances cannot be`
  line `readily or advantageously sold.`
  line
  line `(2) An approval under sub-section (1) shall be sought by the bankruptcy trustee for each transaction,`
  line `and a person dealing with the bankruptcy trustee in good faith and for value shall not be required to`
  line `enquire whether any approval required under sub-section (1) has been given.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the bankruptcy trustee has done anything without the approval of the committee of`
  line `creditors, the committee may, for the purpose of enabling him to meet his expenses out of the estate of the`
  line `bankrupt, ratify the act of the bankruptcy trustee.`
  line
  line `(4) The committee of the creditors shall not ratify the act of the bankruptcy trustee under`
  line `sub-section (3) unless it is satisfied that the bankruptcy trustee acted in a case of urgency and has sought`
  line `its ratification without undue delay.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (955)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 200
  title `Final dividend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=955&sectionno=176&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the bankruptcy trustee has realised the entire estate of the bankrupt`
  line `or so much of it as could be realised in the opinion of the bankruptcy trustee, he shall give notice—`
  line
  line `(a) of his intention to declare a final dividend; or`
  line
  line `(b) that no dividend or further dividend shall be declared.`
  line
  line `(2) The notice under sub-section (1) shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed and shall`
  line `require all claims against the estate of the bankrupt to be established by a final date specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Authority may, on the application of any person interested in the administration`
  line `of the estate of the bankrupt, postpone the final date referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) After the final date referred to in sub-section (2), the bankruptcy trustee shall—`
  line
  line `(a) defray any outstanding expenses of the bankruptcy out of the estate of the bankrupt; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he intends to declare a final dividend, declare and distribute that dividend among the`
  line `creditors who have proved their debts, without regard to the claims of any other persons.`
  line
  line `(5) If a surplus remains after payment in full with interest to all the creditors of the bankrupt and the`
  line `payment of the expenses of the bankruptcy, the bankrupt shall be entitled to the surplus.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a bankruptcy order has been passed in respect of one partner in a firm, a creditor to whom`
  line `the bankrupt is indebted jointly with the other partners in the firm or any of them shall not receive any`
  line `dividend out of the separate property of the bankrupt until all the separate creditors have received the full`
  line `amount of their respective debts.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (956)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 201
  title `Claims of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=956&sectionno=177&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `(1) A creditor who has not proved his debt before the declaration of any`
  line `dividend is not entitled to disturb, by reason that he has not participated in it, the distribution of that`
  line `dividend or any other dividend declared before his debt was proved, but—`
  line
  line `(a) when he has proved the debt, he shall be entitled to be paid any dividend or dividends which`
  line `he has failed to receive, out of any money for the time being available for the payment of any further`
  line `dividend; and`
  line
  line `(b) any dividend or dividends payable to him shall be paid before that money is applied to the`
  line `payment of any such further dividend.`
  line
  line `(2) No action shall lie against the bankruptcy trustee for a dividend, but if the bankruptcy trustee`
  line `refuses to pay a dividend payable under sub-section (1), the Adjudicating Authority may order him to—`
  line
  line `(a) pay the dividend; and Final dividend.`
  line
  line `(b) pay, out of his own money—`
  line
  line `(i) interest on the dividend; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the costs of the proceedings in which the order to pay has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (957)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 202
  title `Priority of payment of debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=957&sectionno=178&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any`
  line `law enacted by the Parliament or the State Legislature for the time being in force, in the distribution of the`
  line `final dividend, the following debts shall be paid in priority to all other debts—`
  line
  line `(a) firstly, the costs and expenses incurred by the bankruptcy trustee for the bankruptcy process in`
  line full;
  line
  line `(b) secondly,—`
  line
  line `(i) the workmen's dues for the period of twenty-four months preceding the bankruptcy`
  line `commencement date; and`
  line
  line `(ii) debts owed to secured creditors;`
  line
  line `(c) thirdly, wages and any unpaid dues owed to employees, other than workmen, of the bankrupt`
  line `for the period of twelve months preceding the bankruptcy commencement date;`
  line
  line `(d) fourthly, any amount due to the Central Government and the State Government including the`
  line `amount to be received on account of Consolidated Fund of India and the Consolidated Fund of a`
  line `State, if any, in respect of the whole or any part of the period of two years preceding the bankruptcy`
  line `commencement date;`
  line
  line `(e) lastly, all other debts and dues owed by the bankrupt including unsecured debts.`
  line
  line `(2) The debts in each class specified in sub-section (1) shall rank in the order mentioned in that`
  line `sub-section but debts of the same class shall rank equally amongst themselves, and shall be paid in full,`
  line `unless the estate of the bankrupt is insufficient to meet them, in which case they shall abate in equal`
  line `proportions between themselves.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any creditor has given any indemnity or has made any payment of moneys by virtue of`
  line `which any asset of the bankrupt has been recovered, protected or preserved, the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `may make such order as it thinks just with respect to the distribution of such asset with a view to giving`
  line `that creditor an advantage over other creditors in consideration of the risks taken by him in so doing.`
  line
  line `(4) Unsecured creditors shall rank equally amongst themselves unless contractually agreed to the`
  line `contrary by such creditors.`
  line
  line `(5) Any surplus remaining after the payment of the debts under sub-section (1) shall be applied in`
  line `paying interest on those debts in respect of the periods during which they have been outstanding since the`
  line `bankruptcy commencement date.`
  line
  line `(6) Interest payments under sub-section (5) shall rank equally irrespective of the nature of the debt.`
  line
  line `(7) In the case of partners, the partnership property shall be applicable in the first instance in payment`
  line `of the partnership debts and the separate property of each partner shall be applicable in the first instance`
  line `in payment of his separate debts.`
  line
  line `(8) Where there is a surplus of the separate property of the partners, it shall be dealt with as part of the`
  line `partnership property; and where there is a surplus of the partnership property, it shall be dealt with as part`
  line `of the respective separate property in proportion to the rights and interests of each partner in the`
  line `partnership property`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (958)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 203
  title `Adjudicating authority for individuals and partnership firms.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=958&sectionno=179&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions`
  line `of section 60, the Adjudicating Authority, in relation to insolvency matters of individuals and firms shall`
  line `be the Debt Recovery Tribunal having territorial jurisdiction over the place where the individual debtor`
  line `actually and voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally works for gain and can entertain an`
  line `application under this Code regarding such person.`
  line
  line `(2) The Debt Recovery Tribunal shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, have jurisdiction to entertain or dispose of—`
  line
  line `(a) any suit or proceeding by or against the individual debtor;`
  line
  line `(b) any claim made by or against the individual debtor;`
  line
  line `(c) any question of priorities or any other question whether of law or facts, arising out of or in`
  line `relation to insolvency and bankruptcy of the individual debtor or firm under this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Limitation Act, 1963 (14 of 1963) or in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, in computing the period of limitation specified for any suit or application in`
  line `the name and on behalf of a debtor for which an order of moratorium has been made under this Part, the`
  line `period during which such moratorium is in place shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (959)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 204
  title `Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=959&sectionno=180&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) No civil court or authority shall have jurisdiction to`
  line `entertain any suit or proceedings in respect of any matter on which the Debt Recovery Tribunal or the`
  line `Debt Recovery Appellate Tribunal has jurisdiction under this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) No injunction shall be granted by any court, tribunal or authority in respect of any action taken, or`
  line `to be taken, in pursuance of any power conferred on the Debt Recovery Tribunal or the Debt Recovery`
  line `Appellate Tribunal by or under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (960)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 205
  title `Appeal to Debt Recovery Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=960&sectionno=181&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal from an order of the Debt`
  line `Recovery Tribunal under this Code shall be filed within thirty days before the Debt Recovery Appellate`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(2) The Debt Recovery Appellate Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that a person was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from filing an appeal within thirty days, allow the appeal to be filed within a further`
  line `period not exceeding fifteen days.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (961)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 206
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=961&sectionno=182&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal from an order of the Debt Recovery Appellate`
  line `Tribunal on a question of law under this Code shall be filed within forty-five days before the Supreme`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(2) The Supreme Court may, if it is satisfied that a person was prevented by sufficient cause from`
  line `filing an appeal within forty-five days, allow the appeal to be filed within a further period not exceeding`
  line `fifteen days.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (962)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 207
  title `Expeditious disposal of applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=962&sectionno=183&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `Where an application is not disposed of or order is not`
  line `passed within the period specified in this Code, the Debt Recovery Tribunal or the Debt Recovery`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, shall record the reasons for not doing so within the period so`
  line `specified; and the Chairperson of the Debt Recovery Appellate Tribunal, after taking into account the`
  line `reasons so recorded, extend the period specified in this Code, but not exceeding ten days.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (963)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 208
  title `Punishment for false information, etc., by creditor in insolvency resolution process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=963&sectionno=184&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `a debtor or creditor provides information which is false in any material particulars to the resolution`
  line `professional, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with`
  line `fine which may extend to five lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If a creditor promises to vote in favour of the repayment plan dishonestly by accepting any`
  line `money, property or security from the debtor, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to three times the amount or its equivalent of`
  line `such money, property or security accepted by such creditor, as the case may be, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such amount is not quantifiable, the total amount of fine shall not exceed five`
  line `lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (964)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 209
  title `Punishment for contravention of provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=964&sectionno=185&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `If an insolvency professional deliberately`
  line `contravenes the provisions of this Part, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months, or with fine, which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend to five`
  line `lakhs rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (965)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 210
  title `Punishment for false information, concealment, etc., by bankrupt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=965&sectionno=186&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `If the bankrupt—`
  line
  line `(a) knowingly makes a false representation or wilfully omits or conceals any material information`
  line `while making an application for bankruptcy under section 122 or while providing any information`
  line `during the bankruptcy process, he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of clause (a), a false representation or omission includes nondisclosure`
  line `of the details of disposal of any property, which but for the disposal, would be comprised`
  line `in the estate of the bankrupt, other than dispositions made in the ordinary course of business carried`
  line `on by the bankrupt;`
  line
  line `(b) fraudulently has failed to provide or deliberately withheld the production of, destroyed,`
  line `falsified or altered, his books of account, financial information and other records under his custody or`
  line `control, he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to one year, or with fine, which`
  line `may extend to five lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(c) has contravened the restrictions under section 140 or the provisions of section 141, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, which may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(d) has failed to deliver the possession of any property comprised in the estate of the bankrupt`
  line `under his possession or control, which he is required to deliver under section 156, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, which may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(e) has failed to account, without any reasonable cause or satisfactory explanation, for any loss`
  line `incurred of any substantial part of his property comprised in the estate of the bankrupt from the date`
  line `which is twelve months before the filing of the bankruptcy application, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, which may extend to three`
  line `times of the value of the loss, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that that where such loss is not quantifiable, the total amount of fine imposed shall not`
  line `exceed five lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(f) has absconded or attempts to absconds after the bankruptcy commencement date, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, which may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this clause, a bankrupt shall be deemed to have absconded if`
  line `he leaves, or attempts to leave the country without delivering the possession of any property which he`
  line `is required to deliver to the bankruptcy trustee under section 156.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (966)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 211
  title `Punishment for certain actions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=966&sectionno=187&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `If a bankruptcy trustee,—`
  line
  line `(a) has fraudulently misapplied, retained or accounted for any money or property comprised in`
  line `the estate of the bankrupt; or`
  line
  line `(b) has wilfully acted in a manner that the estate of the bankrupt has suffered any loss in`
  line `consequence of breach of any duty of the bankruptcy trustee in carrying out his functions under`
  line `section 149,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, which`
  line `shall not be less than three times the amount of the loss caused, or likely to have been caused, to persons`
  line `concerned on account of such contravention, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such loss or unlawful gain is not quantifiable, the total amount of fine imposed`
  line `shall not exceed five lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the bankruptcy trustee shall not be liable under this section if he seizes or`
  line `disposes of any property which is not comprised in the estate of the bankrupt and at that time had`
  line `reasonable grounds to believe that he is entitled to seize or dispose that property.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (967)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 212
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=967&sectionno=188&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be established, for the purposes of this Code, a`
  line `Board by the name of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Code, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Board shall be at such place in the National Capital Region, as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the expression “National Capital Region” shall have`
  line `the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (f) of section 2 of the National Capital Region Planning`
  line `Board Act, 1985 (2 of 1985).`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may establish offices at other places in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (968)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 213
  title `Constitution of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=968&sectionno=189&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall consist of the following members who shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) three members from amongst the officers of the Central Government not below the rank of`
  line `Joint Secretary or equivalent, one each to represent the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Corporate`
  line `Affairs and Ministry of Law, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) one member to be nominated by the Reserve Bank of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) five other members to be nominated by the Central Government, of whom at least three shall`
  line `be the whole-time members.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and the other members shall be persons of ability, integrity and standing, who`
  line `have shown capacity in dealing with problems relating to insolvency or bankruptcy and have special`
  line `knowledge and experience in the field of law, finance, economics, accountancy or administration.`
  line
  line `(3) The appointment of the Chairperson and the members of the Board other than the appointment of`
  line `an ex officio member under this section shall be made after obtaining the recommendation of a selection`
  line `committee consisting of—`
  line
  line `(a) Cabinet Secretary— Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary to the Government of India to be nominated by the Central Government— Member;`
  line
  line `(c) Chairperson of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India (in case of selection of`
  line `members of the Board)— Member;`
  line
  line `(d) three experts of repute from the field of finance, law, management, insolvency and related`
  line `subjects, to be nominated by the Central Government— Members.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of the Chairperson and members (other than ex officio members) shall be five`
  line `years or till they attain the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier, and they shall be eligible for`
  line reappointment.
  line
  line `(5) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and members (other than the ex officio members) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (969)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 214
  title `Removal of member from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=969&sectionno=190&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may remove a member from`
  line `office if he—`
  line
  line `(a) is an undischarged bankrupt as defined under Part III;`
  line
  line `(b) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a member;`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence, which in the opinion of the Central Government involves`
  line `moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(d) has, so abused his position as to render his continuation in office detrimental to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no member shall be removed under clause (d) unless he has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (970)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 215
  title `Powers of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=970&sectionno=191&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise determined by regulations, the Chairperson shall`
  line `have powers of general superintendence and direction of the affairs of the Board and may also exercise`
  line `such other powers as may be delegated to him by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (971)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 216
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=971&sectionno=192&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places, and observe such rules`
  line `of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including quorum at such meetings)`
  line `as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson, or if, for any reason, the Chairperson is unable to attend any meeting of the`
  line `Board, any other member chosen by the members present at the meeting shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority`
  line `votes of the members present and voting, and, in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson, or in`
  line `his absence, the person presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (972)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 217
  title `Member not to participate in meetings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=972&sectionno=193&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `Any member, who is a director of a`
  line `company and who as such director has any direct or indirect pecuniary interest in any matter coming up`
  line `for consideration at a meeting of the Board, shall, as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have`
  line `come to his knowledge, disclose the nature of his interest at such meeting and such disclosure shall be`
  line `recorded in the proceedings of the Board, and the member shall not take any part in any deliberation or`
  line `decision of the Board with respect to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (973)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 218
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Board, Officers and employees of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=973&sectionno=194&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or proceeding of the Board shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board not affecting the merits of the case.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may appoint such other officers and employees as it considers necessary for the`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions in such manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, officers and`
  line `employees of the Board appointed under sub-section (2) shall be such as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (974)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 219
  title `Power to designate financial sector regulator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=974&sectionno=195&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `Until the Board is established, the Central`
  line `Government may by notification, designate any financial sector regulator to exercise the powers and`
  line `functions of the Board under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (975)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 220
  title `Powers and functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=975&sectionno=196&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall, subject to the general direction of the`
  line `Central Government, perform all or any of the following functions namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) register insolvency professional agencies, insolvency professionals and information utilities`
  line `and renew, withdraw, suspend or cancel such registrations;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(aa) promote the development of, and regulate, the working and practices of, insolvency`
  line `professionals, insolvency professional agencies and information utilities and other institutions, in`
  line `furtherance of the purposes of this Code;]`
  line
  line `(b) specify the minimum eligibility requirements for registration of insolvency professional`
  line `agencies, insolvency professionals and information utilities;`
  line
  line `(c) levy fee or other charges ^2`
  line `[for carrying out the purposes of this Code, including fee for`
  line `registration and renewal] of insolvency professional agencies, insolvency professionals and`
  line `information utilities;`
  line
  line `(d) specify by regulations standards for the functioning of insolvency professional agencies,`
  line `insolvency professionals and information utilities;`
  line
  line `(e) lay down by regulations the minimum curriculum for the examination of the insolvency`
  line `professionals for their enrolment as members of the insolvency professional agencies;`
  line
  line `(f) carry out inspections and investigations on insolvency professional agencies, insolvency`
  line `professionals and information utilities and pass such orders as may be required for compliance of the`
  line `provisions of this Code and the regulations issued hereunder;`
  line
  line `(g) monitor the performance of insolvency professional agencies, insolvency professionals and`
  line `information utilities and pass any directions as may be required for compliance of the provisions of`
  line `this Code and the regulations issued hereunder;`
  line
  line `(h) call for any information and records from the insolvency professional agencies, insolvency`
  line `professionals and information utilities;`
  line
  line `(i) publish such information, data, research studies and other information as may be specified by`
  line regulations;
  line
  line `(j) specify by regulations the manner of collecting and storing data by the information utilities`
  line `and for providing access to such data;`
  line
  line `(k) collect and maintain records relating to insolvency and bankruptcy cases and disseminate`
  line `information relating to such cases;`
  line
  line `(l) constitute such committees as may be required including in particular the committees laid`
  line `down in section 197;`
  line
  line `(m) promote transparency and best practices in its governance;`
  line
  line `(n) maintain websites and such other universally accessible repositories of electronic information`
  line `as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(o) enter into memorandum of understanding with any other statutory authorities;`
  line
  line `(p) issue necessary guidelines to the insolvency professional agencies, insolvency professionals`
  line `and information utilities;`
  line
  line `(q) specify mechanism for redressal of grievances against insolvency professionals, insolvency`
  line `professional agencies and information utilities and pass orders relating to complaints filed against the`
  line `aforesaid for compliance of the provisions of this Code and the regulations issued hereunder;`
  line
  line `(r) conduct periodic study, research and audit the functioning and performance of to the`
  line `insolvency professional agencies, insolvency professionals and information utilities at such intervals`
  line `as may be specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(s) specify mechanisms for issuing regulations, including the conduct of public consultation`
  line `processes before notification of any regulations;`
  line
  line `(t) make regulations and guidelines on matters relating to insolvency and bankruptcy as may be`
  line `required under this Code, including mechanism for time bound disposal of the assets of the corporate`
  line `debtor or debtor; and`
  line
  line `(u) perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may make model bye-laws to be to adopted by insolvency professional agencies which`
  line `may provide for—`
  line
  line `(a) the minimum standards of professional competence of the members of insolvency`
  line `professional agencies;`
  line
  line `(b) the standards for professional and ethical conduct of the members of insolvency professional`
  line agencies;
  line
  line `(c) requirements for enrolment of persons as members of insolvency professional agencies which`
  line `shall be non-discriminatory;`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this clause, the term “non-discriminatory” means lack of`
  line `discrimination on the grounds of religion, caste, gender or place of birth and such other grounds as`
  line `may be specified;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of granting membership;`
  line
  line `(e) setting up of a governing board for internal governance and management of insolvency`
  line `professional agency in accordance with the regulations specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) the information required to be submitted by members including the form and the time for`
  line `submitting such information;`
  line
  line `(g) the specific classes of persons to whom services shall be provided at concessional rates or for`
  line `no remuneration by members;`
  line
  line `(h) the grounds on which penalties may be levied upon the members of insolvency professional`
  line `agencies and the manner thereof;`
  line
  line `(i) a fair and transparent mechanism for redressal of grievances against the members of`
  line `insolvency professional agencies;`
  line
  line `(j) the grounds under which the insolvency professionals may be expelled from the membership`
  line `of insolvency professional agencies;`
  line
  line `(k) the quantum of fee and the manner of collecting fee for inducting persons as its members;`
  line
  line `(l) the procedure for enrolment of persons as members of insolvency professional agency;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of conducting examination for enrolment of insolvency professionals;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of monitoring and reviewing the working of insolvency professional who are`
  line members;
  line
  line `(o) the duties and other activities to be performed by members;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of conducting disciplinary proceedings against its members and imposing`
  line penalties;
  line
  line `(q) the manner of utilising the amount received as penalty imposed against any insolvency`
  line professional.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, while exercising`
  line `the powers under this Code, the Board shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the discovery and production of books of account and other documents, at such place and such`
  line `time as may be specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(iii) inspection of any books, registers and other documents of any person at any place;`
  line
  line `(iv) issuing of commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s 32 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018)`
  line
  line `2 Subs by s 32, ibid, for "for the registration" (w.e.f. 6-6-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (976)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 221
  title `Constitution of advisory committee, executive committee or other committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=976&sectionno=197&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `The Board`
  line `may, for the efficient discharge of its functions, may constitute advisory and executive committees or`
  line `such other committees, as it may deem fit, consisting of a Chairperson and such other members as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (977)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 222
  title `Condonation of delay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=977&sectionno=198&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Code, where the Board`
  line `does not perform any act within the period specified under this Code, the relevant Adjudicating Authority`
  line `may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, condone the delay.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (978)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 223
  title `No person to function as insolvency professional agency without valid certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=978&sectionno=199&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Code, no person shall carry on its business as`
  line `insolvency professional agencies under this Code and enrol insolvency professionals as its members`
  line `except under and in accordance with a certificate of registration issued in this behalf by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (979)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 224
  title `Principles governing registration of insolvency professional agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=979&sectionno=200&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall have`
  line `regard to the following principles while registering the insolvency professional agencies under this Code,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to promote the professional development of and regulation of insolvency professionals;`
  line
  line `(b) to promote the services of competent insolvency professionals to cater to the needs of debtors,`
  line `creditors and such other persons as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(c) to promote good professional and ethical conduct amongst insolvency professionals;`
  line
  line `(d) to protect the interests of debtors, creditors and such other persons as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(e) to promote the growth of insolvency professional agencies for the effective resolution of`
  line `insolvency and bankruptcy processes under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (980)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 225
  title `Registration of insolvency professional agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=980&sectionno=201&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for registration shall`
  line `be made to the Board in such form and manner, containing such particulars, and accompanied by such`
  line `fee, as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that every application received by the Board shall be acknowledged within seven days of its`
  line receipt.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the application under sub-section (1), the Board may, on being satisfied that the`
  line `application conforms with all requirements specified under sub-section (1), grant a certificate of`
  line `registration to the applicant or else, reject, by order, such application:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order rejecting the application shall be made without giving an opportunity of being`
  line `heard to the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every order so made shall be communicated to the applicant within a period of`
  line `fifteen days.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may issue a certificate of registration to the applicant in such form and manner and`
  line `subject to such terms and conditions as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may renew the certificate of registration from time to time in such manner and on`
  line `payment of such fee as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may, by order, suspend or cancel the certificate of registration granted to an insolvency`
  line `professional agency on any of the following grounds, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) that it has obtained registration by making a false statement or misrepresentation or by any`
  line `other unlawful means;`
  line
  line `(b) that it has failed to comply with the requirements of the regulations made by the Board or`
  line `bye-laws made by the insolvency professional agency;`
  line
  line `(c) that it has contravened any of the provisions of the Act or the rules or the regulations made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(d) on any other ground as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this sub-section unless the insolvency professional agency`
  line `concerned has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such order shall be passed by any member except whole-time members of the`
  line Board.
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (981)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 226
  title `Appeal to National Company Law Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=981&sectionno=202&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `Any insolvency professional agency`
  line `which is aggrieved by the order of the Board made under section 201 may prefer an appeal to the National`
  line `Company Law Appellate Tribunal in such form, within such period, and in such manner, as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (982)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 227
  title `Governing Board of insolvency professional agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=982&sectionno=203&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, for the purposes of`
  line `ensuring that every insolvency professional agency takes into account the objectives sought to be`
  line `achieved under this Code, make regulations to specify—`
  line
  line `(a) the setting up of a governing board of an insolvency professional agency;`
  line
  line `(b) the minimum number of independent members to be on the governing board of the insolvency`
  line `professional agency; and`
  line
  line `(c) the number of the insolvency professionals being its members who shall be on the governing`
  line `board of the insolvency professional agency.`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (983)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 228
  title `Functions of insolvency professional agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=983&sectionno=204&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `An insolvency professional agency shall`
  line `perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) grant membership to persons who fulfil all requirements set out in its byelaws on payment of`
  line `membership fee;`
  line
  line `(b) lay down standards of professional conduct for its members;`
  line
  line `(c) monitor the performance of its members;`
  line
  line `(d) safeguard the rights, privileges and interests of insolvency professionals who are its members;`
  line
  line `(e) suspend or cancel the membership of insolvency professionals who are its members on the`
  line `grounds set out in its bye-laws;`
  line
  line `(f) redress the grievances of consumers against insolvency professionals who are its members;`
  line and
  line
  line `(g) publish information about its functions, list of its members, performance of its members and`
  line `such other information as may be specified by regulations/`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (984)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 229
  title `Insolvency professional agencies to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=984&sectionno=205&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Code`
  line `and any rules or regulations made thereunder and after obtaining the approval of the Board, every`
  line `insolvency professional agency shall make bye-laws consistent with the model bye-laws specified by the`
  line `Board under sub-section (2) of section 196.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (985)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 230
  title `Enrolled and registered persons to act as insolvency professionals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=985&sectionno=206&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `No person shall render`
  line `his services as insolvency professional under this Code without being enrolled as a member of an`
  line `insolvency professional agency and registered with the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (986)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 231
  title `Registration of insolvency professionals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=986&sectionno=207&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every insolvency professional shall, after`
  line `obtaining the membership of any insolvency professional agency, register himself with the Board within`
  line `such time, in such manner and on payment of such fee, as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may specify the categories of professionals or persons possessing such qualifications`
  line `and experience in the field of finance, law, management, insolvency or such other field, as it deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (987)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 232
  title `Functions and obligations of insolvency professionals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 14 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=987&sectionno=208&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any insolvency resolution,`
  line `fresh start, liquidation or bankruptcy process has been initiated, it shall be the function of an insolvency`
  line `professional to take such actions as may be necessary, in the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) a fresh start order process under Chapter II of Part III;`
  line
  line `(b) individual insolvency resolution process under Chapter III of Part III;`
  line
  line `(c) corporate insolvency resolution process under Chapter II of Part II;`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) pre-packaged insolvency resolution process under Chapter III-A of Part II;]`
  line
  line `(d) individual bankruptcy process under Chapter IV of Part III; and`
  line
  line `(e) liquidation of a corporate debtor firm under Chapter III of Part II.`
  line
  line 1
  line `^1[(1A) Where the name of the insolvency professional proposed to be appointed as a resolution`
  line `professional, is approved under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 54A, it shall be the function of`
  line `such insolvency professional to take such actions as may be necessary to perform his functions and duties`
  line `prior to the initiation of the pre-packaged insolvency resolution process under Chapter III-A of Part II.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every insolvency professional shall abide by the following code of conduct:`
  line
  line `(a) to take reasonable care and diligence while performing his duties;`
  line
  line `(b) to comply with all requirements and terms and conditions specified in the bye-laws of the`
  line `insolvency professional agency of which he is a member;`
  line
  line `(c) to allow the insolvency professional agency to inspect his records;`
  line
  line `(d) to submit a copy of the records of every proceeding before the Adjudicating Authority to the`
  line `Board as well as to the insolvency professional agency of which he is a member; and`
  line
  line `(e) to perform his functions in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (988)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 233
  title `No person to function as information utility without certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=988&sectionno=209&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `Save as`
  line `otherwise provided in this Code, no person shall carry on its business as information utility under this`
  line `Code without a certificate of registration issued in that behalf by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (989)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 234
  title `Registration of information utility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=989&sectionno=210&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for registration shall be made to the`
  line `Board in such form and manner, containing such particulars, and accompanied by such fee, as may be`
  line `specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that every application received by the Board shall be acknowledged within seven days of its`
  line receipt.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the application under sub-section (1), the Board may, on being satisfied that the`
  line `application conforms to all requirements specified under sub-section (1), grant a certificate of registration`
  line `to the applicant or else, reject, by order, such application.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may issue a certificate of registration to the applicant in such form and manner and`
  line `subject to such terms and conditions as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may renew the certificate of registration from time to time in such manner and on`
  line `payment of such fee as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may, by order, suspend or cancel the certificate of registration granted to an`
  line `information utility on any of the following grounds, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) that it has obtained registration by making a false statement or misrepresentation or any other`
  line `unlawful means;`
  line
  line `(b) that it has failed to comply with the requirements of the regulations made by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) that it has contravened any of the provisions of the Act or the rules or the regulations made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(d) on any other ground as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this sub-section unless the information utility concerned`
  line `has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such order shall be passed by any member except whole-time members of the`
  line Board.
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (990)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 235
  title `Appeal to National Company Law Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=990&sectionno=211&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `Any information utility which is`
  line `aggrieved by the order of the Board made under section 210 may prefer an appeal to the National`
  line `Company Law Appellate Tribunal in such form, within such period, and in such manner, as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (991)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 236
  title `Governing Board of information utility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=991&sectionno=212&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, for ensuring that an information`
  line `utility takes into account the objectives sought to be achieved under this Code, require every information`
  line `utility to set up a governing board, with such number of independent members, as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (992)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 237
  title `Core services, etc., of information utilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=992&sectionno=213&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line `An information utility shall provide such services`
  line `as may be specified including core services to any person if such person complies with the terms and`
  line `conditions as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (993)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 238
  title `Obligations of information utility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=993&sectionno=214&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of providing core services to any person,`
  line `every information utility shall—`
  line
  line `(a) create and store financial information in a universally accessible format;`
  line
  line `(b) accept electronic submissions of financial information from persons who are under obligations`
  line `to submit financial information under sub-section (1) of section 215, in such form and manner as may`
  line `be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) accept, in specified form and manner, electronic submissions of financial information from`
  line `persons who intend to submit such information;`
  line
  line `(d) meet such minimum service quality standards as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(e) get the information received from various persons authenticated by all concerned parties`
  line `before storing such information;`
  line
  line `(f) provide access to the financial information stored by it to any person who intends to access`
  line `such information in such manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(g) publish such statistical information as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(h) have inter-operatability with other information utilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (994)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 239
  title `Procedure for submission, etc., of financial information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=994&sectionno=215&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who intends to`
  line `submit financial information to the information utility or access the information from the information`
  line `utility shall pay such fee and submit information in such form and manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) A financial creditor shall submit financial information and information relating to assets in`
  line `relation to which any security interest has been created, in such form and manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(3) An operational creditor may submit financial information to the information utility in such form`
  line `and manner as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (995)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 240
  title `Rights and obligations of persons submitting financial information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=995&sectionno=216&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person who`
  line `intends to update or modify or rectify errors in the financial information submitted under section 215, he`
  line `may make an application to the information utility for such purpose stating reasons therefor, in such`
  line `manner and within such time, as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) A person who submits financial information to an information utility shall not provide such`
  line `information to any other person, except to such extent, under such circumstances, and in such manner, as`
  line `may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (996)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 241
  title `Complaints against insolvency professional agency or its member or information utility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=996&sectionno=217&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by the functioning of an insolvency professional agency or insolvency professional`
  line `or an information utility may file a complaint to the Board in such form, within such time and in such`
  line `manner as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (997)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 242
  title `Investigation of insolvency professional agency or its member or information utility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=997&sectionno=218&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Board, on receipt of a complaint under section 217 or has reasonable grounds to`
  line `believe that any insolvency professional agency or insolvency professional or an information utility has`
  line `contravened any of the provisions of the Code or the rules or regulations made or directions issued by the`
  line `Board thereunder, it may, at any time by an order in writing, direct any person or persons to act as an`
  line `investigating authority to conduct an inspection or investigation of the insolvency professional agency or`
  line `insolvency professional or an information utility.`
  line
  line `(2) The inspection or investigation carried out under sub-section (1) of this section shall be conducted`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Investigating Authority may, in the course of such inspection or investigation, require any`
  line `other person who is likely to have any relevant document, record or information to furnish the same, and`
  line `such person shall be bound to furnish such document, record or information:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Investigating Authority shall provide detailed reasons to such person before`
  line `requiring him to furnish such document, record or information.`
  line
  line `(4) The Investigating Authority may, in the course of its inspection or investigation, enter any`
  line `building or place where they may have reasons to believe that any such document, record or information`
  line `relating to the subject-matter of the inquiry may be found and may seize any such document, record or`
  line `information or take extracts or copies therefrom, subject to the provisions of section 100 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), insofar as they may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(5) The Investigating Authority shall keep in its custody the books, registers, other documents and`
  line `records seized under this section for such period not later than the conclusion of the investigation as it`
  line `considers necessary and thereafter shall return the same to the concerned person from whose custody or`
  line `power they were seized:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Investigating Authority may, before returning such books, registers, other`
  line `documents and record as aforesaid, place identification marks on them or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) A detailed report of inspection or investigation shall be submitted to the Board by the`
  line `Investigating Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (998)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 243
  title `Show cause notice to insolvency professional agency or its member or information utility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=998&sectionno=219&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, upon completion of an inspection or investigation under section 218, issue a`
  line `show cause notice to such insolvency professional agency or insolvency professional or information`
  line `utility, and carry out inspection of such insolvency professional agency or insolvency professional or`
  line `information utility in such manner, giving such time for giving reply, as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (999)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 244
  title `Appointment of disciplinary committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=999&sectionno=220&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall constitute a disciplinary`
  line `committee to consider the reports of the investigating Authority submitted under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 218:`
  line
  line `Provided that the members of the disciplinary committee shall consist of whole-time members of the`
  line `Board only.`
  line
  line `(2) On the examination of the report of the Investigating Authority, if the disciplinary committee is`
  line `satisfied that sufficient cause exists, it may impose penalty as specified in sub-section (3) or suspend or`
  line `cancel the registration of the insolvency professional or, suspend or cancel the registration of insolvency`
  line `professional agency or information utility as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any insolvency professional agency or insolvency professional or an information utility has`
  line `contravened any provision of this Code or rules or regulations made thereunder, the disciplinary`
  line `committee may impose penalty which shall be--`
  line
  line `(i) three times the amount of the loss caused, or likely to have been caused, to persons concerned`
  line `on account of such contravention; or`
  line
  line `(ii) three times the amount of the unlawful gain made on account of such contravention,`
  line
  line `whichever is higher:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such loss or unlawful gain is not quantifiable, the total amount of the penalty`
  line `imposed shall not exceed more than one crore rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), the Board may direct any person who has`
  line `made unlawful gain or averted loss by indulging in any activity in contravention of this Code, or the rules`
  line `or regulations made thereunder, to disgorge an amount equivalent to such unlawful gain or aversion of`
  line loss.
  line
  line `(5) The Board may take such action as may be required to provide restitution to the person who`
  line `suffered loss on account of any contravention from the amount so disgorged, if the person who suffered`
  line `such loss is identifiable and the loss so suffered is directly attributable to such person.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board may make regulations to specify--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for claiming restitution under sub-section (5);`
  line
  line `(b) the period within which such restitution may be claimed; and`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which restitution of amount may be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (1000)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 245
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1000&sectionno=221&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Board grants of such sums of money as that Government`
  line `may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (1001)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 246
  title `Board’s Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1001&sectionno=222&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the Fund of the Insolvency`
  line `and Bankruptcy Board and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(a) all grants, fees and charges received by the Board under this Code;`
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Board from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) such other funds as may be specified by the Board or prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting—`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and other employees`
  line `of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses of the Board in the discharge of its functions under section 196;`
  line
  line `(c) the expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Code;`
  line
  line `(d) such other purposes as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (1002)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 247
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1002&sectionno=223&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (1003)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 248
  title `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1003&sectionno=224&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed a Fund to be called the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Fund (hereafter in this section referred to as the "Fund") for the purposes of`
  line `insolvency resolution, liquidation and bankruptcy of persons under the Code.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be credited to the Fund the following amounts, namely—`
  line
  line `(a) the grants made by the Central Government for the purposes of the Fund;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount deposited by persons as contribution to the Fund;`
  line
  line `(c) the amount received in the Fund from any other source; and`
  line
  line `(d) the interest or other income received out of the investment made from the Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) A person who has contributed any amount to the Fund may, in the event of proceedings initiated`
  line `in respect of such person under this Code before an Adjudicating Authority, make an application to such`
  line `Adjudicating Authority for withdrawal of funds not exceeding the amount contributed by it, for making`
  line `payments to workmen, protecting the assets of such persons, meeting the incidental costs during the`
  line `proceedings or such other purposes as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall, by notification, appoint an administrator to administer the fund in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (1004)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 249
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1004&sectionno=225&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Code, the Board shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions`
  line `under this Code, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give`
  line `in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government as to whether a question is one of policy or not shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (1005)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 250
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1005&sectionno=226&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion—`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of grave emergency, the Board is unable to discharge the functions and duties`
  line `imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Code; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Board has persistently not complied with any direction issued by the Central`
  line `Government under this Code or in the discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or under`
  line `the provisions of this Code and as a result of such noncompliance the financial position of the Board`
  line `or the administration of the Board has deteriorated; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, supersede the Board for such period, not exceeding six`
  line `months, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Board,—`
  line
  line `(a) all the members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Code, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Board, shall until the Board is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the Central Government`
  line `may direct; and`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Board shall, until the Board is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government may reconstitute the Board by a fresh appointment and in such`
  line `case any person or persons who vacated their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2), shall not be`
  line `deemed disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time, before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, take action under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (1006)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 251
  title `Power of Central Government to notify financial service providers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1006&sectionno=227&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything to the contrary ^1[contained in this Code] or any other law for the time being in force, the Central Government may, if it considers necessary, in consultation with the appropriate financial sector`
  line `regulators, notify financial service providers or categories of financial service providers for the purpose of`
  line `their insolvency and liquidation proceedings, which may be conducted under this Code, in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the insolvency and liquidation`
  line `proceedings for financial service providers or categories of financial service providers may be conducted`
  line `with such modifications and in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2020, s. 11, for “examined in this Code” (w.e.f. 28-12-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 2020, s. 11 (w.e.f.28-12-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (1007)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 252
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1007&sectionno=228&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year as may`
  line `be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the`
  line `Board and forward the same to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (1008)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 253
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1008&sectionno=229&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial`
  line `year as may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous`
  line `financial year, and submit a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the report received under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (1009)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 254
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1009&sectionno=230&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order in writing delegate to any member or`
  line `officer of the Board subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers`
  line `and functions under this Code (except the powers under section 240, as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (1010)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 255
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 33, for "Adjudicating Authority" (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1010&sectionno=231&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter in which the`
  line `^1[ Adjudicating Authority or the Board] is empowered by, or under, this Code to pass any order and no injunction shall be`
  line `granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any`
  line `order passed by such [Adjudicating Authority or the Board] under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_232:
  sectionId (1011)
  sectionNo (232)
  orderNo 256
  title `Members, officers and employees of Board to the public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_232_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1011&sectionno=232&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson,`
  line `Members, officers and other employees of the Board shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in`
  line `pursuance of any of the provisions of this Code, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  sectionId (1012)
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 257
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1012&sectionno=233&orderno=257&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer of the Government, or the Chairperson, Member, officer or`
  line `other employee of the Board or an insolvency professional or liquidator for anything which is in done or`
  line `intended to be done in good faith under this Code or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  sectionId (1013)
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 258
  title `Agreements with foreign countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1013&sectionno=234&orderno=258&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may enter into an`
  line `agreement with the Government of any country outside India for enforcing the provisions of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the application of`
  line `provisions of this Code in relation to assets or property of corporate debtor or debtor, including a personal`
  line `guarantor of a corporate debtor, as the case may be, situated at any place in a country outside India with`
  line `which reciprocal arrangements have been made, shall be subject to such conditions as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  sectionId (1014)
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 259
  title `Letter of request to a country outside India in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1014&sectionno=235&orderno=259&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Code or any law for the time being in force if, in the course of insolvency resolution`
  line `process, or liquidation or bankruptcy proceedings, as the case may be, under this Code, the resolution`
  line `professional, liquidator or bankruptcy trustee, as the case may be, is of the opinion that assets of the`
  line `corporate debtor or debtor, including a personal guarantor of a corporate debtor, are situated in a country`
  line `outside India with which reciprocal arrangements have been made under section 234, he may make an`
  line `application to the Adjudicating Authority that evidence or action relating to such assets is required in`
  line `connection with such process or proceeding.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Authority on receipt of an application under sub-section (1) and, on being`
  line `satisfied that evidence or action relating to assets under sub-section (1) is required in connection with`
  line `insolvency resolution process or liquidation or bankruptcy proceeding, may issue a letter of request to a`
  line `court or an authority of such country competent to deal with such request.`
obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235_a:
  sectionId (48998)
  sectionNo 235A
  orderNo 260
  title `Punishment where no specific penalty or punishment is provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2018, s. 8 (w.e.f. 23-11-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=48998&sectionno=235A&orderno=260&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_235_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[235A. Punishment where no specific penalty or punishment is provided.--If any person`
  line `contravenes any of the provisions of this Code or the rules or regulations made thereunder for which no`
  line `penalty or punishment is provided in this Code, such person shall be punishable with fine which shall not`
  line `be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two crore rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_236:
  sectionId (1015)
  sectionNo (236)
  orderNo 261
  title `Trial of offences by Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_236_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1015&sectionno=236&orderno=261&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), offences under this Code shall be tried by the Special Court established`
  line `under Chapter XXVIII of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).`
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Act, save on a complaint`
  line `made by the Board or the Central Government or any person authorised by the Central Government in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to the`
  line `proceedings before a Special Court and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Court of Session and the person conducting a prosecution before a Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, in case of a`
  line `complaint under sub-section (2), the presence of the person authorised by the Central Government or the`
  line `Board before the Court trying the offences shall not be necessary unless the Court requires his personal`
  line `attendance at the trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  sectionId (1016)
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 262
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1016&sectionno=237&orderno=262&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  sectionId (1017)
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 263
  title `Provisions of this Code to override other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1017&sectionno=238&orderno=263&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Code shall have effect,`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `any instrument having effect by virtue of any such law.`
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238_a:
  sectionId (49000)
  sectionNo 238A
  orderNo 264
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 34 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=49000&sectionno=238A&orderno=264&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_238_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[238A. Limitation. --The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 shall, as far as may be, apply to`
  line `the proceedings or appeals before the Adjudicating Authority, the National Company Law Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, the Debt Recovery Tribunal or the Debt Recovery Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  sectionId (1018)
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 265
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_239_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1018&sectionno=239&orderno=265&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_239_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Central Government`
  line `may make rules for any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any other instrument which shall be a financial product under clause (15) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) other accounting standards which shall be a financial debt under clause (d) of sub-section (8)`
  line `of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the form, the manner and the fee for making application before the Adjudicating Authority for`
  line `initiating corporate insolvency resolution process by financial creditor under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and manner in which demand notice may be made and the manner of delivery`
  line `thereof to the corporate debtor under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) the form, the manner and the fee for making application before the Adjudicating Authority for`
  line `initiating corporate insolvency resolution process by operational creditor under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line `^1[(ea) other proof confirming that there is no payment of an unpaid operational debt by the`
  line `corporate debtor or such other information under clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 9;]`
  line
  line `(f) the form, the manner and the fee for making application before the Adjudicating Authority for`
  line `initiating corporate insolvency resolution process by corporate applicant under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `^2[(fa) the transactions under the second proviso to sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(fb) the transactions under Explanation I to clause (c) of section 29A;`
  line
  line `(fc) the transactions under the second proviso to clause (j) of section 29A;]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(fd) the form, particulars, manner and fee for making application before the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority under sub-section (2) of section 54C;`
  line
  line `(fe) the conditions and restrictions with which the promoters, members, personnel and partners of`
  line `the corporate debtor shall exercise and discharge contractual or statutory rights and obligations under`
  line `clause (c) of section 54H;]`
  line
  line `(g) the persons who shall be relative under clause (ii) of the Explanation to sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 79;`
  line
  line `(h) the value of unencumbered single dwelling unit owned by the debtor under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (13) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(i) the value under clause (c), and any other debt under clause (f), of sub-section (14) of`
  line `section 79;`
  line
  line `(j) the form, the manner and the fee for making application for fresh start order under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 81;`
  line
  line `(k) the particulars of the debtor's personal details under clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 81;`
  line
  line `(l) the information and documents to support application under sub-section (3) of section 86;`
  line
  line `(m) the form, the manner and the fee for making application for initiating the insolvency`
  line `resolution process by the debtor under sub-section (6) of section 94;`
  line
  line `(n) the form, the manner and the fee for making application for initiating the insolvency`
  line `resolution process by the creditor under sub-section (6) of section 95;`
  line
  line `(o) the particulars to be provided by the creditor to the resolution professional under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 103;`
  line
  line `(p) the form and the manner for making application for bankruptcy by the debtor under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 122;`
  line
  line `(q) the form and the manner of the statement of affairs of the debtor under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 122;`
  line
  line `(r) the other information under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 123;`
  line
  line `(s) the form, the manner and the fee for making application for bankruptcy under sub-section (6)`
  line `of section 123;`
  line
  line `(t) the form and the manner in which statement of financial position shall be submitted under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 129;`
  line
  line `(u) the matters and the details which shall be included in the public notice under sub-section (2)@/i`
  line `of section 130;`
  line
  line `(v) the matters and the details which shall be included in the notice to the creditors under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 130;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner of sending details of the claims to the bankruptcy trustee and other information`
  line `under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 131;`
  line
  line `(x) the value of financial or commercial transaction under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 141;`
  line
  line `(y) the other things to be done by a bankrupt to assist bankruptcy trustee in carrying out his`
  line `functions under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 150;`
  line
  line `(z) the manner of dealing with the surplus under sub-section (4) of section 170;`
  line
  line `(za) the form and the manner of proof of debt under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 171;`
  line
