  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1019&sectionno=240&orderno=266&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by notification, make regulations consistent`
  line `with this Code and the rules made thereunder, to carry out the provisions of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form and the manner of accepting electronic submission of financial information under`
  line `sub-clause (a) of clause (9) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the persons to whom access to information stored with the information utility may be`
  line `provided under sub-clause (d) of clause (9) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the other information under sub-clause (f) of clause (13) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the other costs under clause (e) of sub-section (13) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) the cost incurred by the liquidator during the period of liquidation which shall be liquidation`
  line `cost under sub-section (16) of section 5;`
  line
  line `^1[(ea) the other costs under sub-clause (e) of clause (23C) of section 5;]`
  line
  line `(f) the other record or evidence of default under clause (a), and any other information under`
  line `clause (c), of sub-section (3) of section 7;`
