obj_root_law_sections_240_a:
  sectionId (48999)
  sectionNo 240A
  orderNo 267
  title `Application of this Code to micro, small and medium enterprises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=48999&sectionno=240A&orderno=267&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_240_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[240A. Application of this Code to micro, small and medium enterprises.--(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in this Code, the provisions of clauses (c) and (h) of section 29A shall`
  line `not apply to the resolution applicant in respect of corporate insolvency resolution process ^2`
  line `[or prepackaged insolvency resolution process] of any micro,`
  line `small and medium enterprises.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to sub-section (1), the Central Government may, in the public interest, by notification,`
  line `direct that any of the provisions of this Code shall--`
  line
  line `(a) not apply to micro, small and medium enterprises; or`
  line
  line `(b) apply to micro, small and medium enterprises, with such modifications as may be specified in`
  line `the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) A draft of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (2), shall be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions.`
  line
  line `(4) If both Houses agree in disapproving the issue of notification or both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification, the notification shall not be issued or shall be issued only in such`
  line `modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) The period of thirty days referred to in sub-section (3) shall not include any period during which`
  line `the House referred to in sub-section (4) is prorogued or adjourned for more than four consecutive days.`
  line
  line `(6) Every notification issued under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression micro, small and medium enterprises`
  line `means any class or classes of enterprises classified as such under sub-section (1) of section 7 of the`
  line `Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act, 2006.]`
obj_root_law_sections_240_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2018, s. 37 (w.e.f. 6-6-2018).`
  line
  line `2.Ins. by Act 26 of 2021, s. 17 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_241:
  sectionId (1020)
  sectionNo (241)
  orderNo 268
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1020&sectionno=241&orderno=268&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Code shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_242:
  sectionId (1021)
  sectionNo (242)
  orderNo 269
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_242_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1021&sectionno=242&orderno=269&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_242_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Code, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Code as may appear to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of five years from the`
  line `commencement of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament`
obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes:
  string
  line
