  title `Repeal of certain enactments and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_243_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1022&sectionno=243&orderno=270&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_243_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Presidency Towns Insolvency`
  line `Act, 1909 (3 of 1909) and the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal under sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(i) all proceedings pending under and relating to the Presidency Towns Insolvency`
  line `Act, 1909 (3 of 1909), and the Provincial Insolvency Act 1920 (5 of 1920) immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Code shall continue to be governed under the aforementioned Acts and be`
  line `heard and disposed of by the concerned courts or tribunals, as if the aforementioned Acts have not`
  line `been repealed;`
  line
  line `(ii) any order, rule, notification, regulation, appointment, conveyance, mortgage, deed, document`
  line `or agreement made, fee directed, resolution passed, direction given, proceeding taken, instrument`
  line `executed or issued, or thing done under or in pursuance of any repealed enactment shall, if in force at`
  line `the commencement of this Code, continue to be in force, and shall have effect as if the`
  line `aforementioned Acts have not been repealed;`
  line
  line `(iii) anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or taken, including any`
  line `rule, notification, inspection, order or notice made or issued or any appointment or declaration made`
  line `or any operation undertaken or any direction given or any proceeding taken or any penalty,`
  line `punishment, forfeiture or fine imposed under the repealed enactments shall be deemed valid;`
  line
  line `(iv) any principle or rule of law, or established jurisdiction, form or course of pleading, practice`
  line `or procedure or existing usage, custom, privilege, restriction or exemption shall not be affected,`
  line `notwithstanding that the same respectively may have been in any manner affirmed or recognised or`
  line `derived by, in, or from, the repealed enactments;`
  line
  line `(v) any prosecution instituted under the repealed enactments and pending immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Code before any court or tribunal shall, subject to the provisions of this Code,`
  line `continue to be heard and disposed of by the concerned court or tribunal;`
  line
  line `(vi) any person appointed to any office under or by virtue of any repealed enactment shall`
  line `continue to hold such office until such time as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(vii) any jurisdiction, custom, liability, right, title, privilege, restriction, exemption, usage,`
  line `practice, procedure or other matter or thing not in existence or in force shall not be revised or`
  line restored.
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice the general`
  line `application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect of repeal`
  line `of the repealed enactments or provisions of the enactments mentioned in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_244:
  sectionId (1023)
  sectionNo (244)
  orderNo 271
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_244_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273&sectionId=1023&sectionno=244&orderno=271&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00055_201631_1517807328273
obj_root_law_sections_244_content:
  string
  line `(1) Until the Board is constituted or a financial sector regulator is`
  line `designated under section 195, as the case may be, the powers and functions of the Board or such`
  line `designated financial sector regulator, including its power to make regulations, shall be exercised by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the power under sub-section (1), the Central Government`
  line `may by regulations provide for the following matters:`
  line
  line `(a) recognition of persons, categories of professionals and persons having such qualifications and`
  line `experience in the field of finance, law, management or insolvency as it deems necessary, as`
  line `insolvency professionals and insolvency professional agencies under this Code;`
  line
  line `(b) recognition of persons with technological, statistical, and data protection capability as it`
  line `deems necessary, as information utilities under this Code; and`
  line
  line `(c) conduct of the corporate insolvency resolution process, insolvency resolution process,`
  line `liquidation process, fresh start process and bankruptcy process under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes:
  string
  line
